</table>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 208.2 Minimum Number.  The term “parking facility” is used Section 208.2 instead of the term “parking lot” so that it is clear that both parking lots and parking structures are required to comply with this section.  The number of parking spaces required to be accessible is to be calculated separately for each parking facility; the required number is not to be based on the total number of parking spaces provided in all of the parking facilities provided on the site.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-208_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.2.1 Hospital Outpatient Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ten percent of patient and visitor parking spaces provided to serve hospital outpatient facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 208.2.1 Hospital Outpatient Facilities.  The term “outpatient facility” is not defined in this document but is intended to cover facilities or units that are located in hospitals and that provide regular and continuing medical treatment without an overnight stay.  Doctors’ offices, independent clinics, or other facilities not located in hospitals are not considered hospital outpatient facilities for purposes of this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-208_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.2.2 Rehabilitation Facilities and Outpatient Physical Therapy Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Twenty percent of patient and visitor parking spaces provided to serve rehabilitation facilities specializing in treating conditions that affect mobility and outpatient physical therapy facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 208.2.2 Rehabilitation Facilities and Outpatient Physical Therapy Facilities.  Conditions that affect mobility include conditions requiring the use or assistance of a brace, cane, crutch, prosthetic device, wheelchair, or powered mobility aid; arthritic, neurological, or orthopedic conditions that severely limit one’s ability to walk; respiratory diseases and other conditions which may require the use of portable oxygen; and cardiac conditions that impose significant functional limitations.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-208_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.2.3 Residential Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking spaces provided to serve residential facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-208_2_3" class="navSectionLink">208.2.3</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-208_2_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.2.3.1 Parking for Residents[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where at least one parking space is provided for each residential dwelling unit, at least one parking space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided for each residential dwelling unit required to provide mobility features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_2" class="navSectionLink">809.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_4" class="navSectionLink">809.4</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-208_2_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.2.3.2 Additional Parking Spaces for Residents[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where the total number of parking spaces provided for each residential dwelling unit exceeds one parking space per residential dwelling unit, 2 percent, but no fewer than one space, of all the parking spaces not covered by 208.2.3.1 shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-208_2_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.2.3.3 Parking for Guests, Employees, and Other Non-Residents[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where parking spaces are provided for persons other than residents, parking shall be provided in accordance with Table 208.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-208_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.2.4 Van Parking Spaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]For every six or fraction of six parking spaces required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-208_2" class="navSectionLink">208.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]at least one shall be a van parking space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-208_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.3 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking facilities shall comply with 208.3[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-208_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.3.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking spaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]that serve a particular building or facility shall be located on the shortest accessible route from parking to an entrance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-206_4" class="navSectionLink">206.4</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where parking serves more than one accessible entrance, parking spaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be dispersed and located on the shortest accessible route to the accessible entrances.  In parking facilities that do not serve a particular building or facility, parking spaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be located on the shortest accessible route to an accessible pedestrian entrance of the parking facility.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-208_3_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  All van parking spaces shall be permitted to be grouped on one level within a multi-story parking facility.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-208_3_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Parking spaces shall be permitted to be located in different parking facilities if substantially equivalent or greater accessibility is provided in terms of distance from an accessible entrance or entrances, parking fee, and user convenience.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 208.3.1 General Exception 2.  Factors that could affect “user convenience” include, but are not limited to, protection from the weather, security, lighting, and comparative maintenance of the alternative parking site.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-208_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]208.3.2 Residential Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In residential facilities containing residential dwelling units required to provide mobility features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_2" class="navSectionLink">809.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_4" class="navSectionLink">809.4</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]parking spaces provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-208_2_3_1" class="navSectionLink">208.2.3.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be located on the shortest accessible route to the residential dwelling unit entrance they serve.  Spaces provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-208_2_3_2" class="navSectionLink">208.2.3.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be dispersed throughout all types of parking provided for the residential dwelling units.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Parking spaces provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-208_2_3_2" class="navSectionLink">208.2.3.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required to be dispersed throughout all types of parking if substantially equivalent or greater accessibility is provided in terms of distance from an accessible entrance, parking fee, and user convenience.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 208.3.2 Residential Facilities Exception.  Factors that could affect “user convenience” include, but are not limited to, protection from the weather, security, lighting, and comparative maintenance of the alternative parking site.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-209">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209 Passenger Loading Zones and Bus Stops[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-209_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Passenger loading zones shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-209" class="navSectionLink">209</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-209_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.2 Type[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, passenger loading zones shall comply with 209.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-209_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.2.1 Passenger Loading Zones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Passenger loading zones, except those required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-209_2_2" class="navSectionLink">209.2.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-209_2_3" class="navSectionLink">209.2.3</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall provide at least one passenger loading zone complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-503" class="navSectionLink">503</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]in every continuous 100 linear feet (30 m) of loading zone space, or fraction thereof.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-209_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.2.2 Bus Loading Zones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In bus loading zones restricted to use by designated or specified public transportation vehicles, each bus bay, bus stop, or other area designated for lift or ramp deployment shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_2" class="navSectionLink">810.2</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 209.2.2 Bus Loading Zones.  The terms “designated public transportation” and “specified public transportation” are defined by the Department of Transportation at 49 CFR 37.3 in regulations implementing the Americans with Disabilities Act.  These terms refer to public transportation services provided by public or private entities, respectively.  For example, designated public transportation vehicles include buses and vans operated by public transit agencies, while specified public transportation vehicles include tour and charter buses, taxis and limousines, and hotel shuttles operated by private entities.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-209_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.2.3 On-Street Bus Stops[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]On-street bus stops shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_2" class="navSectionLink">810.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to the maximum extent practicable.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-209_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.3 Medical Care and Long-Term Care Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one passenger loading zone complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-503" class="navSectionLink">503</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided at an accessible entrance to licensed medical care and licensed long-term care facilities where the period of stay exceeds twenty-four hours.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-209_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.4 Valet Parking[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking facilities that provide valet parking services shall provide at least one passenger loading zone complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-503" class="navSectionLink">503</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-209_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]209.5 Mechanical Access Parking Garages[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Mechanical access parking garages shall provide at least one passenger loading zone complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-503" class="navSectionLink">503</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]at vehicle drop-off and vehicle pick-up areas.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-210">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]210 Stairways[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-210_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]210.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Interior and exterior stairs that are part of a means of egress shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-210_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  In detention and correctional facilities, stairs that are not located in public use areas shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-210_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In alterations, stairs between levels that are connected by an accessible route shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]except that handrails complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided when the stairs are altered.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-210_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  In assembly areas, aisle stairs shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-210_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]4.  Stairs that connect play components shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 210.1 General.  Although these requirements do not mandate handrails on stairs that are not part of a means of egress, State or local building codes may require handrails or guards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-211">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]211 Drinking Fountains[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-211_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]211.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where drinking fountains are provided on an exterior site, on a floor, or within a secured area they shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-211" class="navSectionLink">211</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In detention or correctional facilities, drinking fountains only serving holding or housing cells not required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-232" class="navSectionLink">232</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-211" class="navSectionLink">211</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-211_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]211.2 Minimum Number[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]No fewer than two drinking fountains shall be provided.  One drinking fountain shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_1" class="navSectionLink">602.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_6" class="navSectionLink">602.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and one drinking fountain shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_7" class="navSectionLink">602.7</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where a single drinking fountain complies with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_1" class="navSectionLink">602.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_6" class="navSectionLink">602.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_7" class="navSectionLink">602.7</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]it shall be permitted to be substituted for two separate drinking fountains.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-211_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]211.3 More Than Minimum Number[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where more than the minimum number of drinking fountains specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-211_2" class="navSectionLink">211.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]are provided, 50 percent of the total number of drinking fountains provided shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_1" class="navSectionLink">602.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_6" class="navSectionLink">602.6</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and 50 percent of the total number of drinking fountains provided shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602_7" class="navSectionLink">602.7</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where 50 percent of the drinking fountains yields a fraction, 50 percent shall be permitted to be rounded up or down provided that the total number of drinking fountains complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-211" class="navSectionLink">211</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]equals 100 percent of drinking fountains.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-212">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]212 Kitchens, Kitchenettes, and Sinks[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-212_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]212.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, kitchens, kitchenettes, and sinks shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-212" class="navSectionLink">212</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-212_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]212.2 Kitchens and Kitchenettes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Kitchens and kitchenettes shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804" class="navSectionLink">804</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-212_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]212.3 Sinks[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where sinks are provided, at least 5 percent, but no fewer than one, of each type provided in each accessible room or space shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-606" class="navSectionLink">606</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Mop or service sinks shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-212_3" class="navSectionLink">212.3</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-213">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213 Toilet Facilities and Bathing Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-213_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where toilet facilities and bathing facilities are provided, they shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-213" class="navSectionLink">213</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where toilet facilities and bathing facilities are provided in facilities permitted by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-206_2_3" class="navSectionLink">206.2.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Exceptions 1 and 2 not to connect stories by an accessible route, toilet facilities and bathing facilities shall be provided on a story connected by an accessible route to an accessible entrance.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-213_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.2 Toilet Rooms and Bathing Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where toilet rooms are provided, each toilet room shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where bathing rooms are provided, each bathing room shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-213_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  In alterations where it is technically infeasible to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]altering existing toilet or bathing rooms shall not be required where a single unisex toilet room or bathing room complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-213_2_1" class="navSectionLink">213.2.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is provided and located in the same area and on the same floor as existing inaccessible toilet or bathing rooms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-213_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where exceptions for alterations to qualified historic buildings or facilities are permitted by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-202_5" class="navSectionLink">202.5</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]no fewer than one toilet room for each sex complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or one unisex toilet room complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-213_2_1" class="navSectionLink">213.2.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-213_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Where multiple single user portable toilet or bathing units are clustered at a single location, no more than 5 percent of the toilet units and bathing units at each cluster shall be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Portable toilet units and bathing units complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be identified by the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_1" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.1</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-213_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]4.  Where multiple single user toilet rooms are clustered at a single location, no more than 50 percent of the single user toilet rooms for each use at each cluster shall be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>.</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 213.2 Toilet Rooms and Bathing Rooms.  These requirements allow the use of unisex (or single-user) toilet rooms in alterations when technical infeasibility can be demonstrated.  Unisex toilet rooms benefit people who use opposite sex personal care assistants.  For this reason, it is advantageous to install unisex toilet rooms in addition to accessible single-sex toilet rooms in new facilities.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="last">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 213.2 Toilet Rooms and Bathing Rooms Exceptions 3 and 4.  A “cluster” is a group of toilet rooms proximate to one another.  Generally, toilet rooms in a cluster are within sight of, or adjacent to, one another.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
<h4 id="ada-213_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.2.1 Unisex (Single-Use or Family) Toilet and Unisex Bathing Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Unisex toilet rooms shall contain not more than one lavatory, and two water closets without urinals or one water closet and one urinal.  Unisex bathing rooms shall contain one shower or one shower and one bathtub, one lavatory, and one water closet.  Doors to unisex toilet rooms and unisex bathing rooms shall have privacy latches.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-213_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3 Plumbing Fixtures and Accessories[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Plumbing fixtures and accessories provided in a toilet room or bathing room required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-213_2" class="navSectionLink">213.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall comply with 213.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-213_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3.1 Toilet Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where toilet compartments are provided, at least one toilet compartment shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_1" class="navSectionLink">604.8.1</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In addition to the compartment required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_1" class="navSectionLink">604.8.1</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]at least one compartment shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_2" class="navSectionLink">604.8.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]where six or more toilet compartments are provided, or where the combination of urinals and water closets totals six or more fixtures.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 213.3.1 Toilet Compartments.  A toilet compartment is a partitioned space that is located within a toilet room, and that normally contains no more than one water closet.  A toilet compartment may also contain a lavatory.  A lavatory is a sink provided for hand washing.  Full-height partitions and door assemblies can comprise toilet compartments where the minimum required spaces are provided within the compartment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-213_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3.2 Water Closets[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where water closets are provided, at least one shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604" class="navSectionLink">604</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-213_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3.3 Urinals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where more than one urinal is provided, at least one shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-605" class="navSectionLink">605</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-213_3_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3.4 Lavatories[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where lavatories are provided, at least one shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-606" class="navSectionLink">606</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall not be located in a toilet compartment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-213_3_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3.5 Mirrors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where mirrors are provided, at least one shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603_3" class="navSectionLink">603.3</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-213_3_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3.6 Bathing Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where bathtubs or showers are provided, at least one bathtub complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607" class="navSectionLink">607</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or at least one shower complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-608" class="navSectionLink">608</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-213_3_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]213.3.7 Coat Hooks and Shelves[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where coat hooks or shelves are provided in toilet rooms without toilet compartments, at least one of each type shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603_4" class="navSectionLink">603.4</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where coat hooks or shelves are provided in toilet compartments, at least one of each type complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_3" class="navSectionLink">604.8.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in toilet compartments required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-213_3_1" class="navSectionLink">213.3.1</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where coat hooks or shelves are provided in bathing facilities, at least one of each type complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603_4" class="navSectionLink">603.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall serve fixtures required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-213_3_6" class="navSectionLink">213.3.6</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-214">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]214 Washing Machines and Clothes Dryers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-214_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]214.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, washing machines and clothes dryers shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-214" class="navSectionLink">214</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-214_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]214.2 Washing Machines[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where three or fewer washing machines are provided, at least one shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-611" class="navSectionLink">611</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where more than three washing machines are provided, at least two shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-611" class="navSectionLink">611</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-214_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]214.3 Clothes Dryers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where three or fewer clothes dryers are provided, at least one shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-611" class="navSectionLink">611</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where more than three clothes dryers are provided, at least two shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-611" class="navSectionLink">611</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-215">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]215 Fire Alarm Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-215_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]215.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where fire alarm systems provide audible alarm coverage, alarms shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-215" class="navSectionLink">215</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In existing facilities, visible alarms shall not be required except where an existing fire alarm system is upgraded or replaced, or a new fire alarm system is installed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 215.1 General.  Unlike audible alarms, visible alarms must be located within the space they serve so that the signal is visible.  Facility alarm systems (other than fire alarm systems) such as those used for tornado warnings and other emergencies are not required to comply with the technical criteria for alarms in Section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Every effort should be made to ensure that such alarms can be differentiated in their signal from fire alarms systems and that people who need to be notified of emergencies are adequately safeguarded.  Consult local fire departments and prepare evacuation plans taking into consideration the needs of every building occupant, including people with disabilities.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-215_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]215.2 Public and Common Use Areas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Alarms in public use areas and common use areas shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-215_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]215.3 Employee Work Areas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where employee work areas have audible alarm coverage, the wiring system shall be designed so that visible alarms complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]can be integrated into the alarm system.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-215_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]215.4 Transient Lodging[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Guest rooms required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-224_4" class="navSectionLink">224.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall provide alarms complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-215_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]215.5 Residential Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided in residential dwelling units required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_5" class="navSectionLink">809.5</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]alarms shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-216">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216 Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-216_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216" class="navSectionLink">216</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703" class="navSectionLink">703</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-216_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Building directories, menus, seat and row designations in assembly areas, occupant names, building addresses, and company names and logos shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216" class="navSectionLink">216</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-216_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In parking facilities, signs shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216_2" class="navSectionLink">216.2</a>, <a href="#ada-216_3" class="navSectionLink">216.3</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216_6" class="navSectionLink">216.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216_12" class="navSectionLink">216.12</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-216_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Temporary, 7 days or less, signs shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216" class="navSectionLink">216</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-216_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]4.  In detention and correctional facilities, signs not located in public use areas shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216" class="navSectionLink">216</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.2 Designations[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Interior and exterior signs identifying permanent rooms and spaces shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_1" class="navSectionLink">703.1</a>, <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where pictograms are provided as designations of permanent interior rooms and spaces, the pictograms shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_6" class="navSectionLink">703.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall have text descriptors complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Exterior signs that are not located at the door to the space they serve shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 216.2 Designations.  Section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-216_2" class="navSectionLink">216.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]applies to signs that provide designations, labels, or names for interior rooms or spaces where the sign is not likely to change over time.  Examples include interior signs labeling restrooms, room and floor numbers or letters, and room names.  Tactile text descriptors are required for pictograms that are provided to label or identify a permanent room or space.  Pictograms that provide information about a room or space, such as “no smoking,” occupant logos, and the International Symbol of Accessibility, are not required to have text descriptors.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.3 Directional and Informational Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs that provide direction to or information about interior spaces and facilities of the site shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 216.3 Directional and Informational Signs.  Information about interior spaces and facilities includes rules of conduct, occupant load, and similar signs.  Signs providing direction to rooms or spaces include those that identify egress routes.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.4 Means of Egress[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs for means of egress shall comply with 216.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-216_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.4.1 Exit Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doors at exit passageways, exit discharge, and exit stairways shall be identified by tactile signs complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_1" class="navSectionLink">703.1</a>, <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 216.4.1 Exit Doors.  An exit passageway is a horizontal exit component that is separated from the interior spaces of the building by fire-resistance-rated construction and that leads to the exit discharge or public way.  The exit discharge is that portion of an egress system between the termination of an exit and a public way.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-216_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.4.2 Areas of Refuge[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs required by section 1003.2.13.5.4 of the International Building Code (2000 edition) or section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1007_6_4" class="navSectionLink">1007.6.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the International Building Code (2003 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1) to provide instructions in areas of refuge shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-216_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.4.3 Directional Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs required by section 1003.2.13.6 of the International Building Code (2000 edition) or section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1007_7" class="navSectionLink">1007.7</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the International Building Code (2003 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1) to provide directions to accessible means of egress shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.5 Parking[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking spaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502" class="navSectionLink">502</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be identified by signs complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502_6" class="navSectionLink">502.6</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-216_5x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Where a total of four or fewer parking spaces, including accessible parking spaces, are provided on a site, identification of accessible parking spaces shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-216_5x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In residential facilities, where parking spaces are assigned to specific residential dwelling units, identification of accessible parking spaces shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.6 Entrances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where not all entrances comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]entrances complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be identified by the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with 703.7.2.1.  Directional signs complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]that indicate the location of the nearest entrance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided at entrances that do not comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 216.6 Entrances.  Where a directional sign is required, it should be located to minimize backtracking.  In some cases, this could mean locating a sign at the beginning of a route, not just at the inaccessible entrances to a building.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.7 Elevators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where existing elevators do not comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407" class="navSectionLink">407</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]elevators complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407" class="navSectionLink">407</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be clearly identified with the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_1" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.1</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.8 Toilet Rooms and Bathing Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where existing toilet rooms or bathing rooms do not comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]directional signs indicating the location of the nearest toilet room or bathing room complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]within the facility shall be provided.  Signs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall include the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with 703.7.2.1.  Where existing toilet rooms or bathing rooms do not comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]the toilet rooms or bathing rooms complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be identified by the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with 703.7.2.1.  Where clustered single user toilet rooms or bathing facilities are permitted to use exceptions to[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-213_2" class="navSectionLink">213.2</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]toilet rooms or bathing facilities complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be identified by the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_1" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]unless all toilet rooms and bathing facilities comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.9 TTYs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Identification and directional signs for public TTYs shall be provided in accordance with 216.9.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-216_9_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.9.1 Identification Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Public TTYs shall be identified by the International Symbol of TTY complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_2" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.2</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-216_9_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.9.2 Directional Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Directional signs indicating the location of the nearest public TTY shall be provided at all banks of public pay telephones not containing a public TTY.  In addition, where signs provide direction to public pay telephones, they shall also provide direction to public TTYs.  Directional signs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall include the International Symbol of TTY complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_2" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.2</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_10">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.10 Assistive Listening Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each assembly area required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-219" class="navSectionLink">219</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to provide assistive listening systems shall provide signs informing patrons of the availability of the assistive listening system.  Assistive listening signs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall include the International Symbol of Access for Hearing Loss complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_4" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.4</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where ticket offices or windows are provided, signs shall not be required at each assembly area provided that signs are displayed at each ticket office or window informing patrons of the availability of assistive listening systems.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_11">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.11 Check-Out Aisles[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where more than one check-out aisle is provided, check-out aisles complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be identified by the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with 703.7.2.1.  Where check-out aisles are identified by numbers, letters, or functions, signs identifying check-out aisles complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be located in the same location as the check-out aisle identification.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where all check-out aisles serving a single function comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]signs complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_1" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-216_12">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]216.12 Amusement Rides[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs identifying the type of access provided on amusement rides shall be provided at entries to queues and waiting lines.  In addition, where accessible unload areas also serve as accessible load areas, signs indicating the location of the accessible load and unload areas shall be provided at entries to queues and waiting lines.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 216.12 Amusement Rides.  Amusement rides designed primarily for children, amusement rides that are controlled or operated by the rider, and amusement rides without seats, are not required to provide wheelchair spaces, transfer seats, or transfer systems, and need not meet the sign requirements in 216.12. The load and unload areas of these rides must, however, be on an accessible route and must provide turning space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-217">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217 Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-217_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where coin-operated public pay telephones, coinless public pay telephones, public closed-circuit telephones, public courtesy phones, or other types of public telephones are provided, public telephones shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-217" class="navSectionLink">217</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]for each type of public telephone provided.  For purposes of this section, a bank of telephones shall be considered to be two or more adjacent telephones.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 217.1 General.  These requirements apply to all types of public telephones including courtesy phones at airports and rail stations that provide a free direct connection to hotels, transportation services, and tourist attractions.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-217_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.2 Wheelchair accessible Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where public telephones are provided, wheelchair accessible telephones complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_2" class="navSectionLink">704.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in accordance with Table 217.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Drive-up only public telephones shall not be required to comply with 217.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 217.2 Wheelchair accessible Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Number of Telephones Provided[-END TRANSLATE-] <br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]on a Floor, Level, or Exterior Site[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Minimum Number of Required[-END TRANSLATE-] <br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair accessible Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1 or more single units[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1 per floor, level, and exterior site[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1 bank[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1 per floor, level, and exterior site[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2 or more banks[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1 per bank[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3 id="ada-217_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.3 Volume Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All public telephones shall have volume controls complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_3" class="navSectionLink">704.3</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-217_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4 TTYs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]TTYs complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_4" class="navSectionLink">704.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in accordance with 217.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 217.4 TTYs.  Separate requirements are provided based on the number of public pay telephones provided at a bank of telephones, within a floor, a building, or on a site.  In some instances one TTY can be used to satisfy more than one of these requirements.  For example, a TTY required for a bank can satisfy the requirements for a building.  However, the requirement for at least one TTY on an exterior site cannot be met by installing a TTY in a bank inside a building.  Consideration should be given to phone systems that can accommodate both digital and analog transmissions for compatibility with digital and analog TTYs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.1 Bank Requirement[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where four or more public pay telephones are provided at a bank of telephones, at least one public TTY complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_4" class="navSectionLink">704.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided at that bank.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  TTYs shall not be required at banks of telephones located within 200 feet (61 m) of, and on the same floor as, a bank containing a public TTY.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.2 Floor Requirement[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]TTYs in public buildings shall be provided in accordance with 217.4.2.1.  TTYs in private buildings shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-217_4_2_2" class="navSectionLink">217.4.2.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-217_4_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.2.1 Public Buildings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where at least one public pay telephone is provided on a floor of a public building, at least one public TTY shall be provided on that floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-217_4_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.2.2 Private Buildings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where four or more public pay telephones are provided on a floor of a private building, at least one public TTY shall be provided on that floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.3 Building Requirement[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]TTYs in public buildings shall be provided in accordance with 217.4.3.1.  TTYs in private buildings shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-217_4_3_2" class="navSectionLink">217.4.3.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-217_4_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.3.1 Public Buildings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where at least one public pay telephone is provided in a public building, at least one public TTY shall be provided in the building. Where at least one public pay telephone is provided in a public use area of a public building, at least one public TTY shall be provided in the public building in a public use area.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-217_4_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.3.2 Private Buildings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where four or more public pay telephones are provided in a private building, at least one public TTY shall be provided in the building.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.4 Exterior Site Requirement[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where four or more public pay telephones are provided on an exterior site, at least one public TTY shall be provided on the site.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.5 Rest Stops, Emergency Roadside Stops, and Service Plazas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where at least one public pay telephone is provided at a public rest stop, emergency roadside stop, or service plaza, at least one public TTY shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.6 Hospitals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where at least one public pay telephone is provided serving a hospital emergency room, hospital recovery room, or hospital waiting room, at least one public TTY shall be provided at each location.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.7 Transportation Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In transportation facilities, in addition to the requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-217_4_1" class="navSectionLink">217.4.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-217_4_4" class="navSectionLink">217.4.4</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]where at least one public pay telephone serves a particular entrance to a bus or rail facility, at least one public TTY shall be provided to serve that entrance.  In airports, in addition to the requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-217_4_1" class="navSectionLink">217.4.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-217_4_4" class="navSectionLink">217.4.4</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]where four or more public pay telephones are located in a terminal outside the security areas, a concourse within the security areas, or a baggage claim area in a terminal, at least one public TTY shall be provided in each location.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-217_4_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.4.8 Detention and Correctional Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In detention and correctional facilities, where at least one pay telephone is provided in a secured area used only by detainees or inmates and security personnel, at least one TTY shall be provided in at least one secured area.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-217_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]217.5 Shelves for Portable TTYs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a bank of telephones in the interior of a building consists of three or more public pay telephones, at least one public pay telephone at the bank shall be provided with a shelf and an electrical outlet in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_5" class="navSectionLink">704.5</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-217_5x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Secured areas of detention and correctional facilities where shelves and outlets are prohibited for purposes of security or safety shall not be required to comply with 217.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-217_5x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  The shelf and electrical outlet shall not be required at a bank of telephones with a TTY.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-218">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]218 Transportation Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-218_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]218.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transportation facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-218" class="navSectionLink">218</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-218_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]218.2 New and Altered Fixed Guideway Stations[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]New and altered stations in rapid rail, light rail, commuter rail, intercity rail, high speed rail, and other fixed guideway systems shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_5" class="navSectionLink">810.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_10" class="navSectionLink">810.10</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-218_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]218.3 Key Stations and Existing Intercity Rail Stations[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Key stations and existing intercity rail stations shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_5" class="navSectionLink">810.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_10" class="navSectionLink">810.10</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-218_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]218.4 Bus Shelters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, bus shelters shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_3" class="navSectionLink">810.3</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-218_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]218.5 Other Transportation Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In other transportation facilities, public address systems shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_7" class="navSectionLink">810.7</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and clocks shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_8" class="navSectionLink">810.8</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-219">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]219 Assistive Listening Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-219_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]219.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Assistive listening systems shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-219" class="navSectionLink">219</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-706" class="navSectionLink">706</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-219_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]219.2 Required Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In each assembly area where audible communication is integral to the use of the space, an assistive listening system shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Other than in courtrooms, assistive listening systems shall not be required where audio amplification is not provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-219_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]219.3 Receivers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Receivers complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-706_2" class="navSectionLink">706.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided for assistive listening systems in each assembly area in accordance with Table 219.3.  Twenty-five percent minimum of receivers provided, but no fewer than two, shall be hearing-aid compatible in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-706_3" class="navSectionLink">706.3</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-219_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Where a building contains more than one assembly area and the assembly areas required to provide assistive listening systems are under one management, the total number of required receivers shall be permitted to be calculated according to the total number of seats in the assembly areas in the building provided that all receivers are usable with all systems.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-219_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where all seats in an assembly area are served by an induction loop assistive listening system, the minimum number of receivers required by Table 219.3 to be hearing-aid compatible shall not be required to be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 219.3 Receivers for Assistive Listening Systems [-END TRANSLATE-]<small><br> </small></caption>
<thead>
