<h3 id="ada-224_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]224.5 Dispersion[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Guest rooms required to provide mobility features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806_2" class="navSectionLink">806.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and guest rooms required to provide communication features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806_3" class="navSectionLink">806.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be dispersed among the various classes of guest rooms, and shall provide choices of types of guest rooms, number of beds, and other amenities comparable to the choices provided to other guests.  Where the minimum number of guest rooms required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806" class="navSectionLink">806</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is not sufficient to allow for complete dispersion, guest rooms shall be dispersed in the following priority:  guest room type, number of beds, and amenities.  At least one guest room required to provide mobility features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806_2" class="navSectionLink">806.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall also provide communication features complying with 806.3.  Not more than 10 percent of guest rooms required to provide mobility features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806_2" class="navSectionLink">806.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be used to satisfy the minimum number of guest rooms required to provide communication features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806_3" class="navSectionLink">806.3</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 224.5 Dispersion.  Factors to be considered in providing an equivalent range of options may include, but are not limited to, room size, bed size, cost, view, bathroom fixtures such as hot tubs and spas, smoking and nonsmoking, and the number of rooms provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table role="presentation" class="standards" style="width: 100%; background-color: #eeeeee; border: 1px solid #000000;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<p class="standards"><em>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Note to Reader: [-END TRANSLATE-]</em>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The Department of Justice’s ADA standards also require the following:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards"><strong>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Places of lodging.[-END TRANSLATE-]</strong> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Places of lodging subject to this part [of the title III regulation] shall comply with the provisions of the 2010 Standards applicable to transient lodging, including, but not limited to, the requirements for transient lodging guest rooms in sections[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-224" class="navSectionLink">224</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806" class="navSectionLink">806</a>.</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](1) Guest rooms. Guest rooms with mobility features in places of lodging subject to the transient lodging requirements of 2010 Standards shall be provided as follows--[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](i) Facilities that are subject to the same permit application on a common site that each have 50 or fewer guest rooms may be combined for the purposes of determining the required number of accessible rooms and type of accessible bathing facility in accordance with table 224.2 to section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-224_2" class="navSectionLink">224.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the 2010 Standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](ii) Facilities with more than 50 guest rooms shall be treated separately for the purposes of determining the required number of accessible rooms and type of accessible bathing facility in accordance with table 224.2 to section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-224_2" class="navSectionLink">224.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the 2010 Standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](2) Exception. Alterations to guest rooms in places of lodging where the guest rooms are not owned or substantially controlled by the entity that owns, leases, or operates the overall facility and the physical features of the guest room interiors are controlled by their individual owners are not required to comply with § 36.402 or the alterations requirements in section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-224_1_1" class="navSectionLink">224.1.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the 2010 Standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](3) Facilities with residential units and transient lodging units. Residential dwelling units that are designed and constructed for residential use exclusively are not subject to the transient lodging standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards"><br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The Department of Justice’s ADA standards also require the following:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards"><strong>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Housing at a place of education.[-END TRANSLATE-]</strong> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Housing at a place of education that is subject to this part [of the title III regulation or to this section of the title II regulation] shall comply with the provisions of the 2010 Standards applicable to transient lodging, including, but not limited to, the requirements for transient lodging guest rooms in sections[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-224" class="navSectionLink">224</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806" class="navSectionLink">806</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]subject to the following exceptions. For the purposes of the application of this section, the term “sleeping room” is intended to be used interchangeably with the term “guest room” as it is used in the transient lodging standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](1) Kitchens within housing units containing accessible sleeping rooms with mobility features (including suites and clustered sleeping rooms) or on floors containing accessible sleeping rooms with mobility features shall provide turning spaces that comply with section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_2_2" class="navSectionLink">809.2.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the 2010 Standards and kitchen work surfaces that comply with section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804_3" class="navSectionLink">804.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the 2010 Standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](2) Multi-bedroom housing units containing accessible sleeping rooms with mobility features shall have an accessible route throughout the unit in accordance with section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_2" class="navSectionLink">809.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the 2010 Standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](3) Apartments or townhouse facilities that are provided by or on behalf of a place of education, which are leased on a year-round basis exclusively to graduate students or faculty and do not contain any public use or common use areas available for educational programming, are not subject to the transient lodging standards and shall comply with the requirements for residential facilities in sections[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-233" class="navSectionLink">233</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809" class="navSectionLink">809</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the 2010 Standards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<br>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The Department of Justice’s title II and title III regulations include requirements for social service center establishments which are noted in section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-233" class="navSectionLink">233</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](Residential Facilities).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2 id="ada-225">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]225 Storage[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-225_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]225.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Storage facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-225" class="navSectionLink">225</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-225_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]225.2 Storage[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where storage is provided in accessible spaces, at least one of each type shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-811" class="navSectionLink">811</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 225.2 Storage.  Types of storage include, but are not limited to, closets, cabinets, shelves, clothes rods, hooks, and drawers.  Where provided, at least one of each type of storage must be within the reach ranges specified in 308; however, it is permissible to install additional storage outside the reach ranges.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-225_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]225.2.1 Lockers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where lockers are provided, at least 5 percent, but no fewer than one of each type, shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-811" class="navSectionLink">811</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 225.2.1 Lockers.  Different types of lockers may include full-size and half-size lockers, as well as those specifically designed for storage of various sports equipment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-225_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]225.2.2 Self-Service Shelving[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Self-service shelves shall be located on an accessible route complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-402" class="navSectionLink">402</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Self-service shelving shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 225.2.2 Self-Service Shelving.  Self-service shelves include, but are not limited to, library, store, or post office shelves.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-225_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]225.3 Self-Service Storage Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Self-service storage facilities shall provide individual self-service storage spaces complying with these requirements in accordance with Table 225.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 225.3 Self-Service Storage Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Total Spaces in Facility[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Minimum Number of [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Spaces Required to be accessible[-END TRANSLATE-]</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1 to 200[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]5 percent, but no fewer than 1[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]201 and over[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]10, plus 2 percent of total number of units over 200[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 225.3 Self-Service Storage Facilities.  Although there are no technical requirements that are unique to self-service storage facilities, elements and spaces provided in facilities containing self-service storage spaces required to comply with these requirements must comply with this document where applicable.  For example:  the number of storage spaces required to comply with these requirements must provide accessible Routes complying with Section 206; accessible means of egress complying with Section 207; Parking Spaces complying with Section 208; and, where provided, other public use or common use elements and facilities such as toilet rooms, drinking fountains, and telephones must comply with the applicable requirements of this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-225_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]225.3.1 Dispersion[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Individual self-service storage spaces shall be dispersed throughout the various classes of spaces provided.  Where more classes of spaces are provided than the number required to be accessible, the number of spaces shall not be required to exceed that required by Table 225.3.  Self-service storage spaces complying with Table 225.3 shall not be required to be dispersed among buildings in a multi-building facility.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-226">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]226 Dining Surfaces and Work Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-226_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]226.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where dining surfaces are provided for the consumption of food or drink, at least 5 percent of the seating spaces and standing spaces at the dining surfaces shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902" class="navSectionLink">902</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In addition, where work surfaces are provided for use by other than employees, at least 5 percent shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902" class="navSectionLink">902</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-226_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Sales counters and service counters shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902" class="navSectionLink">902</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-226_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Check writing surfaces provided at check-out aisles not required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902" class="navSectionLink">902</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 226.1 General.  In facilities covered by the ADA, this requirement does not apply to work surfaces used only by employees.  However, the ADA and, where applicable, Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, as amended, provide that employees are entitled to “reasonable accommodations.”  With respect to work surfaces, this means that employers may need to procure or adjust work stations such as desks, laboratory and work benches, fume hoods, reception counters, teller windows, study carrels, commercial kitchen counters, and conference tables to accommodate the individual needs of employees with disabilities on an “as needed” basis.  Consider work surfaces that are flexible and permit installation at variable heights and clearances.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-226_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]226.2 Dispersion[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Dining surfaces and work surfaces required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902" class="navSectionLink">902</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be dispersed throughout the space or facility containing dining surfaces and work surfaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-227">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]227 Sales and Service[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-227_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]227.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, check-out aisles, sales counters, service counters, food service lines, queues, and waiting lines shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-227" class="navSectionLink">227</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904" class="navSectionLink">904</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-227_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]227.2 Check-Out Aisles[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where check-out aisles are provided, check-out aisles complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in accordance with Table 227.2.  Where check-out aisles serve different functions, check-out aisles complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in accordance with Table 227.2 for each function.  Where check-out aisles are dispersed throughout the building or facility, check-out aisles complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be dispersed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where the selling space is under 5000 square feet (465 m2) no more than one check-out aisle complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 227.2 Check-Out Aisles[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Number of Check-Out Aisles[-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of Each Function[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Minimum Number of Check-Out Aisles[-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of Each Function [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Required to Comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_3" class="navSectionLink">904.3</a></th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1 to 4[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>1</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]5 to 8[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>2</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]9 to 15[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>3</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]16 and over[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3, plus 20 percent of additional aisles[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
