{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 404.2.4.2 Maneuvering Clearances at [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doorways without Doors, Sliding Doors, Gates, and Folding Doors"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB25.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figura 404.2.4.2 Holguras de maniobra en puertas sin puertas, puertas correderas manuales y puertas plegables manuales. La figura (a) muestra un enfoque frontal a una puerta corredera o plegable (acordeón).  El espacio libre de maniobra es tan ancho como la abertura de la puerta y 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) mínimo perpendicular a la abertura.  La figura (b) muestra una puerta sin puerta. Para un enfoque lateral, el espacio libre de maniobra es tan ancho como la puerta y 42 pulgadas (1065 mm) mínimo perpendicular a la puerta.  La figura (c) muestra un enfoque de bolsillo o bisagra.  El espacio libre de maniobra se extiende 22 pulgadas (560 mm) desde el lado del bolsillo o la bisagra y es de 42 pulgadas (1065 mm) mínimo perpendicular a la puerta.  La figura (d) muestra un enfoque de parada o cierre.El espacio libre de maniobra se extiende 24 pulgadas (610 mm) desde el lado de la parada o el pestillo y es de 42 pulgadas (1065 mm) mínimo perpendicular a la puerta."[-END TRANSLATE-]    

Figure 404.2.4.2 Maneuvering Clearances at Doorways without Doors, Manual Sliding Doors, and Manual Folding Doors. Figure (a) shows a front approach to a sliding or folding (accordion) door.  Maneuvering clearance is as wide as the door opening and 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum perpendicular to the opening.  Figure (b) shows a doorway without a door.  For a side approach, maneuvering clearance is as wide as the doorway and 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum perpendicular to the doorway.  Figure (c) shows a pocket or hinge approach.  Maneuvering clearance extends 22 inches (560 mm) from the pocket or hinge side and is 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum perpendicular to the doorway.  Figure (d) shows a stop or latch approach.  Maneuvering clearance extends 24 inches (610 mm) from the stop or latch side and is 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum perpendicular to the doorway.  

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-404_2_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.4.3 Recessed Doors and Gates[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Maneuvering clearances for forward approach shall be provided when any obstruction within 18 inches (455 mm) of the latch side of a doorway projects more than 8 inches (205 mm) beyond the face of the door, measured perpendicular to the face of the door or gate.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 404.2.4.3 Recessed Doors and Gates.  A door can be recessed due to wall thickness or because of the placement of casework and other fixed elements adjacent to the doorway.  This provision must be applied wherever doors are recessed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 404.2.4.3 Maneuvering Clearances at Recessed Doors and Gates"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB26.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figura 404.2.4.3 Espacio libre de maniobra en puertas y portones empotrados.  Las figuras (a) – (c) muestran aproximaciones frontales en puertas empotradas de más de 8 pulgadas (455 mm).  El espacio de maniobra en el lado de tracción se extiende 18 pulgadas (455 mm) como mínimo más allá del lado del pestillo de la puerta y 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como mínimo perpendicular al plano de la puerta.En el lado de empuje de las puertas no equipadas con un cierre o pestillo, el espacio de maniobra es del mismo ancho que la abertura de la puerta y se extiende 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) como mínimo perpendicular al plano de la puerta. En las puertas equipadas con un cierre y un pestillo, el espacio de maniobra se extiende 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como mínimo más allá del lado del pestillo de la puerta y 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) como mínimo medido perpendicularmente al plano de la puerta."[-END TRANSLATE-] 

Figure 404.2.4.3 Maneuvering Clearance at Recessed Doors and Gates.  Figures (a) – (c) show front approaches at doors recessed more than 8 inches (455 mm).  Maneuvering space on the pull side extends 18 inches (455 mm) minimum beyond the latch side of the door and 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum perpendicular to the plane of the doorway.  On the push side of doors not equipped with a closer or latch, the maneuvering space is the same width as the door opening and extends 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum perpendicular to the plane of the doorway.  At doors equipped with both a closer and a latch, the maneuvering space extends 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beyond the latch side of the door and 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum measured perpendicular to the plane of the doorway.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-404_2_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.4.4 Floor or Ground Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floor or ground surface within required maneuvering clearances shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Changes in level are not permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_4_4x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_4_4x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Changes in level at thresholds complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_5" class="navSectionLink">404.2.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_2_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.5 Thresholds[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Thresholds, if provided at doorways, shall be 1/2 inch (13 mm) high maximum.  Raised thresholds and changes in level at doorways shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303" class="navSectionLink">303</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing or altered thresholds 3/4 inch (19 mm) high maximum that have a beveled edge on each side with a slope not steeper than 1:2 shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_5" class="navSectionLink">404.2.5</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_2_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.6 Doors in Series and Gates in Series[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The distance between two hinged or pivoted doors in series and gates in series shall be 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum plus the width of doors or gates swinging into the space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 404.2.6 Doors in Series and Gates in Series"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB27.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra dos puertas en serie que se balancean en la misma dirección.  El espacio entre las puertas debe ser de al menos 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) como mínimo más el ancho de la puerta batiente.  La figura (b) muestra dos puertas en serie que se alejan del espacio entre las puertas.  El espacio que separa las puertas debe tener al menos 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) de largo.Figure (c) shows two doors in series which both swing in towards the space between the doors.  The space separating the doors must be at least 48 inches (1220 mm) plus the width of both in-swinging doors."[-END TRANSLATE-]  

Figure (a) shows two doors in series which swing in the same direction.  Space between the doors must be at least 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum plus the width of the in-swinging door.  Figure (b) shows two doors in series which swing away from the space between the doors.  The space separating the doors must be at least 48 inches (1220 mm) long.  Figure (c) shows two doors in series which both swing in towards the space between the doors.  The space separating the doors must be at least 48 inches (1220 mm) plus the width of both in-swinging doors"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-404_2_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.7 Door and Gate Hardware[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handles, pulls, latches, locks, and other operable parts on doors and gates shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Operable parts of such hardware shall be 34 inches (865 mm) minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.  Where sliding doors are in the fully open position, operating hardware shall be exposed and usable from both sides.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_7x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Existing locks shall be permitted in any location at existing glazed doors without stiles, existing overhead rolling doors or grilles, and similar existing doors or grilles that are designed with locks that are activated only at the top or bottom rail.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_7x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Access gates in barrier walls and fences protecting pools, spas, and hot tubs shall be permitted to have operable parts of the release of latch on self-latching devices at 54 inches (1370 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground provided the self-latching devices are not also self-locking devices and operated by means of a key, electronic opener, or integral combination lock.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 404.2.7 Door and Gate Hardware.  Door hardware that can be operated with a closed fist or a loose grip accommodates the greatest range of users. Hardware that requires simultaneous hand and finger movements require greater dexterity and coordination, and is not recommended.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_2_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.8 Closing Speed[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Door and gate closing speed shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_8" class="navSectionLink">404.2.8</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-404_2_8_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.8.1 Door Closers and Gate Closers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Door closers and gate closers shall be adjusted so that from an open position of 90 degrees, the time required to move the door to a position of 12 degrees from the latch is 5 seconds minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-404_2_8_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.8.2 Spring Hinges[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Door and gate spring hinges shall be adjusted so that from the open position of 70 degrees, the door or gate shall move to the closed position in 1.5 seconds minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_2_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.9 Door and Gate Opening Force[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Fire doors shall have a minimum opening force allowable by the appropriate administrative authority.  The force for pushing or pulling open a door or gate other than fire doors shall be as follows:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<ol class="standards">
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Interior hinged doors and gates:  5 pounds (22.2 N) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Sliding or folding doors:  5 pounds (22.2 N) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
</ol>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]These forces do not apply to the force required to retract latch bolts or disengage other devices that hold the door or gate in a closed position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 404.2.9 Door and Gate Opening Force.  The maximum force pertains to the continuous application of force necessary to fully open a door, not the initial force needed to overcome the inertia of the door.  It does not apply to the force required to retract bolts or to disengage other devices used to keep the door in a closed position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-404_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.10 Door and Gate Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Swinging door and gate surfaces within 10 inches (255 mm) of the finish floor or ground measured vertically shall have a smooth surface on the push side extending the full width of the door or gate.  Parts creating horizontal or vertical joints in these surfaces shall be within 1/16 inch (1.6 mm) of the same plane as the other.  Cavities created by added kick plates shall be capped.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_10x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Sliding doors shall not be required to comply with 404.2.10.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_10x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Tempered glass doors without stiles and having a bottom rail or shoe with the top leading edge tapered at 60 degrees minimum from the horizontal shall not be required to meet the 10 inch (255 mm) bottom smooth surface height requirement.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_10x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Doors and gates that do not extend to within 10 inches (255 mm) of the finish floor or ground shall not be required to comply with 404.2.10.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-404_2_10x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]4.  Existing doors and gates without smooth surfaces within 10 inches (255 mm) of the finish floor or ground shall not be required to provide smooth surfaces complying with 404.2.10 provided that if added kick plates are installed, cavities created by such kick plates are capped.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-404_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.2.11 Vision Lights[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doors, gates, and side lights adjacent to doors or gates, containing one or more glazing panels that permit viewing through the panels shall have the bottom of at least one glazed panel located 43 inches (1090 mm) maximum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Vision lights with the lowest part more than 66 inches (1675 mm) from the finish floor or ground shall not be required to comply with 404.2.11.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-404_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3 Automatic and Power-Assisted Doors and Gates[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Automatic doors and automatic gates shall comply with 404.3.  Full-powered automatic doors shall comply with ANSI/BHMA A156.10 (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).  Low-energy and power-assisted doors shall comply with ANSI/BHMA A156.19 (1997 or 2002 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3.1 Clear Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doorways shall provide a clear opening of 32 inches (815 mm) minimum in power-on and power-off mode.  The minimum clear width for automatic door systems in a doorway shall be based on the clear opening provided by all leaves in the open position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3.2 Maneuvering Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearances at power-assisted doors and gates shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_4" class="navSectionLink">404.2.4</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearances at automatic doors and gates without standby power and serving an accessible means of egress shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_4" class="navSectionLink">404.2.4</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: Where automatic doors and gates remain open in the power-off condition, compliance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_4" class="navSectionLink">404.2.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3.3 Thresholds[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Thresholds and changes in level at doorways shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_5" class="navSectionLink">404.2.5</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_3_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3.4 Doors in Series and Gates in Series[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doors in series and gates in series shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_6" class="navSectionLink">404.2.6</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_3_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3.5 Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Manually operated controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The clear floor space adjacent to the control shall be located beyond the arc of the door swing.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_3_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3.6 Break Out Opening[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where doors and gates without standby power are a part of a means of egress, the clear break out opening at swinging or sliding doors and gates shall be 32 inches (815 mm) minimum when operated in emergency mode.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where manual swinging doors and gates comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2" class="navSectionLink">404.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and serve the same means of egress compliance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_3_6" class="navSectionLink">404.3.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-404_3_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]404.3.7 Revolving Doors, Revolving Gates, and Turnstiles[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Revolving doors, revolving gates, and turnstiles shall not be part of an accessible route.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-405">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405 Ramps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-405_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramps on accessible routes shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405" class="navSectionLink">405</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: In assembly areas, aisle ramps adjacent to seating and not serving elements required to be on an accessible route shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405" class="navSectionLink">405</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.2 Slope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramp runs shall have a running slope not steeper than 1:12.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: In existing sites, buildings, and facilities, ramps shall be permitted to have running slopes steeper than 1:12 complying with Table 405.2 where such slopes are necessary due to space limitations.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 405.2 Maximum Ramp Slope and Rise for Existing Sites, Buildings, and Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr><th aria-describedby="more1" scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Slope ¹[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Maximum Rise[-END TRANSLATE-]</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Steeper than 1:10 but not steeper than 1:8[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>3 inches (75 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Steeper than 1:12 but not steeper than 1:10[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>6 inches (150 mm)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><span class="text-italic">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table Legend:[-END TRANSLATE-]</span> 1. <span id="more1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A slope steeper than 1:8 is prohibited[-END TRANSLATE-]</span>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 405.2 Slope.  To accommodate the widest range of users, provide ramps with the least possible running slope and, wherever possible, accompany ramps with stairs for use by those individuals for whom distance presents a greater barrier than steps, e.g., people with heart disease or limited stamina.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.3 Cross Slope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Cross slope of ramp runs shall not be steeper than 1:48.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 405.3 Cross Slope.  Cross slope is the slope of the surface perpendicular to the direction of travel.  Cross slope is measured the same way as slope is measured (i.e., the rise over the run).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.4 Floor or Ground Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floor or ground surfaces of ramp runs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Changes in level other than the running slope and cross slope are not permitted on ramp runs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.5 Clear Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The clear width of a ramp run and, where handrails are provided, the clear width between handrails shall be 36 inches (915 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Within employee work areas, the required clear width of ramps that are a part of common use circulation paths shall be permitted to be decreased by work area equipment provided that the decrease is essential to the function of the work being performed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.6 Rise[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The rise for any ramp run shall be 30 inches (760 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.7 Landings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramps shall have landings at the top and the bottom of each ramp run.  Landings shall comply with 405.7.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 405.7 Landings.  Ramps that do not have level landings at changes in direction can create a compound slope that will not meet the requirements of this document.  Circular or curved ramps continually change direction.  Curvilinear ramps with small radii also can create compound cross slopes and cannot, by their nature, meet the requirements for accessible routes.  A level landing is needed at the accessible door to permit maneuvering and simultaneously door operation.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 405.7 Ramp Landings"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB28.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) muestra en la vista del plano una rampa con dos aterrizajes, cada uno de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de largo en la dirección de la carrera de la rampa y tan ancha como la carrera de la rampa de conexión.  La Figura (b) muestra una rampa que tiene dos recorridos conectados por un aterrizaje de 60 por 60 pulgadas (1525 por 1525 mm); cada carrera está orientada a 90 grados de la otra carrera, que se conecta a un lado adyacente del aterrizaje".[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows in plan view a ramp with two landings, each 60 inches (1525 mm) long in the direction of the ramp run and as wide as the connecting ramp run.  Figure (b) shows a ramp that has two runs connected by a landing 60 by 60 inches (1525 by 1525 mm); each run is oriented at 90 degrees from the other run, which connect to an adjacent sides of the landing.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-405_7_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.7.1 Slope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Landings shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Changes in level are not permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-405_7_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.7.2 Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The landing clear width shall be at least as wide as the widest ramp run leading to the landing.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-405_7_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.7.3 Length[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The landing clear length shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-405_7_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.7.4 Change in Direction[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramps that change direction between runs at landings shall have a clear landing 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum by 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-405_7_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.7.5 Doorways[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where doorways are located adjacent to a ramp landing, maneuvering clearances required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_4" class="navSectionLink">404.2.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_3_2" class="navSectionLink">404.3.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to overlap the required landing area.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.8 Handrails[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramp runs with a rise greater than 6 inches (150 mm) shall have handrails complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: Within employee work areas, handrails shall not be required where ramps that are part of common use circulation paths are designed to permit the installation of handrails complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramps not subject to the exception to[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_5" class="navSectionLink">405.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be designed to maintain a 36 inch (915 mm) minimum clear width when handrails are installed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-405_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.9 Edge Protection[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Edge protection complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_9_1" class="navSectionLink">405.9.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_9_2" class="navSectionLink">405.9.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on each side of ramp runs and at each side of ramp landings.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-405_9x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Edge protection shall not be required on ramps that are not required to have handrails and have sides complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-406_3" class="navSectionLink">406.3</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-405_9x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Edge protection shall not be required on the sides of ramp landings serving an adjoining ramp run or stairway.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-405_9x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Edge protection shall not be required on the sides of ramp landings having a vertical drop-off of 1/2 inch (13 mm) maximum within 10 inches (255 mm) horizontally of the minimum landing area specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_7" class="navSectionLink">405.7</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-405_9_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.9.1 Extended Floor or Ground Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The floor or ground surface of the ramp run or landing shall extend 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beyond the inside face of a handrail complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 405.9.1 Extended Floor or Ground Surface.  The extended surface prevents wheelchair casters and crutch tips from slipping off the ramp surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 405.9.1 Extended Floor or Ground Surface Edge Protection"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB29.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La sección transversal de una rampa con pasamanos se muestra donde la superficie de la rampa se extiende 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como mínimo hasta el exterior de los pasamanos".[-END TRANSLATE-]

The cross section of a ramp with handrails is shown where the ramp surface extends 12 inches (305 mm) minimum to the outside of the handrails.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-405_9_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.9.2 Curb or Barrier[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A curb or barrier shall be provided that prevents the passage of a 4 inch (100 mm) diameter sphere, where any portion of the sphere is within 4 inches (100 mm) of the finish floor or ground surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 405.9.2 Curb or Barrier Edge Protection"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB30.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación muestra un espacio libre vertical de menos de 4 pulgadas (100 mm) entre la superficie de la rampa y el borde inferior de un riel horizontal."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing shows a vertical clearance of less than 4 inches (100 mm) between the ramp surface and the bottom edge of a horizontal rail.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-405_10">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]405.10 Wet Conditions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Landings subject to wet conditions shall be designed to prevent the accumulation of water.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-406">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406 Curb Ramps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-406_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Curb ramps on accessible routes shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-406" class="navSectionLink">406</a>, <a href="#ada-405_2" class="navSectionLink">405.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_5" class="navSectionLink">405.5</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_10" class="navSectionLink">405.10</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-406_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.2 Counter Slope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Counter slopes of adjoining gutters and road surfaces immediately adjacent to the curb ramp shall not be steeper than 1:20.  The adjacent surfaces at transitions at curb ramps to walks, gutters, and streets shall be at the same level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 406.2 Counter Slope of Surfaces Adjacent to Curb Ramps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB31.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "En sección transversal, una rampa de bordillo con una pendiente máxima de 1:12 colinda con una superficie en la parte inferior que tiene una contrapensa máxima de 1:20."[-END TRANSLATE-]

In cross section, a curb ramp with a maximum slope of 1:12 adjoins a surface at the bottom that has a maximum counter slope of 1:20. 

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-406_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.3 Sides of Curb Ramps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, curb ramp flares shall not be steeper than 1:10.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 406.3 Sides of Curb Ramps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB32.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra una rampa de bordillo con lados acampanados triangulares.  Los lados acampanados tienen una pendiente máxima de 1:10, medida en la cara de la acera"[-END TRANSLATE-]

A curb ramp with triangular flared sides is shown.  The flared sides have a maximum 1:10 slope, measured at the curb face."[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-406_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.4 Landings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Landings shall be provided at the tops of curb ramps. The landing clear length shall be 36 inches (915 mm) minimum.  The landing clear width shall be at least as wide as the curb ramp, excluding flared sides, leading to the landing.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In alterations, where there is no landing at the top of curb ramps, curb ramp flares shall be provided and shall not be steeper than 1:12.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 406.4 Landings at the Top of Curb Ramps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB33.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista plana de una rampa de bordillo muestra el aterrizaje superior requerido que tiene una longitud de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) como mínimo en la dirección de la rampa y es al menos tan ancho como la rampa."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view of a curb ramp shows the required top landing which has a length of 36 inches (915 mm) minimum in the direction of the ramp run and is at least as wide as the ramp.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-406_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.5 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Curb ramps and the flared sides of curb ramps shall be located so that they do not project into vehicular traffic lanes, parking spaces, or parking access aisles.  Curb ramps at marked crossings shall be wholly contained within the markings, excluding any flared sides.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-406_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.6 Diagonal Curb Ramps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Diagonal or corner type curb ramps with returned curbs or other well-defined edges shall have the edges parallel to the direction of pedestrian flow.  The bottom of diagonal curb ramps shall have a clear space 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum outside active traffic lanes of the roadway.  Diagonal curb ramps provided at marked crossings shall provide the 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum clear space within the markings.  Diagonal curb ramps with flared sides shall have a segment of curb 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum located on each side of the curb ramp and within the marked crossing.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 406.6 Diagonal or Corner Type Curb Ramps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB34.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista en planta de una rampa diagonal de bordillo se muestra en un cruce marcado.  Un espacio de 48 pulgadas (220 mm) como mínimo, medido en la dirección de la carrera de rampa, se proporciona en la parte inferior de la rampa fuera de los carriles de tráfico activo y dentro del límite del cruce peatonal marcado.  Las secciones de bordillo de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) de longitud mínima se muestran más allá de los lados acampanados y dentro del cruce marcado."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view of a diagonal curb ramp is shown at a marked crossing.  A space 48 inches (220 mm) minimum, measured in the direction of the ramp run, is provided at the bottom of the ramp outside active traffic lanes and within the boundary of the marked pedestrian crossing.  Sections of curb 24 inches (610 mm) minimum in length are shown beyond the flared sides and within the marked crossing.  

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-406_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.7 Islands[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Raised islands in crossings shall be cut through level with the street or have curb ramps at both sides.  Each curb ramp shall have a level area 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum by 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum at the top of the curb ramp in the part of the island intersected by the crossings.  Each 48 inch (1220 mm) minimum by 36 inch (915 mm) minimum area shall be oriented so that the 48 inch (1220 mm) minimum length is in the direction of the running slope of the curb ramp it serves.  The 48 inch (1220 mm) minimum by 36 inch (915 mm) minimum areas and the accessible route shall be permitted to overlap.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 406.7 Islands in Crossings"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB35.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es una vista en planta de una isla peatonal elevada con una pasarela cortada al mismo nivel que el cruce de la calle.  La Figura (b) es una vista plana de una isla peatonal elevada entre dos carriles de tráfico.  Rampas de bordillo alineadas con bengalas laterales que se inclinan hacia abajo a cada lado.  El espacio nivelado entre la parte superior de ambas rampas es de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) de largo como mínimo.  El ancho de ambas rampas es de 36 pulgadas (915 mm)".[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is a plan view of a raised pedestrian island with a walkway cut through at the same level as the street crossing.  Figure (b) is a plan view of a raised pedestrian island between two traffic lanes.  Aligned curb ramps with side flares slope down on each side.  The level space between the top of both ramps is 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum.  The width of both ramp runs is 36 inches (915 mm).

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<div style="background-color: #eeeeee; border: 1px solid #000000;">
<h3 id="ada-406_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]406.8 Detectable Warnings.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards dot"><em>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Note to Reader:[-END TRANSLATE-]</em>&nbsp; [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The Department of Transportation’s ADA standards require detectable warnings on curb ramps:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
    <p>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A curb ramp shall have a detectable warning complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-705" class="navSectionLink">705</a>.&nbsp; [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]
The detectable warning shall extend the full width of the curb ramp (exclusive of flared sides) and shall extend either the full depth of the curb ramp or 24 inches (610 mm) deep minimum measured from the back of the curb on the ramp surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
<h2 id="ada-407">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407 Elevators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-407_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevators shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407" class="navSectionLink">407</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and with ASME A17.1 (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).  They shall be passenger elevators as classified by ASME A17.1.  Elevator operation shall be automatic.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 407.1 General.  The ADA and other Federal civil rights laws require that accessible features be maintained in working order so that they are accessible to and usable by those people they are intended to benefit.  Building owners should note that the ASME Safety Code for Elevators and Escalators requires routine maintenance and inspections.  Isolated or temporary interruptions in service due to maintenance or repairs may be unavoidable; however, failure to take prompt action to effect repairs could constitute a violation of Federal laws and these requirements.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-407_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2 Elevator Landing Requirements[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator landings shall comply with 407.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.1 Call Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where elevator call buttons or keypads are provided, they shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_1" class="navSectionLink">407.2.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Call buttons shall be raised or flush.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing elevators shall be permitted to have recessed call buttons.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.1.1 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Call buttons and keypads shall be located within one of the reach ranges specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]measured to the centerline of the highest operable part.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing call buttons and existing keypads shall be permitted to be located at 54 inches (1370 mm) maximum above the finish floor, measured to the centerline of the highest operable part.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.1.2 Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Call buttons shall be 3/4 inch (19 mm) minimum in the smallest dimension.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing elevator call buttons shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_1_2" class="navSectionLink">407.2.1.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_1_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.1.3 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided at call controls.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 407.2.1.3 Clear Floor or Ground Space.  The clear floor or ground space required at elevator call buttons must remain free of obstructions including ashtrays, plants, and other decorative elements that prevent wheelchair users and others from reaching the call buttons.  The height of the clear floor or ground space is considered to be a volume from the floor to 80 inches (2030 mm) above the floor.  Recessed ashtrays should not be placed near elevator call buttons so that persons who are blind or visually impaired do not inadvertently contact them or their contents as they reach for the call buttons.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_1_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.1.4 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The call button that designates the up direction shall be located above the call button that designates the down direction.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Destination-oriented elevators shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_1_4" class="navSectionLink">407.2.1.4</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 407.2.1.4 Location Exception.  A destination-oriented elevator system provides lobby controls enabling passengers to select floor stops, lobby indicators designating which elevator to use, and a car indicator designating the floors at which the car will stop.  Responding cars are programmed for maximum efficiency by reducing the number of stops any passenger experiences.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_1_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.1.5 Signals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Call buttons shall have visible signals to indicate when each call is registered and when each call is answered.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_1_5x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1. Destination-oriented elevators shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_1_5" class="navSectionLink">407.2.1.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]provided that visible and audible signals complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_2" class="navSectionLink">407.2.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]indicating which elevator car to enter are provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_1_5x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Existing elevators shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_1_5" class="navSectionLink">407.2.1.5</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_1_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.1.6 Keypads[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where keypads are provided, keypads shall be in a standard telephone keypad arrangement and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_7_2" class="navSectionLink">407.4.7.2</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.2 Hall Signals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Hall signals, including in-car signals, shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_2" class="navSectionLink">407.2.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.2.1 Visible and Audible Signals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A visible and audible signal shall be provided at each hoistway entrance to indicate which car is answering a call and the car’s direction of travel.  Where in-car signals are provided, they shall be visible from the floor area adjacent to the hall call buttons.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_2_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Visible and audible signals shall not be required at each destination-oriented elevator where a visible and audible signal complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_2" class="navSectionLink">407.2.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is provided indicating the elevator car designation information.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In existing elevators, a signal indicating the direction of car travel shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.2.2 Visible Signals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Visible signal fixtures shall be centered at 72 inches (1830 mm) minimum above the finish floor or ground.  The visible signal elements shall be 2 1/2 inches (64 mm) minimum measured along the vertical centerline of the element.  Signals shall be visible from the floor area adjacent to the hall call button.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_2_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Destination-oriented elevators shall be permitted to have signals visible from the floor area adjacent to the hoistway entrance.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_2_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Existing elevators shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_2_2" class="navSectionLink">407.2.2.2</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 407.2.2.2 Visible Hall Signals"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB36.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Las señales visibles se muestran centradas a 72 pulgadas (1830 mm) como mínimo sobre el suelo.  Los elementos individuales "arriba" y "abajo", uno con elementos circulares, otro con elementos triangulares, son de 21/2 pulgadas (64 mm) como mínimo medidos a lo largo de la línea central vertical del elemento."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Visible signals are shown centered at 72 inches (1830 mm) minimum above the floor ground.  The individual “up” and “down” elements, one with circular elements, another with triangular elements, are 2½ inches (64 mm) minimum measured along the vertical centerline of the element.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-407_2_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.2.3 Audible Signals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Audible signals shall sound once for the up direction and twice for the down direction, or shall have verbal annunciators that indicate the direction of elevator car travel.  Audible signals shall have a frequency of 1500 Hz maximum. Verbal annunciators shall have a frequency of 300 Hz minimum and 3000 Hz maximum.  The audible signal and verbal annunciator shall be 10 dB minimum above ambient, but shall not exceed 80 dB, measured at the hall call button.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_2_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Destination-oriented elevators shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_2_3" class="navSectionLink">407.2.2.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]provided that the audible tone and verbal announcement is the same as those given at the call button or call button keypad.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_2_2_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Existing elevators shall not be required to comply with the requirements for frequency and dB range of audible signals.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.2.4 Differentiation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each destination-oriented elevator in a bank of elevators shall have audible and visible means for differentiation.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.3 Hoistway Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs at elevator hoistways shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_3" class="navSectionLink">407.2.3</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_2_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.3.1 Floor Designation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floor designations complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_4_1" class="navSectionLink">703.4.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on both jambs of elevator hoistway entrances.  Floor designations shall be provided in both tactile characters and braille. Tactile characters shall be 2 inches (51 mm) high minimum. A tactile star shall be provided on both jambs at the main entry level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 407.2.3.1 Floor Designations on Jambs of Elevator Hoistway Entrances"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB37.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra un detalle ampliado de una designación de piso táctil.  El signo contiene una estrella y el número A1&quot; al lado, que tiene 2 pulgadas (51 mm) de alto; el equivalente en braille se proporciona debajo de cada uno."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An enlarged detail of a tactile floor designation is shown.  The sign contains a star and the number A1&quot; next to it which is 2 inches (51 mm) high; the braille equivalent is provided below each.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-407_2_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.2.3.2 Car Designations[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Destination-oriented elevators shall provide tactile car identification complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]on both jambs of the hoistway immediately below the floor designation. Car designations shall be provided in both tactile characters and braille. Tactile characters shall be 2 inches (51 mm) high minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 407.2.3.2 Car Designations on Jambs of Destination-Oriented Elevator Hoistway Entrances"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB38.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un detalle ampliado muestra la designación del automóvil debajo de la designación del piso.  La designación del automóvil es de 2 pulgadas (51 mm) de altura mínima con el equivalente en braille debajo de ella".[-END TRANSLATE-]

An enlarged detail shows the car designation below the floor designation.  The car designation is 2 inches (51 mm) minimum high with the braille equivalent below it.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-407_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3 Elevator Door Requirements[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Hoistway and car doors shall comply with 407.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.1 Type[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator doors shall be the horizontal sliding type.  Car gates shall be prohibited.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.2 Operation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator hoistway and car doors shall open and close automatically.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing manually operated hoistway swing doors shall be permitted provided that they comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_3" class="navSectionLink">404.2.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_9" class="navSectionLink">404.2.9</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Car door closing shall not be initiated until the hoistway door is closed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.3 Reopening Device[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator doors shall be provided with a reopening device complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_3_3" class="navSectionLink">407.3.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]that shall stop and reopen a car door and hoistway door automatically if the door becomes obstructed by an object or person.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing elevators with manually operated doors shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_3_3" class="navSectionLink">407.3.3</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_3_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.3.1 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The device shall be activated by sensing an obstruction passing through the opening at 5 inches (125 mm) nominal and 29 inches (735 mm) nominal above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_3_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.3.2 Contact[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The device shall not require physical contact to be activated, although contact is permitted to occur before the door reverses.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_3_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.3.3 Duration[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Door reopening devices shall remain effective for 20 seconds minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_3_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.4 Door and Signal Timing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The minimum acceptable time from notification that a car is answering a call or notification of the car assigned at the means for the entry of destination information until the doors of that car start to close shall be calculated from the following equation:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]T = D/(1.5 ft/s) or T = D/(455 mm/s) = 5 seconds minimum where T equals the total time in seconds and D equals the distance (in feet or millimeters) from the point in the lobby or corridor 60 inches (1525 mm) directly in front of the farthest call button controlling that car to the centerline of its hoistway door.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_3_4x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  For cars with in-car lanterns, T shall be permitted to begin when the signal is visible from the point 60 inches (1525 mm) directly in front of the farthest hall call button and the audible signal is sounded.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_3_4x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Destination-oriented elevators shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_3_4" class="navSectionLink">407.3.4</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_3_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.5 Door Delay[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator doors shall remain fully open in response to a car call for 3 seconds minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_3_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.3.6 Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The width of elevator doors shall comply with Table 407.4.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In existing elevators, a power-operated car door complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_3" class="navSectionLink">404.2.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-407_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4 Elevator Car Requirements[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator cars shall comply with 407.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.1 Car Dimensions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Inside dimensions of elevator cars and clear width of elevator doors shall comply with Table 407.4.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing elevator car configurations that provide a clear floor area of 16 square feet (1.5 m2) minimum and also provide an inside clear depth 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum and a clear width 36 inches (915 mm) minimum shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 407.4.1 Elevator Car Dimensions[-END TRANSLATE-] </caption>
