</ol>
</p>

<figure role="figure" aria-label="Figure (a) shows an elevator car with a centered door.  The door clear width is 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 80 inches (2030 mm) minimum.  The car depth is 51 inches (1295 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return, and 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the inside face of the door.  Figure (b) shows an elevator car with an off-centered door.  The door clear width is 36 inches (915 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 68 inches (1725 mm) minimum.  The depth is 51 inches (1295 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return, and 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the inside face of the door. Figure (c) shows a car with a clear door width of 36 inches (915 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum.  The car depth is 80 inches (2030 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return.  Figure (d) shows a car with a clear door width of 36 inches (915 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.  The car depth is 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return.  Figure (e) illustrates the exception for an existing elevator car configuration.  The car depth is 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum, the width is 39 inches (915 mm) minimum, and the clear floor area is 16 square feet (1.5 square m) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
>
<figcaption class="text-bold text-center">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Figure 407.4.1 Elevator Car Dimensions[-END TRANSLATE-]</figcaption>
<img class="img-large" src="{{ site.baseurl }}/images/ada-aba/standards/ADA-AB39.gif" alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-]"La figura (a) muestra un vagón elevador con una puerta centrada.  El ancho libre de la puerta es de 42 pulgadas (1065 mm) como mínimo y el ancho del automóvil medido de lado a lado es de 80 pulgadas (2030 mm) como mínimo.  La profundidad del automóvil es de 51 pulgadas (1295 mm) como mínimo medido desde la pared trasera hasta el retorno delantero, y 54 pulgadas (1370 mm) como mínimo medido desde la pared posterior hasta la cara interior de la puerta. La figura (b) muestra un vagón elevador con una puerta descentrada.  El ancho libre de la puerta es de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) como mínimo y el ancho del automóvil medido de lado a lado es de 68 pulgadas (1725 mm) como mínimo.  La profundidad es de 51 pulgadas (1295 mm) como mínimo medido desde la pared posterior hasta el retorno frontal, y 54 pulgadas (1370 mm) como mínimo medido desde la pared posterior hasta la cara interior de la puerta."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows an elevator car with a centered door.  The door clear width is 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 80 inches (2030 mm) minimum.  The car depth is 51 inches (1295 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return, and 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the inside face of the door.  Figure (b) shows an elevator car with an off-centered door.  The door clear width is 36 inches (915 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 68 inches (1725 mm) minimum.  The depth is 51 inches (1295 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return, and 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the inside face of the door.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]>
<img class="img-large" src="{{ site.baseurl }}/images/ada-aba/standards/ADA-AB40.gif" alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-]"La Figura (c) muestra un automóvil con un ancho de puerta claro de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) como mínimo y el ancho del automóvil medido de lado a lado es de 54 pulgadas (1370 mm) como mínimo.  La profundidad del automóvil es de 80 pulgadas (2030 mm) como mínimo medida desde la pared trasera hasta el retorno delantero.  La Figura (d) muestra un automóvil con un ancho de puerta claro de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) como mínimo y el ancho del automóvil medido de lado a lado es de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como mínimo. La profundidad del automóvil es de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como mínimo medida desde la pared trasera hasta el retorno delantero.  La figura e) ilustra la excepción para una configuración de ascensor existente.  La profundidad del automóvil es de 54 pulgadas (1370 mm) como mínimo, el ancho es de 39 pulgadas (915 mm) como mínimo y el área de piso clara es de 16 pies cuadrados (1.5 metros cuadrados) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (c) shows a car with a clear door width of 36 inches (915 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum.  The car depth is 80 inches (2030 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return.  Figure (d) shows a car with a clear door width of 36 inches (915 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.  The car depth is 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum measured from the back wall to the front return.  Figure (e) illustrates the exception for an existing elevator car configuration.  The car depth is 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum, the width is 39 inches (915 mm) minimum, and the clear floor area is 16 square feet (1.5 square m) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
>
</figure>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.2 Floor Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floor surfaces in elevator cars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303" class="navSectionLink">303</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.3 Platform to Hoistway Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The clearance between the car platform sill and the edge of any hoistway landing shall be 1 1/4 inch (32 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.4 Leveling[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each car shall be equipped with a self-leveling feature that will automatically bring and maintain the car at floor landings within a tolerance of 1/2 inch (13 mm) under rated loading to zero loading conditions.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.5 Illumination[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The level of illumination at the car controls, platform, car threshold and car landing sill shall be 5 foot candles (54 lux) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6 Elevator Car Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, elevator car controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_6" class="navSectionLink">407.4.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In existing elevators, where a new car operating panel complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_6" class="navSectionLink">407.4.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is provided, existing car operating panels shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_6" class="navSectionLink">407.4.6</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.1 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Controls shall be located within one of the reach ranges specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_4_6_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Where the elevator panel serves more than 16 openings and a parallel approach is provided, buttons with floor designations shall be permitted to be 54 inches (1370 mm) maximum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-407_4_6_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In existing elevators, car control buttons with floor designations shall be permitted to be located 54 inches (1370 mm) maximum above the finish floor where a parallel approach is provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.2 Buttons[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Car control buttons with floor designations shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_6_2" class="navSectionLink">407.4.6.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be raised or flush.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In existing elevators, buttons shall be permitted to be recessed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_6_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.2.1 Size.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Buttons shall be 3/4 inch (19 mm) minimum in their smallest dimension.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_6_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.2.2 Arrangement.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Buttons shall be arranged with numbers in ascending order.  When two or more columns of buttons are provided they shall read from left to right.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_6_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.3 Keypads[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Car control keypads shall be in a standard telephone keypad arrangement and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_7_2" class="navSectionLink">407.4.7.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_6_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.4 Emergency Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Emergency controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_6_4" class="navSectionLink">407.4.6.4</a>.</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_6_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.4.1 Height.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Emergency control buttons shall have their centerlines 35 inches (890 mm) minimum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_6_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.6.4.2 Location.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Emergency controls, including the emergency alarm, shall be grouped at the bottom of the panel.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.7 Designations and Indicators of Car Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Designations and indicators of car controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_7" class="navSectionLink">407.4.7</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: In existing elevators, where a new car operating panel complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_7" class="navSectionLink">407.4.7</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is provided, existing car operating panels shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_7" class="navSectionLink">407.4.7</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_7_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.7.1 Buttons[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Car control buttons shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_7_1" class="navSectionLink">407.4.7.1</a>.</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_7_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.7.1.1 Type.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Control buttons shall be identified by tactile characters complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a>.</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_7_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.7.1.2 Location.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Raised character and braille designations shall be placed immediately to the left of the control button to which the designations apply.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where space on an existing car operating panel precludes tactile markings to the left of the controls, markings shall be placed as near to the control as possible.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_7_1_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.7.1.3 Symbols.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The control button for the emergency stop, alarm, door open, door close, main entry floor, and phone, shall be identified with tactile symbols as shown in Table 407.4.7.1.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 407.4.7.1.3 Elevator Control Button Identification[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
