<h6 id="ada-407_4_7_1_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.7.1.4 Visible Indicators.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Buttons with floor designations shall be provided with visible indicators to show that a call has been registered.  The visible indication shall extinguish when the car arrives at the designated floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_7_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.7.2 Keypads[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Keypads shall be identified by characters complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be centered on the corresponding keypad button.  The number five key shall have a single raised dot.  The dot shall be 0.118 inch (3 mm) to 0.120 inch (3.05 mm) base diameter and in other aspects comply with Table 703.3.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8 Car Position Indicators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Audible and visible car position indicators shall be provided in elevator cars.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_8_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.1 Visible Indicators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Visible indicators shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_8_1" class="navSectionLink">407.4.8.1</a>.</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_8_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.1.1 Size.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters shall be 1/2 inch (13 mm) high minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_8_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.1.2 Location.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Indicators shall be located above the car control panel or above the door.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_8_1_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.1.3 Floor Arrival.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]As the car passes a floor and when a car stops at a floor served by the elevator, the corresponding character shall illuminate.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Destination-oriented elevators shall not be required to comply with 407.4.8.1.3 provided that the visible indicators extinguish when the call has been answered.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_8_1_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.1.4 Destination Indicator.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In destination-oriented elevators, a display shall be provided in the car with visible indicators to show car destinations.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-407_4_8_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.2 Audible Indicators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Audible indicators shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_8_2" class="navSectionLink">407.4.8.2</a>.</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_8_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.2.1 Signal Type.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The signal shall be an automatic verbal annunciator which announces the floor at which the car is about to stop.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  For elevators other than destination-oriented elevators that have a rated speed of 200 feet per minute (1 m/s) or less, a non-verbal audible signal with a frequency of 1500 Hz maximum which sounds as the car passes or is about to stop at a floor served by the elevator shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_8_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.2.2 Signal Level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The verbal annunciator shall be 10 dB minimum above ambient, but shall not exceed 80 dB, measured at the annunciator.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-407_4_8_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.8.2.3 Frequency.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The verbal annunciator shall have a frequency of 300 Hz minimum to 3000 Hz maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-407_4_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]407.4.9 Emergency Communication[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Emergency two-way communication systems shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Tactile symbols and characters shall be provided adjacent to the device and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-408">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408 Limited-Use / Limited-Application Elevators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-408_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Limited-use/limited-application elevators shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-408" class="navSectionLink">408</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and with ASME A17.1 (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).  They shall be passenger elevators as classified by ASME A17.1.  Elevator operation shall be automatic.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-408_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.2 Elevator Landings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Landings serving limited-use/limited-application elevators shall comply with 408.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.2.1 Call Buttons[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator call buttons and keypads shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_1" class="navSectionLink">407.2.1</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.2.2 Hall Signals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Hall signals shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_2" class="navSectionLink">407.2.2</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.2.3 Hoistway Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs at elevator hoistways shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_2_3_1" class="navSectionLink">407.2.3.1</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-408_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.3 Elevator Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator hoistway doors shall comply with 408.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.3.1 Sliding Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Sliding hoistway and car doors shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_3_1" class="navSectionLink">407.3.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_3_3" class="navSectionLink">407.3.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-408_4_1" class="navSectionLink">408.4.1</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.3.2 Swinging Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Swinging hoistway doors shall open and close automatically and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a>, <a href="#ada-407_3_2" class="navSectionLink">407.3.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and 408.3.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-408_3_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.3.2.1 Power Operation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Swinging doors shall be power-operated and shall comply with ANSI/BHMA A156.19 (1997 or 2002 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-408_3_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.3.2.2 Duration[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Power-operated swinging doors shall remain open for 20 seconds minimum when activated.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-408_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4 Elevator Cars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator cars shall comply with 408.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.1 Car Dimensions and Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator cars shall provide a clear width 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum and a clear depth 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum.  Car doors shall be positioned at the narrow ends of cars and shall provide 32 inches (815 mm) minimum clear width.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-408_4_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS: 1. Cars that provide a clear width 51 inches (1295 mm) minimum shall be permitted to provide a clear depth 51 inches (1295 mm) minimum provided that car doors provide a clear opening 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-408_4_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Existing elevator cars shall be permitted to provide a clear width 36 inches (915 mm) minimum, clear depth 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum, and a net clear platform area 15 square feet (1.4 m2) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 408.4.1 Limited-Use/Limited-Application (LULA) Elevator Car Dimensions"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB41.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra la configuración de la nueva construcción.  El ancho libre de la puerta es de 32 pulgadas (815 mm) como mínimo y el ancho del automóvil medido de lado a lado es de 42 pulgadas (1065 mm) como mínimo.  La profundidad del automóvil es de 54 pulgadas (1370 mm) como mínimo.  La figura b) ilustra la excepción 1.  El ancho de la puerta es de 36 pulgadas (815 mm) como mínimo y el automóvil tiene un espacio interior claro de 51 por 51 pulgadas (1295 por 1295 mm) como mínimo. La figura c) ilustra la excepción 2.  El ancho del automóvil es de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) como mínimo, la profundidad es de 54 pulgadas (1370 mm) como mínimo y el área neta clara del automóvil es de 15 pies cuadrados (1.4 metros cuadrados) como mínimo"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows the configuration for new construction.  The door clear width is 32 inches (815 mm) minimum and the car width measured side to side is 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum.  The car depth is 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum.  Figure (b) illustrates Exception 1.  The door width is 36 inches (815 mm) minimum and the car has a clear interior space 51 by 51 inches (1295 by 1295 mm) minimum.  Figure (c) illustrates Exception 2.  The car width is 36 inches (915 mm) minimum, the depth is 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum, and the net clear car area is 15 square feet (1.4 square m) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-408_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.2 Floor Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floor surfaces in elevator cars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303" class="navSectionLink">303</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.3 Platform to Hoistway Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The platform to hoistway clearance shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_3" class="navSectionLink">407.4.3</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.4 Leveling[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator car leveling shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_4" class="navSectionLink">407.4.4</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_4_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.5 Illumination[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator car illumination shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_5" class="navSectionLink">407.4.5</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_4_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.6 Car Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator car controls shall comply with 407.4.6.  Control panels shall be centered on a side wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_4_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.7 Designations and Indicators of Car Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Designations and indicators of car controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_7" class="navSectionLink">407.4.7</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-408_4_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]408.4.8 Emergency Communications[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Car emergency signaling devices complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_9" class="navSectionLink">407.4.9</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-409">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409 Private Residence Elevators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-409_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Private residence elevators that are provided within a residential dwelling unit required to provide mobility features complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_2" class="navSectionLink">809.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_4" class="navSectionLink">809.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-409" class="navSectionLink">409</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and with ASME A17.1 (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1). They shall be passenger elevators as classified by ASME A17.1.  Elevator operation shall be automatic.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-409_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.2 Call Buttons[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Call buttons shall be 3/4 inch (19 mm) minimum in the smallest dimension and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-409_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.3 Elevator Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Hoistway doors, car doors, and car gates shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-409_3" class="navSectionLink">409.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Doors shall not be required to comply with the maneuvering clearance requirements in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_4_1" class="navSectionLink">404.2.4.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]for approaches to the push side of swinging doors.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.3.1 Power Operation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator car and hoistway doors and gates shall be power operated and shall comply with ANSI/BHMA A156.19 (1997 or 2002 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).  Power operated doors and gates shall remain open for 20 seconds minimum when activated.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In elevator cars with more than one opening, hoistway doors and gates shall be permitted to be of the manual-open, self-close type.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.3.2 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator car doors or gates shall be positioned at the narrow end of the clear floor spaces required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-409_4_1" class="navSectionLink">409.4.1</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-409_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4 Elevator Cars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Private residence elevator cars shall comply with 409.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.1 Inside Dimensions of Elevator Cars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator cars shall provide a clear floor space of 36 inches (915 mm) minimum by 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.2 Floor Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floor surfaces in elevator cars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303" class="navSectionLink">303</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.3 Platform to Hoistway Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The clearance between the car platform and the edge of any landing sill shall be 1 1/2 inch (38 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.4 Leveling[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each car shall automatically stop at a floor landing within a tolerance of 1/2 inch (13 mm) under rated loading to zero loading conditions.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_4_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.5 Illumination Levels[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator car illumination shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-407_4_5" class="navSectionLink">407.4.5</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-409_4_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.6 Car Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Elevator car control buttons shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-409_4_6" class="navSectionLink">409.4.6</a>, <a href="#ada-309_3" class="navSectionLink">309.3</a>, <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be raised or flush.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-409_4_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.6.1 Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Control buttons shall be 3/4 inch (19 mm) minimum in their smallest dimension.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-409_4_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.6.2 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Control panels shall be on a side wall, 12 inches (305 mm) minimum from any adjacent wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 409.4.6.2 Location of Private Residence Elevator Control Panel"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB42.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de planta muestra un ascensor con una puerta de elevación abatible.  El panel de control se muestra en la pared lateral del automóvil a 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como mínimo desde la parte delantera"[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows an elevator with an out-swinging hoistway door.  The control panel is shown on the car side wall 12 inches (305 mm) minimum from the front.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-409_4_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.7 Emergency Communications[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Emergency two-way communication systems shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-409_4_7" class="navSectionLink">409.4.7</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-409_4_7_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.7.1 Type[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A telephone and emergency signal device shall be provided in the car.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-409_4_7_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.7.2 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The telephone and emergency signaling device shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_3" class="navSectionLink">309.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-409_4_7_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.7.3 Compartment[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]If the telephone or device is in a closed compartment, the compartment door hardware shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-409_4_7_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]409.4.7.4 Cord[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The telephone cord shall be 29 inches (735 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-410">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]410 Platform Lifts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-410_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]410.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Platform lifts shall comply with ASME A18.1 (1999 edition or 2003 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1). Platform lifts shall not be attendant-operated and shall provide unassisted entry and exit from the lift.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 410.1 General.  Inclined stairway chairlifts and inclined and vertical platform lifts are available for short-distance vertical transportation.  Because an accessible route requires an 80 inch (2030 mm) vertical clearance, care should be taken in selecting lifts as they may not be equally suitable for use by people using wheelchairs and people standing.  If a lift does not provide 80 inch (2030 mm) vertical clearance, it cannot be considered part of an accessible route in new construction.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="last">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The ADA and other Federal civil rights laws require that accessible features be maintained in working order so that they are accessible to and usable by those people they are intended to benefit.  Building owners are reminded that the ASME A18 Safety Standard for Platform Lifts and Stairway Chairlifts requires routine maintenance and inspections.  Isolated or temporary interruptions in service due to maintenance or repairs may be unavoidable; however, failure to take prompt action to effect repairs could constitute a violation of Federal laws and these requirements.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
<h3 id="ada-410_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]410.2 Floor Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floor surfaces in platform lifts shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303" class="navSectionLink">303</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-410_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]410.3 Clear Floor Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clear floor space in platform lifts shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-410_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]410.4 Platform to Runway Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The clearance between the platform sill and the edge of any runway landing shall be 1 1/4 inch (32 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-410_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]410.5 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Controls for platform lifts shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-410_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]410.6 Doors and Gates[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Platform lifts shall have low-energy power-operated doors or gates complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_3" class="navSectionLink">404.3</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doors shall remain open for 20 seconds minimum.  End doors and gates shall provide a clear width 32 inches (815 mm) minimum.  Side doors and gates shall provide a clear width 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: Platform lifts serving two landings maximum and having doors or gates on opposite sides shall be permitted to have self-closing manual doors or gates.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 410.6 Platform Lift Doors and Gates"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB43.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una plataforma elevadora rectangular se muestra en la vista de planta con una puerta final de 32 pulgadas (815 mm) como mínimo, y una puerta lateral de 42 pulgadas (1065 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A rectangular lift platform is shown in plan view with an end door 32 inches (815 mm) minimum, and a side door 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
  <h1></h1> <!--empty last heading for kms load function to work-->
  </div>   <!--close #adaCh4-->
  <div id="adaCh5">
  <h1 id="a5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Chapter 5: General Site and Building Elements[-END TRANSLATE-]</h1>
  <h2 id="ada-501">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]501 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-501_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]501.1 Scope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The provisions of Chapter 5 shall apply where required by Chapter 2 or where referenced by a requirement in this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-502">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502 Parking Spaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-502_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Car and van parking spaces shall comply with 502.  Where parking spaces are marked with lines, width measurements of parking spaces and access aisles shall be made from the centerline of the markings.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where parking spaces or access aisles are not adjacent to another parking space or access aisle, measurements shall be permitted to include the full width of the line defining the parking space or access aisle.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-502_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.2 Vehicle Spaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Car parking spaces shall be 96 inches (2440 mm) wide minimum and van parking spaces shall be 132 inches (3350 mm) wide minimum, shall be marked to define the width, and shall have an adjacent access aisle complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-502_3" class="navSectionLink">502.3</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Van parking spaces shall be permitted to be 96 inches (2440 mm) wide minimum where the access aisle is 96 inches (2440 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 502.2 Vehicle Parking Spaces"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB44.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Dos espacios de estacionamiento marcados se muestran en la vista del plano.  El espacio para el automóvil es de 96 pulgadas (2440 mm) de ancho como mínimo y el espacio de la camioneta es de 132 pulgadas (3350 mm) de ancho como mínimo, con un pasillo de acceso entre ellos."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Two marked parking spaces are shown in plan view.  The car space is 96 inches (2440 mm) wide minimum and the van space is 132 inches (3350 mm) wide minimum, with an access aisle between them.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-502_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.3 Access Aisle[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles serving parking spaces shall comply with 502.3.  Access aisles shall adjoin an accessible route.  Two parking spaces shall be permitted to share a common access aisle.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 502.3 Access Aisle.  Accessible routes must connect parking spaces to accessible entrances.  In parking facilities where the accessible route must cross vehicular traffic lanes, marked crossings enhance pedestrian safety, particularly for people using wheelchairs and other mobility aids.  Where possible, it is preferable that the accessible route not pass behind parked vehicles.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 502.3 Parking Space Access Aisle"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB45.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una furgoneta y una plaza de aparcamiento se muestran en la vista del plano compartiendo un pasillo de acceso.  Se muestra que el pasillo de acceso tiene un mínimo de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de ancho y es tan largo como el espacio de estacionamiento.  Se marcará toda la longitud del área del pasillo"[-END TRANSLATE-]

A van and a car parking space are shown in plan view sharing an access aisle.  The access aisle is shown to be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and as long as the parking space.  The entire length of the aisle area is to be marked.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-502_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.3.1 Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles serving car and van parking spaces shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-502_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.3.2 Length[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles shall extend the full length of the parking spaces they serve.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-502_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.3.3 Marking[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles shall be marked so as to discourage parking in them.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 502.3.3 Marking.  The method and color of marking are not specified by these requirements but may be addressed by State or local laws or regulations.  Because these requirements permit the van access aisle to be as wide as a parking space, it is important that the aisle be clearly marked.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-502_3_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.3.4 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles shall not overlap the vehicular way.  Access aisles shall be permitted to be placed on either side of the parking space except for angled van parking spaces which shall have access aisles located on the passenger side of the parking spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 502.3.4 Location.  Wheelchair lifts typically are installed on the passenger side of vans.  Many drivers, especially those who operate vans, find it more difficult to back into parking spaces than to back out into comparatively unrestricted vehicular lanes.  For this reason, where a van and car share an access aisle, consider locating the van space so that the access aisle is on the passenger side of the van space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-502_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.4 Floor or Ground Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking spaces and access aisles serving them shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles shall be at the same level as the parking spaces they serve.  Changes in level are not permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 502.4 Floor or Ground Surfaces.  Access aisles are required to be nearly level in all directions to provide a surface for wheelchair transfer to and from vehicles.  The exception allows sufficient slope for drainage.  Built-up curb ramps are not permitted to project into access aisles and parking spaces because they would create slopes greater than 1:48.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-502_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.5 Vertical Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking spaces for vans and access aisles and vehicular routes serving them shall provide a vertical clearance of 98 inches (2490 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 502.5 Vertical Clearance.  Signs provided at entrances to parking facilities informing drivers of clearances and the location of van accessible parking spaces can provide useful customer assistance.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-502_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.6 Identification[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking space identification signs shall include the International Symbol of Accessibility complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_1" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.1</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs identifying van parking spaces shall contain the designation “van accessible.”  Signs shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum above the finish floor or ground surface measured to the bottom of the sign.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 502.6 Identification.  The required “van accessible” designation is intended to be informative, not restrictive, in identifying those spaces that are better suited for van use.  Enforcement of motor vehicle laws, including parking privileges, is a local matter.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-502_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]502.7 Relationship to Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parking spaces and access aisles shall be designed so that cars and vans, when parked, cannot obstruct the required clear width of adjacent accessible routes.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 502.7 Relationship to Accessible Routes.  Wheel stops are an effective way to prevent vehicle overhangs from reducing the clear width of accessible routes.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-503">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503 Passenger Loading Zones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-503_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Passenger loading zones shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-503" class="navSectionLink">503</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-503_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.2 Vehicle Pull-Up Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Passenger loading zones shall provide a vehicular pull-up space 96 inches (2440 mm) wide minimum and 20 feet (6100 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-503_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.3 Access Aisle[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Passenger loading zones shall provide access aisles complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-503" class="navSectionLink">503</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]adjacent to the vehicle pull-up space.  Access aisles shall adjoin an accessible route and shall not overlap the vehicular way.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-503_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.3.1 Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles serving vehicle pull-up spaces shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-503_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.3.2 Length[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles shall extend the full length of the vehicle pull-up spaces they serve.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-503_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.3.3 Marking[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles shall be marked so as to discourage parking in them.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 503.3 Passenger Loading Zone Access Aisle"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB46.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra que un pasillo de acceso en una zona de carga de pasajeros es la longitud completa del espacio de extracción del vehículo y un mínimo de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de ancho.  El área del pasillo debe ser marcada"[-END TRANSLATE-]

An access aisle at a passenger loading zone is shown to be the full length of the vehicle pull-up space and 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum.  The aisle area is to be marked.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-503_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.4 Floor and Ground Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Vehicle pull-up spaces and access aisles serving them shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Access aisles shall be at the same level as the vehicle pull-up space they serve. Changes in level are not permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-503_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]503.5 Vertical Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Vehicle pull-up spaces, access aisles serving them, and a vehicular route from an entrance to the passenger loading zone, and from the passenger loading zone to a vehicular exit shall provide a vertical clearance of 114 inches (2895 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-504">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504 Stairways[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-504_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Stairs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-504_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504.2 Treads and Risers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All steps on a flight of stairs shall have uniform riser heights and uniform tread depths.  Risers shall be 4 inches (100 mm) high minimum and 7 inches (180 mm) high maximum.  Treads shall be 11 inches (280 mm) deep minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-504_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504.3 Open Risers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Open risers are not permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-504_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504.4 Tread Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Stair treads shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Changes in level are not permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Treads shall be permitted to have a slope not steeper than 1:48.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 504.4 Tread Surface.  Consider providing visual contrast on tread nosings, or at the leading edges of treads without nosings, so that stair treads are more visible for people with low vision.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-504_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504.5 Nosings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The radius of curvature at the leading edge of the tread shall be ½ inch (13 mm) maximum. Nosings that project beyond risers shall have the underside of the leading edge curved or beveled.  Risers shall be permitted to slope under the tread at an angle of 30 degrees maximum from vertical.  The permitted projection of the nosing shall extend 1½ (38 mm) maximum over the tread below.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 504.5 Stair Nosings"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB55.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) muestra elevadores verticales donde el radio de curvatura del borde de ataque de cada banda de rodadura es de 1/2 pulgada (13 mm) como máximo.  La figura (b) muestra los elevadores en ángulo.  Los elevadores pueden inclinarse en un ángulo de 30 grados máximo desde la vertical.  Las figuras c) y d) muestran narices curvas y biseladas, respectivamente.  La proyección máxima de la nariz es de 11/2 pulgadas (38 mm) más allá de la parte trasera de la banda de rodadura de abajo"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows vertical risers where the radius of curvature of the leading edge of each tread is ½ inch (13 mm) maximum.  Figure (b) shows angled risers.  Risers can slope at an angle of 30 degrees maximum from the vertical.  Figures (c) and (d) show curved and beveled nosings, respectively.  The maximum projection of the nosing is 1½ inches (38 mm) beyond the rear of the tread below.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-504_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504.6 Handrails[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Stairs shall have handrails complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-504_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]504.7 Wet Conditions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Stair treads and landings subject to wet conditions shall be designed to prevent the accumulation of water.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-505">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505 Handrails[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-505_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrails provided along walking surfaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-403" class="navSectionLink">403</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]required at ramps complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405" class="navSectionLink">405</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and required at stairs complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 505.1 General.  Handrails are required on ramp runs with a rise greater than 6 inches (150 mm) (see 405.8) and on certain stairways (see 504).  Handrails are not required on walking surfaces with running slopes less than 1:20.  However, handrails are required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]when they are provided on walking surfaces with running slopes less than 1:20 (see 403.6).  Sections[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505_2" class="navSectionLink">505.2</a>, <a href="#ada-505_3" class="navSectionLink">505.3</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and 505.10 do not apply to handrails provided on walking surfaces with running slopes less than 1:20 as these sections only reference requirements for ramps and stairs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-505_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.2 Where Required[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrails shall be provided on both sides of stairs and ramps.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In assembly areas, handrails shall not be required on both sides of aisle ramps where a handrail is provided at either side or within the aisle width.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-505_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.3 Continuity[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrails shall be continuous within the full length of each stair flight or ramp run.  Inside handrails on switchback or dogleg stairs and ramps shall be continuous between flights or runs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In assembly areas, handrails on ramps shall not be required to be continuous in aisles serving seating.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-505_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.4 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Top of gripping surfaces of handrails shall be 34 inches (865 mm) minimum and 38 inches (965 mm) maximum vertically above walking surfaces, stair nosings, and ramp surfaces.  Handrails shall be at a consistent height above walking surfaces, stair nosings, and ramp surfaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 505.4 Height.  The requirements for stair and ramp handrails in this document are for adults.  When children are the principal users in a building or facility (e.g., elementary schools), a second set of handrails at an appropriate height can assist them and aid in preventing accidents.  A maximum height of 28 inches (710 mm) measured to the top of the gripping surface from the ramp surface or stair nosing is recommended for handrails designed for children.  Sufficient vertical clearance between upper and lower handrails, 9 inches (230 mm) minimum, should be provided to help prevent entrapment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 505.4 Handrail Height"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB56.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) muestra escaleras con la superficie de agarre superior de un pasamanos de 34 a 38 pulgadas (865 a 965 mm) por encima de las narices de las escaleras.  Las figuras (b) y (c) muestran rampas y superficies para caminar, respectivamente.  La superficie de agarre superior de un pasamanos es de 34 a 38 pulgadas (865 a 965 mm) por encima de la superficie"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows stairs with the top gripping surface of a handrail 34 to 38 inches (865 to 965 mm) above stair nosings.  Figures (b) and (c) show ramps and walking surfaces, respectively.  The top gripping surface of a handrail is 34 to 38 inches (865 to 965 mm) above the surface.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-505_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.5 Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearance between handrail gripping surfaces and adjacent surfaces shall be 1½ inches (38 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 505.5 Handrail Clearance"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB57.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra que el espacio libre entre el pasamanos y la pared es de 11/2 pulgadas (38 mm) como mínimo"[-END TRANSLATE-]

The clearance between the handrail and wall is shown to be 1½ inches (38 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-505_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.6 Gripping Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrail gripping surfaces shall be continuous along their length and shall not be obstructed along their tops or sides.  The bottoms of handrail gripping surfaces shall not be obstructed for more than 20 percent of their length.  Where provided, horizontal projections shall occur 1½ (38 mm) minimum below the bottom of the handrail gripping surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-505_6x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Where handrails are provided along walking surfaces with slopes not steeper than 1:20, the bottoms of handrail gripping surfaces shall be permitted to be obstructed along their entire length where they are integral to crash rails or bumper guards.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-505_6x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  The distance between horizontal projections and the bottom of the gripping surface shall be permitted to be reduced by 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) for each ½ inch (13 mm) of additional handrail perimeter dimension that exceeds 4 inches (100 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 505.6 Gripping Surface.  People with disabilities, older people, and others benefit from continuous gripping surfaces that permit users to reach the fingers outward or downward to grasp the handrail, particularly as the user senses a loss of equilibrium or begins to fall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 505.6 Horizontal Projections Below Gripping Surface"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB58.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una barandilla con soportes unidos a la superficie inferior se muestra en sección transversal.  La proyección horizontal del soporte desde la pared es de 11/2 pulgadas (38 mm) por debajo de la parte inferior de la barandilla"[-END TRANSLATE-]

A handrail with brackets attached to the bottom surface is shown in cross section.  The horizontal projection of the bracket from the wall is 1½ inches (38 mm) below the bottom of the handrail.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-505_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.7 Cross Section[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrail gripping surfaces shall have a cross section complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505_7_1" class="navSectionLink">505.7.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505_7_2" class="navSectionLink">505.7.2</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-505_7_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.7.1 Circular Cross Section[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrail gripping surfaces with a circular cross section shall have an outside diameter of 1¼ inches (32 mm) minimum and 2 inches (51 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-505_7_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.7.2 Non-Circular Cross Sections[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrail gripping surfaces with a non-circular cross section shall have a perimeter dimension of 4 inches (100 mm) minimum and 6¼ inches (160 mm) maximum, and a cross-section dimension of 2¼ inches (57 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 505.7.2 Handrail Non-Circular Cross Section"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB51.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra una barandilla con una sección transversal aproximadamente cuadrada y la figura (c) muestra una sección transversal elíptica.  La dimensión de sección transversal más grande es de 21/4 pulgadas (57 mm) como máximo.  La dimensión perimetral debe ser de 4 a 61/4 pulgadas (100 a 160 mm)"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a handrail with an approximately square cross section and figure (c) shows an elliptical cross section.  The largest cross section dimension is 2¼ inches (57 mm) maximum.  The perimeter dimension must be 4 to 6¼ inches (100 to 160 mm).

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-505_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.8 Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrail gripping surfaces and any surfaces adjacent to them shall be free of sharp or abrasive elements and shall have rounded edges.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-505_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.9 Fittings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrails shall not rotate within their fittings.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-505_10">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.10 Handrail Extensions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrail gripping surfaces shall extend beyond and in the same direction of stair flights and ramp runs in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505_10" class="navSectionLink">505.10</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-505_10x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Extensions shall not be required for continuous handrails at the inside turn of switchback or dogleg stairs and ramps.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-505_10x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In assembly areas, extensions shall not be required for ramp handrails in aisles serving seating where the handrails are discontinuous to provide access to seating and to permit crossovers within aisles.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-505_10x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  In alterations, full extensions of handrails shall not be required where such extensions would be hazardous due to plan configuration.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-505_10_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.10.1 Top and Bottom Extension at Ramps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramp handrails shall extend horizontally above the landing for 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beyond the top and bottom of ramp runs.  Extensions shall return to a wall, guard, or the landing surface, or shall be continuous to the handrail of an adjacent ramp run.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 505.10.1 Top and Bottom Handrail Extension at Ramps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB52.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra que los pasamanos de rampa en la parte superior e inferior se extienden horizontalmente por encima del aterrizaje 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como mínimo desde la rampa.  Las extensiones vuelven a los puestos"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Ramp handrails at the top and bottom are shown to extend horizontally above the landing 12 inches (305 mm) minimum from the ramp run.  The extensions return to posts.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-505_10_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.10.2 Top Extension at Stairs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At the top of a stair flight, handrails shall extend horizontally above the landing for 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beginning directly above the first riser nosing.  Extensions shall return to a wall, guard, or the landing surface, or shall be continuous to the handrail of an adjacent stair flight.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 505.10.2 Top Handrail Extension at Stairs"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB53.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El pasamanos se extiende horizontalmente por encima del rellano durante un mínimo de 12 pulgadas (305 mm) comenzando directamente sobre la primera nariz del elevador"[-END TRANSLATE-]

The handrail extends horizontally above the landing for 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beginning directly above the first riser nosing.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-505_10_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]505.10.3 Bottom Extension at Stairs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At the bottom of a stair flight, handrails shall extend at the slope of the stair flight for a horizontal distance at least equal to one tread depth beyond the last riser nosing.  Extension shall return to a wall, guard, or the landing surface, or shall be continuous to the handrail of an adjacent stair flight.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 505.10.3 Bottom Handrail Extension at Stairs"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB54.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra que una barandilla se extiende en la pendiente del vuelo de la escalera para una distancia horizontal igual a una profundidad de la banda de rodadura más allá de la última nariz ascendente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A handrail is shown to extend at the slope of the stair flight for a horizontal distance equal to one tread depth beyond the last riser nosing.  

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
  <h1></h1> <!--empty last heading for kms load function to work-->
  </div>   <!--close #adaCh5-->
  <div id="adaCh6">
  <h1 id="a6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Chapter 6: Plumbing Elements and Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h1>
  <h2 id="ada-601">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]601 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-601_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]601.1 Scope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The provisions of Chapter 6 shall apply where required by Chapter 2 or where referenced by a requirement in this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-602">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602 Drinking Fountains[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-602_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Drinking fountains shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-307" class="navSectionLink">307</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-602" class="navSectionLink">602</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-602_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602.2 Clear Floor Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Units shall have a clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for a forward approach and centered on the unit.  Knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  A parallel approach complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted at units for children’s use where the spout is 30 inches (760 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground and is 3½ inches (90 mm) maximum from the front edge of the unit, including bumpers.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-602_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602.3 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Operable parts shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-602_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602.4 Spout Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Spout outlets shall be 36 inches (915 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-602_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602.5 Spout Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The spout shall be located 15 inches (380 mm) minimum from the vertical support and 5 inches (125 mm) maximum from the front edge of the unit, including bumpers.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 602.5 Drinking Fountain Spout Location"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB59.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "En la vista del plano, se muestra que el caño tiene un mínimo de 15 pulgadas (380 mm) desde el soporte vertical y 5 pulgadas (125 mm) desde el borde frontal de la unidad."[-END TRANSLATE-]

In plan view, the spout is shown to be 15 inches (380 mm) minimum from the vertical support and 5 inches (125 mm) from the front edge of the unit.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-602_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602.6 Water Flow[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The spout shall provide a flow of water 4 inches (100 mm) high minimum and shall be located 5 inches (125 mm) maximum from the front of the unit.  The angle of the water stream shall be measured horizontally relative to the front face of the unit.  Where spouts are located less than 3 inches (75 mm) of the front of the unit, the angle of the water stream shall be 30 degrees maximum.  Where spouts are located between 3 inches (75 mm) and 5 inches (125 mm) maximum from the front of the unit, the angle of the water stream shall be 15 degrees maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 602.6 Water Flow.  The purpose of requiring the drinking fountain spout to produce a flow of water 4 inches (100 mm) high minimum is so that a cup can be inserted under the flow of water to provide a drink of water for an individual who, because of a disability, would otherwise be incapable of using the drinking fountain.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-602_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]602.7 Drinking Fountains for Standing Persons[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Spout outlets of drinking fountains for standing persons shall be 38 inches (965 mm) minimum and 43 inches (1090 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-603">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603 Toilet and Bathing Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-603_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet and bathing rooms shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-603_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603.2 Clearances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearances shall comply with 603.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-603_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603.2.1 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided within the room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-603_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603.2.2 Overlap[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Required clear floor spaces, clearance at fixtures, and turning space shall be permitted to overlap.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-603_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603.2.3 Door Swing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doors shall not swing into the clear floor space or clearance required for any fixture.  Doors shall be permitted to swing into the required turning space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-603_2_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Doors to a toilet room or bathing room for a single occupant accessed only through a private office and not for common use or public use shall be permitted to swing into the clear floor space or clearance provided the swing of the door can be reversed to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603_2_3" class="navSectionLink">603.2.3</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-603_2_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where the toilet room or bathing room is for individual use and a clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305_3" class="navSectionLink">305.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is provided within the room beyond the arc of the door swing, doors shall be permitted to swing into the clear floor space or clearance required for any fixture.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 603.2.3 Door Swing Exception 1.  At the time the door is installed, and if the door swing is reversed in the future, the door must meet all the requirements specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Additionally, the door swing cannot reduce the required width of an accessible route. Also, avoid violating other building or life safety codes when the door swing is reversed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-603_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603.3 Mirrors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Mirrors located above lavatories or countertops shall be installed with the bottom edge of the reflecting surface 40 inches (1015 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.  Mirrors not located above lavatories or countertops shall be installed with the bottom edge of the reflecting surface 35 inches (890 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 603.3 Mirrors.  A single full-length mirror can accommodate a greater number of people, including children.  In order for mirrors to be usable by people who are ambulatory and people who use wheelchairs, the top edge of mirrors should be 74 inches (1880 mm) minimum from the floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-603_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]603.4 Coat Hooks and Shelves[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Coat hooks shall be located within one of the reach ranges specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Shelves shall be located 40 inches (1015 mm) minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-604">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604 Water Closets and Toilet Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-604_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Water closets and toilet compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_2" class="navSectionLink">604.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8" class="navSectionLink">604.8</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Water closets and toilet compartments for children’s use shall be permitted to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_9" class="navSectionLink">604.9</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-604_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.2 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The water closet shall be positioned with a wall or partition to the rear and to one side.  The centerline of the water closet shall be 16 inches (405 mm) minimum to 18 inches (455 mm) maximum from the side wall or partition, except that the water closet shall be 17 inches (430 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum from the side wall or partition in the ambulatory accessible toilet compartment specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_2" class="navSectionLink">604.8.2</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Water closets shall be arranged for a left-hand or right-hand approach.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.2 Water Closet Location"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB60.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra un armario de agua accesible para sillas de ruedas, con espacio en un lado, y la figura (b) muestra un armario de agua accesible ambulatorio, con paredes de puestos y barras de agarre en ambos lados.  Se muestra que la línea central del armario de agua está a 16 a 18 pulgadas (405 a 455 mm) de la pared lateral."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a wheelchair accessible water closet, with space on one side, and figure (b) shows an ambulatory accessible water closet, with stall walls and grab bars on both sides.  The water closet centerline is shown to be 16 to 18 inches (405 to 455 mm) from the side wall.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-604_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.3 Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearances around water closets and in toilet compartments shall comply with 604.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.3.1 Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearance around a water closet shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum measured perpendicular from the side wall and 56 inches (1420 mm) minimum measured perpendicular from the rear wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.3.1 Size of Clearance at Water Closets"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB61.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El espacio libre alrededor de un armario de agua se muestra en la vista del plano para ser de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de ancho mínimo y 56 pulgadas (1420 mm) de profundidad mínimo"[-END TRANSLATE-]

The clearance around a water closet is shown in plan view to be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and 56 inches (1420 mm) deep minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-604_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.3.2 Overlap[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The required clearance around the water closet shall be permitted to overlap the water closet, associated grab bars, dispensers, sanitary napkin disposal units, coat hooks, shelves, accessible routes, clear floor space and clearances required at other fixtures, and the turning space.  No other fixtures or obstructions shall be located within the required water closet clearance.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In residential dwelling units, a lavatory complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-606" class="navSectionLink">606</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted on the rear wall 18 inches (455 mm) minimum from the water closet centerline where the clearance at the water closet is 66 inches (1675 mm) minimum measured perpendicular from the rear wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 604.3.2 Overlap.  When the door to the toilet room is placed directly in front of the water closet, the water closet cannot overlap the required maneuvering clearance for the door inside the room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.3.2 (Exception) Overlap of Water Closet Clearance in Residential Dwelling Units"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB62.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El espacio libre alrededor de un armario de agua se muestra en la vista de plan de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de ancho mínimo y 66 pulgadas (1675 mm) de profundidad mínimo con un baño permitido en la pared real si la distancia entre el borde del baño más cercano y la línea central del armario de agua es de 18 pulgadas (455 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

The clearance around a water closet is shown in plan view to be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and 66 inches (1675 mm) deep minimum with a lavatory permitted on the real wall if the distance between the lavatory nearest edge and the water closet center line is 18 inches (455 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-604_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.4 Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The seat height of a water closet above the finish floor shall be 17 inches (430 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum measured to the top of the seat.  Seats shall not be sprung to return to a lifted position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-604_4x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  A water closet in a toilet room for a single occupant accessed only through a private office and not for common use or public use shall not be required to comply with 604.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-604_4x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In residential dwelling units, the height of water closets shall be permitted to be 15 inches (380 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum above the finish floor measured to the top of the seat.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-604_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.5 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars for water closets shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall be provided on the side wall closest to the water closet and on the rear wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-604_5x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Grab bars shall not be required to be installed in a toilet room for a single occupant accessed only through a private office and not for common use or public use provided that reinforcement has been installed in walls and located so as to permit the installation of grab bars complying with 604.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-604_5x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In residential dwelling units, grab bars shall not be required to be installed in toilet or bathrooms provided that reinforcement has been installed in walls and located so as to permit the installation of grab bars complying with 604.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-604_5x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  In detention or correction facilities, grab bars shall not be required to be installed in housing or holding cells that are specially designed without protrusions for purposes of suicide prevention.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 604.5 Grab Bars Exception 2.  Reinforcement must be sufficient to permit the installation of rear and side wall grab bars that fully meet all accessibility requirements including, but not limited to, required length, installation height, and structural strength.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.5.1 Side Wall[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The side wall grab bar shall be 42 inches (1065 mm) long minimum, located 12 inches (305 mm) maximum from the rear wall and extending 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum from the rear wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.5.1 Side Wall Grab Bar at Water Closets"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB63.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra que la barra de agarre de la pared lateral tiene un mínimo de 42 pulgadas (1065) de largo, ubicada a 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como máximo desde la pared trasera y se extiende 54 pulgadas (1370 mm) como mínimo desde la pared trasera"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows the side wall grab bar to be 42 inches (1065) long minimum, located 12 inches (305 mm) maximum from the rear wall and extending 54 inches (1370 mm) minimum from the rear wall.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-604_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.5.2 Rear Wall[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The rear wall grab bar shall be 36 inches (915 mm) long minimum and extend from the centerline of the water closet 12 inches (305 mm) minimum on one side and 24 inches (610 mm) minimum on the other side.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-604_5_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  The rear grab bar shall be permitted to be 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum, centered on the water closet, where wall space does not permit a length of 36 inches (915 mm) minimum due to the location of a recessed fixture adjacent to the water closet.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-604_5_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where an administrative authority requires flush controls for flush valves to be located in a position that conflicts with the location of the rear grab bar, then the rear grab bar shall be permitted to be split or shifted to the open side of the toilet area.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.5.2 Rear Wall Grab Bar at Water Closets"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB64.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra la barra de agarre trasera de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de largo como mínimo, colocada de modo que el mínimo de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) se extiende hacia el lado de transferencia abierto y el mínimo de 12 pulgadas (305 mm) se extiende hacia la pared lateral."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows the rear grab bar 36 inches (915 mm) long minimum, positioned so that 24 inches (610 mm) minimum extends toward the open transfer side and 12 inches (305 mm) minimum extends toward the side wall.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-604_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.6 Flush Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Flush controls shall be hand operated or automatic.  Hand operated flush controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Flush controls shall be located on the open side of the water closet except in ambulatory accessible compartments complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_2" class="navSectionLink">604.8.2</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 604.6 Flush Controls.  If plumbing valves are located directly behind the toilet seat, flush valves and related plumbing can cause injury or imbalance when a person leans back against them.  To prevent causing injury or imbalance, the plumbing can be located behind walls or to the side of the toilet; or if approved by the local authority having jurisdiction, provide a toilet seat lid.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-604_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.7 Dispensers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet paper dispensers shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be 7 inches (180 mm) minimum and 9 inches (230 mm) maximum in front of the water closet measured to the centerline of the dispenser.  The outlet of the dispenser shall be 15 inches (380 mm) minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the finish floor and shall not be located behind grab bars.  Dispensers shall not be of a type that controls delivery or that does not allow continuous paper flow.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 604.7 Dispensers.  If toilet paper dispensers are installed above the side wall grab bar, the outlet of the toilet paper dispenser must be 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the finish floor and the top of the gripping surface of the grab bar must be 33 inches (840 mm) minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) maximum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.7 Dispenser Outlet Location"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB65.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra que la línea central del dispensador de papel higiénico es de 7 a 9 pulgadas (180 a 230 mm) frente al armario de agua.  La salida del dispensador es de 15 pulgadas (380 mm) como mínimo y 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) como máximo sobre el piso."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows the centerline of the toilet paper dispenser to be 7 to 9 inches (180 to 230 mm) in front of the water closet.  The outlet of the dispenser is 15 inches (380 mm) minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the floor. 

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-604_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8 Toilet Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair accessible toilet compartments shall meet the requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_1" class="navSectionLink">604.8.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_3" class="navSectionLink">604.8.3</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Compartments containing more than one plumbing fixture shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ambulatory accessible compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_2" class="navSectionLink">604.8.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_3" class="navSectionLink">604.8.3</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_8_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.1 Wheelchair Accessible Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair accessible compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_1" class="navSectionLink">604.8.1</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-604_8_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.1.1 Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair accessible compartments shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum measured perpendicular to the side wall, and 56 inches (1420 mm) deep minimum for wall hung water closets and 59 inches (1500 mm) deep minimum for floor mounted water closets measured perpendicular to the rear wall. Wheelchair accessible compartments for children’s use shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum measured perpendicular to the side wall, and 59 inches (1500 mm) deep minimum for wall hung and floor mounted water closets measured perpendicular to the rear wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 604.8.1.1 Size.  The minimum space required in toilet compartments is provided so that a person using a wheelchair can maneuver into position at the water closet.  This space cannot be obstructed by baby changing tables or other fixtures or conveniences, except as specified at[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_3_2" class="navSectionLink">604.3.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-](Overlap).  If toilet compartments are to be used to house fixtures other than those associated with the water closet, they must be designed to exceed the minimum space requirements.  Convenience fixtures such as baby changing tables must also be accessible to people with disabilities as well as to other users.  Toilet compartments that are designed to meet, and not exceed, the minimum space requirements may not provide adequate space for maneuvering into position at a baby changing table.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.8.1.1 Size of Wheelchair Accessible Toilet Compartment"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB66.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es una vista en planta de un armario de agua colgado de la pared para adultos.  Se muestra que el compartimento tiene un mínimo de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de ancho y un mínimo de 56 pulgadas (1420 mm) de profundidad.  La figura (b) es una vista en planta de un piso para adultos montado y un armario de agua para niños.  Se muestra que el compartimento tiene un mínimo de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de ancho y un mínimo de 59 pulgadas (1500 mm) de profundidad."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is a plan view of an adult wall hung water closet.  The compartment is shown to be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and 56 inches (1420 mm) deep minimum.  Figure (b) is a plan view of an adult floor mounted and a children’s water closet.  The compartment is shown to be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and 59 inches (1500 mm) deep minimum.  

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-604_8_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.1.2 Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet compartment doors, including door hardware, shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]except that if the approach is to the latch side of the compartment door, clearance between the door side of the compartment and any obstruction shall be 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum.  Doors shall be located in the front partition or in the side wall or partition farthest from the water closet. Where located in the front partition, the door opening shall be 4 inches (100 mm) maximum from the side wall or partition farthest from the water closet.  Where located in the side wall or partition, the door opening shall be 4 inches (100 mm) maximum from the front partition.  The door shall be self-closing.  A door pull complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_7" class="navSectionLink">404.2.7</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be placed on both sides of the door near the latch. Toilet compartment doors shall not swing into the minimum required compartment area.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.8.1.2 Wheelchair Accessible Toilet Compartment Doors"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB67.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La puerta del compartimento tiene bisagras de 4 pulgadas (100 mm) como máximo desde la pared lateral o partición más alejada del armario de agua para que la puerta se abra al espacio de transferencia abierto.  El espacio mínimo entre el lado de la puerta del puesto y cualquier obstrucción es de 42 pulgadas (1065 mm)"[-END TRANSLATE-]

The compartment door is hinged 4 inches (100 mm) maximum from the side wall or partition farthest from the water closet so that the door opens on to the open transfer space.  The minimum clearance between the door side of the stall and any obstruction is 42 inches (1065 mm).

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-604_8_1_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.1.3 Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Compartments shall be arranged for left-hand or right-hand approach to the water closet.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-604_8_1_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.1.4 Toe Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The front partition and at least one side partition shall provide a toe clearance of 9 inches (230 mm) minimum above the finish floor and 6 inches (150 mm) deep minimum beyond the compartment-side face of the partition, exclusive of partition support members.  Compartments for children’s use shall provide a toe clearance of 12 inches (305 mm) minimum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Toe clearance at the front partition is not required in a compartment greater than 62 inches (1575 mm) deep with a wall-hung water closet or 65 inches (1650 mm) deep with a floor-mounted water closet.  Toe clearance at the side partition is not required in a compartment greater than 66 inches (1675 mm) wide.  Toe clearance at the front partition is not required in a compartment for children’s use that is greater than 65 inches (1650 mm) deep.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.8.1.4 Wheelchair Accessible Toilet Compartment Toe Clearance"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB68.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación que muestra la holgura de los dedos de los pies debajo de una partición del compartimiento del inodoro.  El espacio libre de los dedos de los pies es de 9 pulgadas (230 mm) de alto mínimo y 6 pulgadas (150 mm) de profundidad mínimo más allá de la cara del lado del compartimento de la partición.  La figura (b) es un dibujo de elevación para un compartimento de inodoro para niños. La holgura de los dedos de los pies es de 12 pulgadas (305 mm) de alto mínimo y 6 pulgadas (150 mm) de profundidad mínima más allá de la cara del lado del compartimento de la partición.  La Figura (c) es una vista de plano que muestra la holgura de los dedos de los pies debajo de la partición frontal y una partición lateral, 6 pulgadas (150 mm) de profundidad como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing showing toe clearance under a toilet compartment partition.  Toe clearance is 9 inches (230 mm) high minimum and 6 inches (150 mm) deep minimum beyond the compartment-side face of the partition.  Figure (b) is an elevation drawing for a children’s toilet compartment.  Toe clearance is 12 inches (305 mm) high minimum and 6 inches (150 mm) deep minimum beyond the compartment-side face of the partition.  Figure (c) is a plan view showing toe clearance under the front partition and one side partition, 6 inches (150 mm) deep minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-604_8_1_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.1.5 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A side-wall grab bar complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_5_1" class="navSectionLink">604.5.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided and shall be located on the wall closest to the water closet.  In addition, a rear-wall grab bar complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_5_2" class="navSectionLink">604.5.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_8_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.2 Ambulatory Accessible Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ambulatory accessible compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_2" class="navSectionLink">604.8.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-604_8_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.2.1 Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ambulatory accessible compartments shall have a depth of 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum and a width of 35 inches (890 mm) minimum and 37 inches (940 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-604_8_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.2.2 Doors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet compartment doors, including door hardware, shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404" class="navSectionLink">404</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]except that if the approach is to the latch side of the compartment door, clearance between the door side of the compartment and any obstruction shall be 42 inches (1065 mm) minimum.  The door shall be self-closing.  A door pull complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-404_2_7" class="navSectionLink">404.2.7</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be placed on both sides of the door near the latch.  Toilet compartment doors shall not swing into the minimum required compartment area.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-604_8_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.2.3 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A side-wall grab bar complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_5_1" class="navSectionLink">604.5.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on both sides of the compartment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 604.8.2 Ambulatory Accessible Toilet Compartment"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB69.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El compartimento tiene 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de profundidad mínima y 35 a 37 pulgadas (890 a 940 mm) de ancho, con barras de agarre en ambos lados.   El espacio mínimo entre el lado de la puerta del puesto y cualquier obstrucción es de 42 pulgadas (1065 mm)"[-END TRANSLATE-]

The compartment is 60 inches (1525 mm) deep minimum and 35 to 37 inches (890 to 940 mm) wide, with grab bars on both sides.   The minimum clearance between the door side of the stall and any obstruction is 42 inches (1065 mm).

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-604_8_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.8.3 Coat Hooks and Shelves[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Coat hooks shall be located within one of the reach ranges specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Shelves shall be located 40 inches (1015 mm) minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-604_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9 Water Closets and Toilet Compartments for Children’s Use[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Water closets and toilet compartments for children’s use shall comply with 604.9.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 604.9 Water Closets and Toilet Compartments for Children’s Use.  The requirements in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_9" class="navSectionLink">604.9</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]are to be followed where the exception for children’s water closets in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_1" class="navSectionLink">604.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is used.  The following table provides additional guidance in applying the specifications for water closets for children according to the age group served and reflects the differences in the size, stature, and reach ranges of children ages 3 through 12.  The specifications chosen should correspond to the age of the primary user group.  The specifications of one age group should be applied consistently in the installation of a water closet and related elements.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory Specifications for Water Closets Serving Children Ages 3 through 12[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr>
<td> </td>
<th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ages 3 and 4[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ages 5 through 8[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ages 9 through 12[-END TRANSLATE-]</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Water Closet Centerline[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>12 inches (305 mm)</td>
<td>12 to 15 inches (305 to 380 mm)</td>
<td>15 to 18 inches (380 to 455 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet Seat Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>11 to 12 inches (280 to 305 mm)</td>
<td>12 to 15 inches (305 to 380 mm)</td>
<td>15 to 17 inches (380 to 430 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab Bar Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>18 to 20 inches (455 to 510 mm)</td>
<td>20 to 25 inches (510 to 635 mm)</td>
<td>25 to 27 inches (635 to 685 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Dispenser Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>14 inches (355 mm)</td>
<td>14 to 17 inches (355 to 430 mm)</td>
<td>17 to 19 inches (430 to 485 mm)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h4 id="ada-604_9_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9.1 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The water closet shall be located with a wall or partition to the rear and to one side.  The centerline of the water closet shall be 12 inches (305 mm) minimum and 18 inches (455 mm) maximum from the side wall or partition, except that the water closet shall be 17 inches (430 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum from the side wall or partition in the ambulatory accessible toilet compartment specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_2" class="navSectionLink">604.8.2</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Compartments shall be arranged for left-hand or right-hand approach to the water closet.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_9_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9.2 Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearance around a water closet shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_3" class="navSectionLink">604.3</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_9_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9.3 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The height of water closets shall be 11 inches (280 mm) minimum and 17 inches (430 mm) maximum measured to the top of the seat.  Seats shall not be sprung to return to a lifted position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_9_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9.4 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars for water closets shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_5" class="navSectionLink">604.5</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_9_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9.5 Flush Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Flush controls shall be hand operated or automatic.  Hand operated flush controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_2" class="navSectionLink">309.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be installed 36 inches (915 mm) maximum above the finish floor.  Flush controls shall be located on the open side of the water closet except in ambulatory accessible compartments complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8_2" class="navSectionLink">604.8.2</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_9_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9.6 Dispensers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet paper dispensers shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be 7 inches (180 mm) minimum and 9 inches (230 mm) maximum in front of the water closet measured to the centerline of the dispenser.  The outlet of the dispenser shall be 14 inches (355 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum above the finish floor.  There shall be a clearance of 1½ inches (38 mm) minimum below the grab bar.  Dispensers shall not be of a type that controls delivery or that does not allow continuous paper flow.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-604_9_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]604.9.7 Toilet Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_8" class="navSectionLink">604.8</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-605">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]605 Urinals[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-605_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]605.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Urinals shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-605" class="navSectionLink">605</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 605.1 General.  Stall-type urinals provide greater accessibility for a broader range of persons, including people of short stature.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-605_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]605.2 Height and Depth[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Urinals shall be the stall-type or the wall-hung type with the rim 17 inches (430 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.  Urinals shall be 13½ inches (345 mm) deep minimum measured from the outer face of the urinal rim to the back of the fixture.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 605.2 Height and Depth of Urinals"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB70.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación de un tipo de pared colgado que tiene el borde del urinario de 17 pulgadas (430 mm) como máximo sobre el piso con una profundidad mínima de 131/2 pulgadas (350 mm) medida desde la cara exterior del borde hasta la parte posterior del accesorio.  La figura (b) es un dibujo de elevación de un tipo de puesto (piso) que tiene una profundidad mínima de 131/2 pulgadas (350 mm) medida desde la cara exterior del borde hasta la parte posterior del accesorio."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing of a wall hung type having the urinal rim 17 inches (430 mm) maximum above the floor with a minimum depth of 13½ inches (350 mm) measured from the outer face of the rim to the back of the fixture.  Figure (b) is an elevation drawing of a stall (floor) type having a minimum depth of 13½ inches (350 mm) measured from the outer face of the rim to the back of the fixture.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-605_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]605.3 Clear Floor Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for forward approach shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-605_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]605.4 Flush Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Flush controls shall be hand operated or automatic.  Hand operated flush controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-606">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]606 Lavatories and Sinks[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-606_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]606.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Lavatories and sinks shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-606" class="navSectionLink">606</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 606.1 General.  If soap and towel dispensers are provided, they must be located within the reach ranges specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Locate soap and towel dispensers so that they are conveniently usable by a person at the accessible lavatory.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-606_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]606.2 Clear Floor Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for a forward approach, and knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  A parallel approach complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to a kitchen sink in a space where a cook top or conventional range is not provided and to wet bars.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  A lavatory in a toilet room or bathing facility for a single occupant accessed only through a private office and not for common use or public use shall not be required to provide knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  In residential dwelling units, cabinetry shall be permitted under lavatories and kitchen sinks provided that all of the following conditions are met:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<ol class="standards" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]the cabinetry can be removed without removal or replacement of the fixture;[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]the finish floor extends under the cabinetry; and[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]the walls behind and surrounding the cabinetry are finished.[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
</ol>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]4.  A knee clearance of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum above the finish floor or ground shall be permitted at lavatories and sinks used primarily by children 6 through 12 years where the rim or counter surface is 31 inches (785 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]5.  A parallel approach complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to lavatories and sinks used primarily by children 5 years and younger.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]6.  The dip of the overflow shall not be considered in determining knee and toe clearances.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]7.  No more than one bowl of a multi-bowl sink shall be required to provide knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-606_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]606.3 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Lavatories and sinks shall be installed with the front of the higher of the rim or counter surface 34 inches (865 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  A lavatory in a toilet or bathing facility for a single occupant accessed only through a private office and not for common use or public use shall not be required to comply with 606.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-606_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In residential dwelling unit kitchens, sinks that are adjustable to variable heights, 29 inches (735 mm) minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) maximum, shall be permitted where rough-in plumbing permits connections of supply and drain pipes for sinks mounted at the height of 29 inches (735 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-606_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]606.4 Faucets[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Controls for faucets shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Hand-operated metering faucets shall remain open for 10 seconds minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-606_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]606.5 Exposed Pipes and Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Water supply and drain pipes under lavatories and sinks shall be insulated or otherwise configured to protect against contact.  There shall be no sharp or abrasive surfaces under lavatories and sinks.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-607">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607 Bathtubs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-607_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bathtubs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607" class="navSectionLink">607</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-607_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.2 Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearance in front of bathtubs shall extend the length of the bathtub and shall be 30 inches (760 mm) wide minimum.  A lavatory complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-606" class="navSectionLink">606</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted at the control end of the clearance.  Where a permanent seat is provided at the head end of the bathtub, the clearance shall extend 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beyond the wall at the head end of the bathtub.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 607.2 Clearance for Bathtubs"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB71.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra una bañera con un asiento extraíble en la bañera.  La bañera tiene un espacio libre en la parte delantera de 30 pulgadas (760 mm) de ancho mínimo que se extiende a lo largo de la bañera.  La figura (b) muestra una bañera con un asiento permanente en el extremo de la cabeza (el extremo opuesto a los controles).  La bañera tiene un espacio libre en la parte delantera de 30 pulgadas (760 mm) de ancho mínimo que extiende la longitud de la bañera más 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como mínimo más allá del asiento.  Ambas figuras muestran que un baño se puede ubicar en el extremo del pie de la holgura de la bañera"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a bathtub with a removable in-tub seat.  The bathtub has clearance in front 30 inches (760 mm) wide minimum that extends the length of the tub.  Figure (b) shows a bathtub with a permanent seat at the head end (the end opposite the controls).  The tub has clearance in front 30 inches (760 mm) wide minimum that extends the length of the tub plus 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beyond the seat.  Both figures show that a lavatory can be located at the foot end of the tub clearance.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-607_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.3 Seat[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A permanent seat at the head end of the bathtub or a removable in-tub seat shall be provided.  Seats shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-607_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars for bathtubs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607_4_1" class="navSectionLink">607.4.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607_4_2" class="navSectionLink">607.4.2</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-607_4x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1. Grab bars shall not be required to be installed in a bathtub located in a bathing facility for a single occupant accessed only through a private office and not for common use or public use provided that reinforcement has been installed in walls and located so as to permit the installation of grab bars complying with 607.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-607_4x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In residential dwelling units, grab bars shall not be required to be installed in bathtubs located in bathing facilities provided that reinforcement has been installed in walls and located so as to permit the installation of grab bars complying with 607.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-607_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4.1 Bathtubs With Permanent Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]For bathtubs with permanent seats, grab bars shall be provided in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607_4_1" class="navSectionLink">607.4.1</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-607_4_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4.1.1 Back Wall[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Two grab bars shall be installed on the back wall, one located in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609_4" class="navSectionLink">609.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and the other located 8 inches (205 mm) minimum and 10 inches (255 mm) maximum above the rim of the bathtub.  Each grab bar shall be installed 15 inches (380 mm) maximum from the head end wall and 12 inches (305 mm) maximum from the control end wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-607_4_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4.1.2 Control End Wall[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A grab bar 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum shall be installed on the control end wall at the front edge of the bathtub.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 607.4.1 Grab Bars for Bathtubs with Permanent Seats"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB72.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra un dibujo de elevación de una bañera con un asiento permanente y dos barras de agarre paralelas en la pared posterior.  La barra de agarre superior está montada de 33 a 36 pulgadas (840 a 915 mm) sobre el piso de acabado.  La barra de agarre inferior está montada de 8 a 10 pulgadas (205 a 255 mm) por encima del borde de la bañera.  La figura (b) es una vista de plano.  Una barra de agarre en la pared del extremo del pie mide 24 pulgadas (610 mm) de largo como mínimo y se instala en el borde frontal de la bañera.  Las barras de agarre traseras están montadas a 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como máximo desde la pared del extremo del pie y 15 pulgadas (380 mm) como máximo desde la pared del extremo de la cabeza"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows an elevation drawing of a tub with a permanent seat and two parallel grab bars on the back wall.  The upper grab bar is mounted 33 to 36 inches (840 to 915 mm) above the finish floor.  The lower grab bar is mounted 8 to 10 inches (205 to 255 mm) above the tub rim.  Figure (b) is a plan view.  A grab bar on the foot end wall is 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum and is installed at the front edge of the tub.  The rear grab bars are mounted 12 inches (305 mm) maximum from the foot end wall and 15 inches (380 mm) maximum from the head end wall."[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-607_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4.2 Bathtubs Without Permanent Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]For bathtubs without permanent seats, grab bars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607_4_2" class="navSectionLink">607.4.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-607_4_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4.2.1 Back Wall[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Two grab bars shall be installed on the back wall, one located in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609_4" class="navSectionLink">609.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and other located 8 inches (205 mm) minimum and 10 inches (255 mm) maximum above the rim of the bathtub.  Each grab bar shall be 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum and shall be installed 24 inches (610 mm) maximum from the head end wall and 12 inches (305 mm) maximum from the control end wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-607_4_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4.2.2 Control End Wall[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A grab bar 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum shall be installed on the control end wall at the front edge of the bathtub.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-607_4_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.4.2.3 Head End Wall[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A grab bar 12 inches (305 mm) long minimum shall be installed on the head end wall at the front edge of the bathtub.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 607.4.2 Grab Bars for Bathtubs with Removable In-Tub Seats"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB73.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación que muestra barras de agarre traseras, una montada de 33 a 36 pulgadas (840 a 915 mm) sobre el piso de acabado, y otra montada de 8 a 10 pulgadas (205 a 255 mm) por encima del borde de la bañera.  La Figura (b) es una vista de planta que muestra una barra de agarre en la pared del extremo del pie (control) de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) de largo como mínimo instalada en el borde frontal de la bañera.  Las barras de agarre traseras miden 24 pulgadas (610 mm) de largo como mínimo y están montadas a 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como máximo desde la pared del extremo del pie (control) y 24 pulgadas (610 mm) como máximo desde la pared del extremo de la cabeza.  Una barra de agarre de 12 pulgadas (305 mm) de largo como mínimo está instalada en la pared del extremo de la cabeza en el borde frontal de la bañera."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing showing rear grab bars, one mounted 33 to 36 inches (840 to 915 mm) above the finish floor, and one mounted 8 to 10 inches (205 to 255 mm) above the tub rim.  Figure (b) is a plan view showing a grab bar on the foot (control) end wall 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum installed at the front edge of the tub.  Rear grab bars are 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum and are mounted 12 inches (305 mm) maximum from the foot (control) end wall and 24 inches (610 mm) maximum from the head end wall.  A grab bar 12 inches (305 mm) long minimum is installed on the head end wall at the front edge of the tub.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-607_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.5 Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Controls, other than drain stoppers, shall be located on an end wall.  Controls shall be between the bathtub rim and grab bar, and between the open side of the bathtub and the centerline of the width of the bathtub.  Controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 607.5 Bathtub Control Location"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB74.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra la ubicación de los controles por encima del borde de la bañera y por debajo de la barra de agarre y entre el borde frontal de la bañera y la línea central de la bañera"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows the location of controls above the tub rim and below the grab bar and between the front edge of the tub and the tub centerline.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-607_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.6 Shower Spray Unit and Water[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A shower spray unit with a hose 59 inches (1500 mm) long minimum that can be used both as a fixed-position shower head and as a hand-held shower shall be provided.  The shower spray unit shall have an on/off control with a non-positive shut-off.  If an adjustable-height shower head on a vertical bar is used, the bar shall be installed so as not to obstruct the use of grab bars.  Bathtub shower spray units shall deliver water that is 120°F (49°C) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 607.6 Shower Spray Unit and Water.  Ensure that hand-held shower spray units are capable of delivering water pressure substantially equivalent to fixed shower heads.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-607_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]607.7 Bathtub Enclosures[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Enclosures for bathtubs shall not obstruct controls, faucets, shower and spray units or obstruct transfer from wheelchairs onto bathtub seats or into bathtubs. Enclosures on bathtubs shall not have tracks installed on the rim of the open face of the bathtub.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-608">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608 Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-608_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Shower compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-608" class="navSectionLink">608</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 608.1 General.  Shower stalls that are 60 inches (1525 mm) wide and have no curb may increase the usability of a bathroom because the shower area provides additional maneuvering space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-608_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.2 Size and Clearances for Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Shower compartments shall have sizes and clearances complying with 608.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-608_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.2.1 Transfer Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer type shower compartments shall be 36 inches (915 mm) by 36 inches (915 mm) clear inside dimensions measured at the center points of opposing sides and shall have a 36 inch (915 mm) wide minimum entry on the face of the shower compartment.  Clearance of 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum by 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum measured from the control wall shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.2.1 Transfer Type Shower Compartment Size and Clearance"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB75.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un puesto de transferencia se muestra en la vista del plano para ser de 36 por 36 pulgadas (915 por 915 mm).  El espacio libre en el piso delantero es de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho mínimo y 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) de largo mínimo medido desde la pared de control."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A transfer stall is shown in plan view to be 36 by 36 inches (915 by 915 mm).  Clear floor space in front is 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum measured from the control wall.  

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-608_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.2.2 Standard Roll-In Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Standard roll-in type shower compartments shall be 30 inches (760 mm) wide minimum by 60 inches (1525 mm) deep minimum clear inside dimensions measured at center points of opposing sides and shall have a 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum entry on the face of the shower compartment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-608_2_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.2.2.1 Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A 30 inch (760 mm) wide minimum by 60 inch (1525 mm) long minimum clearance shall be provided adjacent to the open face of the shower compartment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  A lavatory complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-606" class="navSectionLink">606</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted on one 30 inch (760 mm) wide minimum side of the clearance provided that it is not on the side of the clearance adjacent to the controls or, where provided, not on the side of the clearance adjacent to the shower seat.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.2.2 Standard Roll-In Type Shower Compartment Size and Clearance"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB76.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de planta muestra que el compartimiento de la ducha es de 30 pulgadas (760 mm) como mínimo por 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como mínimo con una entrada de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de ancho en la cara del compartimento.  Se proporciona un espacio de piso libre de 30 pulgadas (760 mm) adyacente a la cara abierta del compartimento.  Se muestra un asiento en un extremo.  Se permite un baño dentro del espacio libre del piso en el extremo opuesto al asiento."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows the shower compartment is 30 inches (760 mm) minimum by 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum with a 60 inch (1525 mm) wide entry on the face of the compartment.  A clear floor space 30 inches (760 mm) side is provided adjacent to the open face of the compartment.  A seat is shown on one end.  A lavatory is permitted within the clear floor space on the end opposite the seat.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-608_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.2.3 Alternate Roll-In Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Alternate roll-in type shower compartments shall be 36 inches (915 mm) wide and 60 inches (1525 mm) deep minimum clear inside dimensions measured at center points of opposing sides.  A 36 inch (915 mm) wide minimum entry shall be provided at one end of the long side of the compartment.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.2.3 Alternate Roll-In Type Shower Compartment Size and Clearance"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB77.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de planta muestra que el compartimiento de la ducha tiene 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho absoluto y 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de profundidad como mínimo.  Se proporciona una entrada mínima de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho en una pared larga.  Se proporciona un asiento adyacente a la entrada en la misma pared."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows the shower compartment is 36 inches (915 mm) wide absolute and 60 inches (1525 mm) deep minimum.  A 36 inch (915 mm) wide minimum entry is provided on one long wall.  A seat is provided adjacent to the entry on the same wall.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-608_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.3 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be provided in accordance with 608.3.  Where multiple grab bars are used, required horizontal grab bars shall be installed at the same height above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-608_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Grab bars shall not be required to be installed in a shower located in a bathing facility for a single occupant accessed only through a private office, and not for common use or public use provided that reinforcement has been installed in walls and located so as to permit the installation of grab bars complying with 608.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-608_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In residential dwelling units, grab bars shall not be required to be installed in showers located in bathing facilities provided that reinforcement has been installed in walls and located so as to permit the installation of grab bars complying with 608.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-608_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.3.1 Transfer Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In transfer type compartments, grab bars shall be provided across the control wall and back wall to a point 18 inches (455 mm) from the control wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.3.1 Grab Bars for Transfer Type Showers"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB78.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La vista de plano muestra una barra de agarre que se extiende a través de la pared de control y la pared posterior hasta un punto a 18 pulgadas (455 mm) de la pared de control"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Plan view shows a grab bar that extends across the control wall and the back wall to a point 18 inches (455 mm) from the control wall.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-608_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.3.2 Standard Roll-In Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a seat is provided in standard roll-in type shower compartments, grab bars shall be provided on the back wall and the side wall opposite the seat.  Grab bars shall not be provided above the seat.  Where a seat is not provided in standard roll-in type shower compartments, grab bars shall be provided on three walls.  Grab bars shall be installed 6 inches (150 mm) maximum from adjacent walls.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.3.2 Grab Bars for Standard Roll-In Type Showers"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB79.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es una vista en planta de una ducha sin asiento.  Las barras de agarre se proporcionan en tres paredes que son de 6 pulgadas (150 mm) como máximo desde la pared adyacente.  La figura (b) es una vista en planta de una ducha con un asiento en una pared lateral.  Las barras de agarre se proporcionan en la pared lateral opuesta y la pared posterior.  La barra de agarre de la pared trasera no se extiende sobre el asiento.  Las barras de agarre son de 6 pulgadas (150 mm) como máximo desde la pared adyacente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is a plan view of a shower without a seat.  Grab bars are provided on three walls that are 6 inches (150 mm) maximum from the adjacent wall.  Figure (b) is a plan view of a shower with a seat on one side wall.  Grab bars are provided on the opposite side wall and the back wall.  The back wall grab bar does not extend over the seat.  The grab bars are 6 inches (150 mm) maximum from the adjacent wall.  

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-608_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.3.3 Alternate Roll-In Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In alternate roll-in type shower compartments, grab bars shall be provided on the back wall and the side wall farthest from the compartment entry.  Grab bars shall not be provided above the seat. Grab bars shall be installed 6 inches (150 mm) maximum from adjacent walls.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.3.3 Grab Bars for Alternate Roll-In Type Showers"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB80.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Esta figura muestra una ducha plegable alternativa con un asiento.  Una barra de agarre se extiende en la pared opuesta al asiento y es de 6 pulgadas (150 mm) como máximo desde las paredes adyacentes.  Otra barra de agarre está montada en la pared lateral adyacente al asiento; Esta barra de agarre no se extiende sobre el asiento y tiene un máximo de 6 pulgadas (150 mm) desde la pared posterior."[-END TRANSLATE-]

This figure shows an alternate roll-in shower with a seat.  A grab bar extends on the wall opposite the seat and is 6 inches (150 mm) maximum from adjacent walls.  Another grab bar is mounted on the side wall adjacent to the seat; this grab bar does not extend over the seat and is 6 inches (150 mm) maximum from the back wall. 

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-608_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.4 Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A folding or non-folding seat shall be provided in transfer type shower compartments.  A folding seat shall be provided in roll-in type showers required in transient lodging guest rooms with mobility features complying with 806.2.  Seats shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In residential dwelling units, seats shall not be required in transfer type shower compartments provided that reinforcement has been installed in walls so as to permit the installation of seats complying with 608.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-608_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.5 Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Controls, faucets, and shower spray units shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-608_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.5.1 Transfer Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In transfer type shower compartments, the controls, faucets, and shower spray unit shall be installed on the side wall opposite the seat 38 inches (965 mm) minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the shower floor and shall be located on the control wall 15 inches (380 mm) maximum from the centerline of the seat toward the shower opening.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.5.1 Transfer Type Shower Compartment Control Location"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB81.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El área para controles, grifos y unidades de pulverización de ducha se encuentra de 38 pulgadas (965 mm) como mínimo a 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) como máximo por encima del piso de la ducha en la pared de control 15 pulgadas (380 mm) como máximo desde la línea central del asiento, hacia la abertura de la ducha."[-END TRANSLATE-]

The area for controls, faucets and shower spray units is located 38 inches (965 mm) minimum to 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the shower floor on the control wall 15 inches (380 mm) maximum from the centerline of the seat, toward the shower opening.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-608_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.5.2 Standard Roll-In Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In standard roll-in type shower compartments, the controls, faucets, and shower spray unit shall be located above the grab bar, but no higher than 48 inches (1220 mm) above the shower floor.  Where a seat is provided, the controls, faucets, and shower spray unit shall be installed on the back wall adjacent to the seat wall and shall be located 27 inches (685 mm) maximum from the seat wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 608.5.2 Standard Roll-In Type Shower Compartments.  In standard roll-in type showers without seats, the shower head and operable parts can be located on any of the three walls of the shower without adversely affecting accessibility.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.5.2 Standard Roll-In Type Shower Compartment Control Location

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB82.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación de un compartimento sin asiento.  El área para controles, grifos y unidades de pulverización de ducha se encuentra en cualquier pared de la ducha por encima de la barra de agarre, pero no más de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) por encima del piso de la ducha.  La figura (b) es un dibujo de elevación de un compartimento con un asiento. El área para controles, grifos y unidades de pulverización de ducha se encuentra en la pared posterior a 27 pulgadas (685 mm) de la pared del asiento y por encima de la barra de agarre, pero no más de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) por encima del piso de la ducha."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing of a compartment without a seat.  The area for controls, faucets and shower spray units is located on any wall of the shower above the grab bar but no higher than 48 inches (1220 mm) above the shower floor.  Figure (b) is an elevation drawing of a compartment with a seat.  The area for controls, faucets and shower spray units is located on the back wall 27 inches (685 mm) from the seat wall and above the grab bar, but no higher than 48 inches (1220 mm) above the shower floor.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-608_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.5.3 Alternate Roll-In Type Shower Compartments[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In alternate roll-in type shower compartments, the controls, faucets, and shower spray unit shall be located above the grab bar, but no higher than 48 inches (1220 mm) above the shower floor.  Where a seat is provided, the controls, faucets, and shower spray unit shall be located on the side wall adjacent to the seat 27 inches (685 mm) maximum from the side wall behind the seat or shall be located on the back wall opposite the seat 15 inches (380 mm) maximum, left or right, of the centerline of the seat.  Where a seat is not provided, the controls, faucets, and shower spray unit shall be installed on the side wall farthest from the compartment entry.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 608.5.3 Alternate Roll-In Type Shower Compartment Control Location

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB83.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación de una pared lateral adyacente a un asiento.  El área para controles, grifos y unidades de pulverización de ducha se encuentra en la pared lateral adyacente al asiento, sobre la barra de agarre, pero no más de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) por encima del piso de la ducha, y se extiende 27 pulgadas (685 mm) como máximo desde la pared del asiento.  La Figura (b) muestra una ubicación alternativa en la pared posterior, por encima de la barra de agarre, pero no más de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) por encima del piso de la ducha, y que se extiende desde la pared lateral hasta 15 pulgadas (380 mm) como máximo desde la línea central del asiento.  Las figuras (c) y (d) son vistas planas de compartimentos sin y con un asiento, respectivamente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing of a side wall adjacent to a seat.  The area for controls, faucets and shower spray units is located on the side wall adjacent to the seat, above the grab bar but no higher than 48 inches (1220 mm) above the shower floor, and extending 27 inches (685 mm) maximum from the seat wall.  Figure (b) shows an alternate location on the back wall, above the grab bar but no higher than 48 inches (1220 mm) above the shower floor, and extending from the side wall to 15 inches (380 mm) maximum from the center line of the seat.  Figures (c) and (d) are plan views of compartments without and with a seat, respectively.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-608_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.6 Shower Spray Unit and Water[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A shower spray unit with a hose 59 inches (1500 mm) long minimum that can be used both as a fixed-position shower head and as a hand-held shower shall be provided.  The shower spray unit shall have an on/off control with a non-positive shut-off.  If an adjustable-height shower head on a vertical bar is used, the bar shall be installed so as not to obstruct the use of grab bars.  Shower spray units shall deliver water that is 120°F (49°C) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  A fixed shower head located at 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the shower finish floor shall be permitted instead of a hand-held spray unit in facilities that are not medical care facilities, long-term care facilities, transient lodging guest rooms, or residential dwelling units.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 608.6 Shower Spray Unit and Water.  Ensure that hand-held shower spray units are capable of delivering water pressure substantially equivalent to fixed shower heads.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-608_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.7 Thresholds[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Thresholds in roll-in type shower compartments shall be ½ inch (13 mm) high maximum in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303" class="navSectionLink">303</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In transfer type shower compartments, thresholds ½ inch (13 mm) high maximum shall be beveled, rounded, or vertical.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  A threshold 2 inches (51 mm) high maximum shall be permitted in transfer type shower compartments in existing facilities where provision of a ½ inch (13 mm) high threshold would disturb the structural reinforcement of the floor slab.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-608_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]608.8 Shower Enclosures[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Enclosures for shower compartments shall not obstruct controls, faucets, and shower spray units or obstruct transfer from wheelchairs onto shower seats.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-609">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-609_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars in toilet facilities and bathing facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-609_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.2 Cross Section[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall have a cross section complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609_2_1" class="navSectionLink">609.2.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609_2_2" class="navSectionLink">609.2.2</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-609_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.2.1 Circular Cross Section[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars with circular cross sections shall have an outside diameter of 1¼ inches (32 mm) minimum and 2 inches (51 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-609_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.2.2 Non-Circular Cross Section[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars with non-circular cross sections shall have a cross-section dimension of 2 inches (51 mm) maximum and a perimeter dimension of 4 inches (100 mm) minimum and 4.8 inches (120 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 609.2.2 Grab Bar Non-Circular Cross Section"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB84.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra una barandilla con una sección transversal aproximadamente cuadrada y la figura (c) muestra una sección transversal elíptica.  La dimensión de sección transversal más grande es de 2 pulgadas (51 mm) como máximo.  La dimensión perimetral debe ser de 4 a 4,8 pulgadas (100 a 120 mm)."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a handrail with an approximately square cross section and figure (c) shows an elliptical cross section.  The largest cross section dimension is 2 inches (51 mm) maximum.  The perimeter dimension must be 4 to 4.8 inches (100 to 120 mm).

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-609_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.3 Spacing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The space between the wall and the grab bar shall be 1½ inches (38 mm).  The space between the grab bar and projecting objects below and at the ends shall be 1½ inches (38 mm) minimum.  The space between the grab bar and projecting objects above shall be 12 inches (305 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  The space between the grab bars and shower controls, shower fittings, and other grab bars above shall be permitted to be 1½ inches (38 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 609.3 Spacing of Grab Bars"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB85.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra una barra de agarre con un objeto saliente montado por encima y por debajo de él.  Los objetos salientes deben estar espaciados 11/2 pulgadas (38 mm) mínimo por debajo y 12 pulgadas (305 mm) mínimo por encima de la barra de agarre.  Los objetos empotrados se pueden espaciar inmediatamente por encima y por debajo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A grab bar is shown with a projecting object mounted above and below it.  Projecting objects must spaced 1½ inch (38 mm) minimum below and 12 inches (305 mm) minimum above the grab bar.  Recessed objects can be spaced immediately above and below.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-609_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.4 Position of Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall be installed in a horizontal position, 33 inches (840 mm) minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) maximum above the finish floor measured to the top of the gripping surface, except that at water closets for children’s use complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-604_9" class="navSectionLink">604.9</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]grab bars shall be installed in a horizontal position 18 inches (455 mm) minimum and 27 inches (685 mm) maximum above the finish floor measured to the top of the gripping surface.  The height of the lower grab bar on the back wall of a bathtub shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607_4_1_1" class="navSectionLink">607.4.1.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-607_4_2_1" class="navSectionLink">607.4.2.1</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-609_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.5 Surface Hazards[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars and any wall or other surfaces adjacent to grab bars shall be free of sharp or abrasive elements and shall have rounded edges.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-609_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.6 Fittings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall not rotate within their fittings.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-609_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.7 Installation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Grab bars shall be installed in any manner that provides a gripping surface at the specified locations and that does not obstruct the required clear floor space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-609_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]609.8 Structural Strength[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Allowable stresses shall not be exceeded for materials used when a vertical or horizontal force of 250 pounds (1112 N) is applied at any point on the grab bar, fastener, mounting device, or supporting structure.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-610">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]610 Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-610_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]610.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Seats in bathtubs and shower compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-610_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]610.2 Bathtub Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The top of bathtub seats shall be 17 inches (430 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum above the bathroom finish floor.  The depth of a removable in-tub seat shall be 15 inches (380 mm) minimum and 16 inches (405 mm) maximum.  The seat shall be capable of secure placement.  Permanent seats at the head end of the bathtub shall be 15 inches (380 mm) deep minimum and shall extend from the back wall to or beyond the outer edge of the bathtub.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 610.2 Bathtub Seats"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB86.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) muestra un asiento extraíble en la bañera en vista de elevación y plano que tiene de 15 a 16 pulgadas (380 a 405 mm) de profundidad y de 17 a 19 pulgadas (430 a 485 mm) sobre el piso medido hasta la parte superior del asiento.  La Figura (b) muestra el asiento permanente de la bañera en elevación y vistas de planta que tiene una profundidad mínima de 15 pulgadas (380 mm) y de 17 a 19 pulgadas (430 a 485 mm) sobre el piso medido hasta la parte superior del asiento."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a removable in-tub seat in elevation and plan views that is 15 to 16 inches (380 to 405 mm) deep and 17 to 19 inches (430 to 485 mm) above the floor measured to the top of the seat.  Figure (b) shows permanent tub seat in elevation and plan views that is 15 inches (380 mm) minimum deep and 17 to 19 inches (430 to 485 mm) above the floor measured to the top of the seat.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-610_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]610.3 Shower Compartment Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a seat is provided in a standard roll-in shower compartment, it shall be a folding type, shall be installed on the side wall adjacent to the controls, and shall extend from the back wall to a point within 3 inches (75 mm) of the compartment entry.  Where a seat is provided in an alternate roll-in type shower compartment, it shall be a folding type, shall be installed on the front wall opposite the back wall, and shall extend from the adjacent side wall to a point within 3 inches (75 mm) of the compartment entry.  In transfer-type showers, the seat shall extend from the back wall to a point within 3 inches (75 mm) of the compartment entry.  The top of the seat shall be 17 inches (430 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum above the bathroom finish floor.  Seats shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610_3_1" class="navSectionLink">610.3.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610_3_2" class="navSectionLink">610.3.2</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 610.3 Extent of Seat"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB87.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es una vista en planta de un asiento rectangular y la figura (b) es una vista en planta de un asiento en forma de L.  El borde frontal de cada uno es de 3 pulgadas (75 mm) como máximo desde la entrada del compartimento."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is a plan view of a rectangular seat and figure (b) is a plan view of an L-shaped seat.  The front edge of each is 3 inches (75 mm) maximum from the compartment entry.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-610_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]610.3.1 Rectangular Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The rear edge of a rectangular seat shall be 2½ inches (64 mm) maximum and the front edge 15 inches (380 mm) minimum and 16 inches (405 mm) maximum from the seat wall.  The side edge of the seat shall be 1½ inches (38 mm) maximum from the adjacent wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 610.3.1 Rectangular Shower Seat"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB88.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El borde trasero es de 21/2 pulgadas (64 mm) máximo y el borde delantero de 15 a 16 pulgadas (380 a 405 mm) de la pared del asiento.  El borde lateral es de 11/2 pulgadas (38 mm) como máximo desde la pared posterior."[-END TRANSLATE-]

The rear edge is 2½ inches (64 mm) maximum and the front edge 15 to 16 inches (380 to 405 mm) from the seat wall.  The side edge is 1½ inches (38 mm) maximum from the back wall.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-610_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]610.3.2 L-Shaped Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The rear edge of an L-shaped seat shall be 2½ inches (64 mm) maximum and the front edge 15 inches (380 mm) minimum and 16 inches (405 mm) maximum from the seat wall.  The rear edge of the “L” portion of the seat shall be 1½ inches (38 mm) maximum from the wall and the front edge shall be 14 inches (355 mm) minimum and 15 inches (380 mm) maximum from the wall.  The end of the “L” shall be 22 inches (560 mm) minimum and 23 inches maximum (585 mm) from the main seat wall.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 610.3.2 L-Shaped Shower Seat"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB89.jpg"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Las figuras (a) muestran que la "L" está orientada con la parte más estrecha hacia la abertura del compartimento y la base hacia la parte posterior.  El borde frontal de la parte estrecha de la L está a 15 a 16 pulgadas (380 a 405 mm) de la pared del asiento y el extremo de la base está a 22 a 23 pulgadas (560 a 585 mm) de la pared del asiento. La base de la L está a 14 a 15 pulgadas (355 a 380 mm) de la pared adyacente.  La Figura (b) muestra que el asiento tiene un máximo de 21/2 pulgadas (64 mm) de la pared del asiento y el borde trasero de la parte L es de 11/2 pulgadas (38 mm) como máximo de la pared adyacente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figures (a) shows the “L” is oriented with the narrower portion toward the compartment opening and the base toward the back.  The front edge of the narrow portion of the L is 15 to 16 inches (380 to 405 mm) from the seat wall and the base end is 22 to 23 inches (560 to 585 mm) from the seat wall.  The base of the L is 14 to 15 inches (355 to 380 mm) from the adjacent wall.  Figure (b) shows that the seat is 2½ inches (64 mm) maximum from the seat wall and the rear edge of the L portion is 1½ inches (38 mm) maximum from the adjacent wall.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-610_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]610.4 Structural Strength[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Allowable stresses shall not be exceeded for materials used when a vertical or horizontal force of 250 pounds (1112 N) is applied at any point on the seat, fastener, mounting device, or supporting structure.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-611">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]611 Washing Machines and Clothes Dryers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-611_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]611.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Washing machines and clothes dryers shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-611" class="navSectionLink">611</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-611_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]611.2 Clear Floor Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for parallel approach shall be provided.  The clear floor or ground space shall be centered on the appliance.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-611_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]611.3 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Operable parts, including doors, lint screens, and detergent and bleach compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-611_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]611.4 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Top loading machines shall have the door to the laundry compartment located 36 inches (915 mm) maximum above the finish floor.  Front loading machines shall have the bottom of the opening to the laundry compartment located 15 inches (380 mm) minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) maximum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 611.4 Height of Laundry Compartment Opening"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB90.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra una máquina de carga superior con la puerta del compartimiento de lavandería a 36 pulgadas (915 mm) como máximo sobre el piso.  La Figura (b) muestra una máquina de carga frontal con la parte inferior de la abertura del compartimiento de lavandería de 15 a 36 pulgadas (380 a 915 mm) sobre el piso."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a top loading machine with the door to the laundry compartment 36 inches (915 mm) maximum above the floor.  Figure (b) shows a front loading machine with the bottom of the opening to the laundry compartment 15 to 36 inches (380 to 915 mm) above the floor.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h2 id="ada-612">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]612 Saunas and Steam Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-612_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]612.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Saunas and steam rooms shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-612" class="navSectionLink">612</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-612_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]612.2 Bench[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where seating is provided in saunas and steam rooms, at least one bench shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-903" class="navSectionLink">903</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doors shall not swing into the clear floor space required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-903_2" class="navSectionLink">903.2</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  A readily removable bench shall be permitted to obstruct the turning space required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-612_3" class="navSectionLink">612.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and the clear floor or ground space required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-903_2" class="navSectionLink">903.2</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-612_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]612.3 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided within saunas and steam rooms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
  <h1></h1> <!--empty last heading for kms load function to work-->
  </div>    <!--close #adaCh6-->
  <div id="adaCh7">
  <h1 id="a7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Chapter 7: Communication Elements and Features[-END TRANSLATE-]</h1>
  <h2 id="ada-701">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]701 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-701_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]701.1 Scope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The provisions of Chapter 7 shall apply where required by Chapter 2 or where referenced by a requirement in this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-702">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]702 Fire Alarm Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-702_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]702.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Fire alarm systems shall have permanently installed audible and visible alarms complying with NFPA 72 (1999 or 2002 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1), except that the maximum allowable sound level of audible notification appliances complying with section 4-3.2.1 of NFPA 72 (1999 edition) shall have a sound level no more than 110 dB at the minimum hearing distance from the audible appliance.  In addition, alarms in guest rooms required to provide communication features shall comply with sections 4-3 and 4-4 of NFPA 72 (1999 edition) or sections 7.4 and 7.5 of NFPA 72 (2002 edition).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Fire alarm systems in medical care facilities shall be permitted to be provided in accordance with industry practice.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-703">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703 Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-703_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703" class="navSectionLink">703</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where both visual and tactile characters are required, either one sign with both visual and tactile characters, or two separate signs, one with visual, and one with tactile characters, shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-703_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2 Raised Characters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Raised characters shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be duplicated in braille complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_3" class="navSectionLink">703.3</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Raised characters shall be installed in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_4" class="navSectionLink">703.4</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 703.2 Raised Characters. Signs that are designed to be read by touch should not have sharp or abrasive edges.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.1 Depth[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Raised characters shall be 1/32 inch (0.8 mm) minimum above their background.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.2 Case[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters shall be uppercase.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.3 Style[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters shall be sans serif.  Characters shall not be italic, oblique, script, highly decorative, or of other unusual forms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.4 Character Proportions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters shall be selected from fonts where the width of the uppercase letter “O” is 55 percent minimum and 110 percent maximum of the height of the uppercase letter “I”.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_2_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.5 Character Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Character height measured vertically from the baseline of the character shall be 5/8 inch (16 mm) minimum and 2 inches (51 mm) maximum based on the height of the uppercase letter “I”.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where separate raised and visual characters with the same information are provided, raised character height shall be permitted to be ½ inch (13 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 703.2.5 Height of Raised Characters"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB91.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un detalle ampliado muestra que la altura del carácter medida desde la línea de base del carácter es de cinco octavos a 2 pulgadas (16 a 51 mm) según la letra I mayúscula."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An Enlarged detail shows the character height measured from the baseline of the character is five-eighths to 2 inches (16 to 51 mm) based on the uppercase letter I.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-703_2_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.6 Stroke Thickness[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Stroke thickness of the uppercase letter “I” shall be 15 percent maximum of the height of the character.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_2_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.7 Character Spacing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Character spacing shall be measured between the two closest points of adjacent raised characters within a message, excluding word spaces. Where characters have rectangular cross sections, spacing between individual raised characters shall be 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) minimum and 4 times the raised character stroke width maximum.  Where characters have other cross sections, spacing between individual raised characters shall be 1/16 inch (1.6 mm) minimum and 4 times the raised character stroke width maximum at the base of the cross sections, and 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) minimum and 4 times the raised character stroke width maximum at the top of the cross sections.  Characters shall be separated from raised borders and decorative elements 3/8 inch (9.5 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_2_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.2.8 Line Spacing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Spacing between the baselines of separate lines of raised characters within a message shall be 135 percent minimum and 170 percent maximum of the raised character height.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-703_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.3 Braille[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Braille shall be contracted (Grade 2) and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_3" class="navSectionLink">703.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_4" class="navSectionLink">703.4</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.3.1 Dimensions and Capitalization[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Braille dots shall have a domed or rounded shape and shall comply with Table 703.3.1.  The indication of an uppercase letter or letters shall only be used before the first word of sentences, proper nouns and names, individual letters of the alphabet, initials, and acronyms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 703.3.1 Braille Dimensions[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Measurement Range[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Minimum in Inches Maximum in Inches[-END TRANSLATE-]</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Dot base diameter[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
<td>0.059 (1.5 mm)[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] to [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> 0.063 (1.6 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th aria-describedby="add1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Distance between [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]two dots in the same cell ¹[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>0.090 (2.3 mm)[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] to [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> 0.100 (2.5 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th aria-describedby="add1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Distance between corresponding dots [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]in adjacent cells ¹[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>0.241 (6.1 mm)[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] to [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> 0.300 (7.6 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Dot height[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>0.025 (0.6 mm)[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] to [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> 0.037 (0.9 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th aria-describedby="add1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Distance between [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]corresponding dots [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]from one cell directly below ¹[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>0.395 (10 mm)[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] to [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> 0.400 (10.2 mm)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><span class="text-italic">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table Legend:[-END TRANSLATE-]</span> 1. <span id="add1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Measured center to center[-END TRANSLATE-]</span>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 703.3.1 Braille Measurement"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "final_clip_image002_0000.jpg"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestran seis celdas Braille que indican lo que se entiende por diámetro de punto, distancia entre puntos en la misma celda, distancia entre puntos en celdas adyacentes, distancia entre puntos correspondientes de una celda directamente debajo en la Tabla 703.3.1"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Six Braille cells are shown indicating what is meant by dot diameter, distance between dots in the same cell, distance between dots in adjacent cells, distance between corresponding dots from one cell directly below in Table 703.3.1.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-703_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.3.2 Position[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Braille shall be positioned below the corresponding text.  If text is multi-lined, braille shall be placed below the entire text.  Braille shall be separated 3/8 inch (9.5 mm) minimum from any other tactile characters and 3/8 inch (9.5 mm) minimum from raised borders and decorative elements.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Braille provided on elevator car controls shall be separated 3/16 inch (4.8 mm) minimum and shall be located either directly below or adjacent to the corresponding raised characters or symbols.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 703.3.2 Position of Braille"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB93.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un detalle ampliado muestra puntos Braille colocados 3/8 pulgadas (9,5 mm) como mínimo por debajo de las letras táctiles y 3/8 de pulgada (9,5 mm) de separación mínima del borde del signo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An enlarged detail shows Braille dots positioned 3/8 inch (9.5 mm) minimum below tactile letters and 3/8 inch (9.5 mm) minimum separation from the sign border.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-703_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.4 Installation Height and Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Signs with tactile characters shall comply with 703.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.4.1 Height Above Finish Floor or Ground[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Tactile characters on signs shall be located 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum above the finish floor or ground surface, measured from the baseline of the lowest tactile character and 60 inches (1525 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground surface, measured from the baseline of the highest tactile character.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Tactile characters for elevator car controls shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_4_1" class="navSectionLink">703.4.1</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 703.4.1 Height of Tactile Characters Above Finish Floor or Ground"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB94.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra un letrero táctil montado con la línea de base de los caracteres más bajos 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) como mínimo y la línea de base de los caracteres más altos 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como máximo sobre el piso de acabado."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A tactile sign is shown mounted with the baseline of the lowest characters 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum and the baseline of the highest characters 60 inches (1525 mm) maximum above the finish floor.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-703_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.4.2 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a tactile sign is provided at a door, the sign shall be located alongside the door at the latch side.  Where a tactile sign is provided at double doors with one active leaf, the sign shall be located on the inactive leaf.  Where a tactile sign is provided at double doors with two active leafs, the sign shall be located to the right of the right hand door.  Where there is no wall space at the latch side of a single door or at the right side of double doors, signs shall be located on the nearest adjacent wall.  Signs containing tactile characters shall be located so that a clear floor space of 18 inches (455 mm) minimum by 18 inches (455 mm) minimum, centered on the tactile characters, is provided beyond the arc of any door swing between the closed position and 45 degree open position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Signs with tactile characters shall be permitted on the push side of doors with closers and without hold-open devices.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 703.4.2 Location of Tactile Signs at Doors"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB95.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se monta un letrero con caracteres táctiles para que el espacio libre del piso de 18 por 18 pulgadas (455 por 455 mm) como mínimo, centrado en los caracteres táctiles, se proporcione más allá del arco de cualquier oscilación de la puerta entre la posición cerrada y la posición abierta de 45 grados."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A sign with tactile characters is mounted so that clear floor space 18 by 18 inches (455 by 455 mm) minimum, centered on the tactile characters, is provided beyond the arc of any door swing between the closed position and 45 degree open position.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-703_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5 Visual Characters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Visual characters shall comply with 703.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: Where visual characters comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and are accompanied by braille complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_3" class="navSectionLink">703.3</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]they shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_2" class="navSectionLink">703.5.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_9" class="navSectionLink">703.5.9</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.1 Finish and Contrast[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters and their background shall have a non-glare finish. Characters shall contrast with their background with either light characters on a dark background or dark characters on a light background.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 703.5.1 Finish and Contrast.  Signs are more legible for persons with low vision when characters contrast as much as possible with their background.  Additional factors affecting the ease with which the text can be distinguished from its background include shadows cast by lighting sources, surface glare, and the uniformity of the text and its background colors and textures.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.2 Case[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters shall be uppercase or lowercase or a combination of both.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.3 Style[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters shall be conventional in form.  Characters shall not be italic, oblique, script, highly decorative, or of other unusual forms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.4 Character Proportions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters shall be selected from fonts where the width of the uppercase letter “O” is 55 percent minimum and 110 percent maximum of the height of the uppercase letter “I”.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.5 Character Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Minimum character height shall comply with Table 703.5.5. Viewing distance shall be measured as the horizontal distance between the character and an obstruction preventing further approach towards the sign.  Character height shall be based on the uppercase letter “I”.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Table 703.5.5 Visual Character Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Height to Finish Floor or Ground [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]from Baseline of Character[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Horizontal Viewing Distance[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Minimum Character Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope="row" rowspan="">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]40 inches (1015 mm) to less than or equal to 70 inches (1780 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]less than 72 inches (1830 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>5/8 inch (16 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="ro">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]72 inches (1830 mm) and greater[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]5/8 inch (16 mm), plus 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) per foot (305 mm) [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of viewing distance above 72 inches (1830 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" rowspan="2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Greater than 70 inches (1780 mm) [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to less than or equal to 120 inches (3050 mm)<[-END TRANSLATE-]/th>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]less than 180 inches (4570 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>2 inches (51 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="ro">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]180 inches (4570 mm) and greater[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2 inches (51 mm), plus 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) per foot (305 mm) [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of viewing distance above 180 inches (4570 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" rowspan="2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]greater than 120 inches (3050 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]less than 21 feet (6400 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>3 inches (75 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="ro">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]21 feet (6400 mm) and greater[-END TRANSLATE-]</th>
<td>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3 inches (75 mm), plus 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) per foot (305 mm) [-END TRANSLATE-]<br> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of viewing distance above 21 feet (6400 mm)[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.6 Height From Finish Floor or Ground[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Visual characters shall be 40 inches (1015 mm) minimum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Visual characters indicating elevator car controls shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_6" class="navSectionLink">703.5.6</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.7 Stroke Thickness[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Stroke thickness of the uppercase letter “I” shall be 10 percent minimum and 30 percent maximum of the height of the character.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.8 Character Spacing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Character spacing shall be measured between the two closest points of adjacent characters, excluding word spaces.  Spacing between individual characters shall be 10 percent minimum and 35 percent maximum of character height.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_5_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.5.9 Line Spacing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Spacing between the baselines of separate lines of characters within a message shall be 135 percent minimum and 170 percent maximum of the character height.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-703_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.6 Pictograms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pictograms shall comply with 703.6.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.6.1 Pictogram Field[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pictograms shall have a field height of 6 inches (150 mm) minimum.  Characters and braille shall not be located in the pictogram field.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 703.6.1 Pictogram Field"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB96.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La altura del campo para un pictograma de habitación para hombres se muestra como mínimo 6 pulgadas (150 mm).  Los caracteres táctiles y Braille se encuentran debajo, fuera del campo del pictograma."[-END TRANSLATE-]

The field height for a men’s room pictogram is shown to be 6 inches (150 mm) minimum.  Tactile and Braille characters are located below, outside the pictogram field.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-703_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.6.2 Finish and Contrast[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pictograms and their field shall have a non-glare finish. Pictograms shall contrast with their field with either a light pictogram on a dark field or a dark pictogram on a light field.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 703.6.2 Finish and Contrast.  Signs are more legible for persons with low vision when characters contrast as much as possible with their background.  Additional factors affecting the ease with which the text can be distinguished from its background include shadows cast by lighting sources, surface glare, and the uniformity of the text and background colors and textures.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_6_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.6.3 Text Descriptors[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pictograms shall have text descriptors located directly below the pictogram field.  Text descriptors shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a>, <a href="#ada-703_3" class="navSectionLink">703.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_4" class="navSectionLink">703.4</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-703_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.7 Symbols of Accessibility[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Symbols of accessibility shall comply with 703.7.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_7_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.7.1 Finish and Contrast[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Symbols of accessibility and their background shall have a non-glare finish.  Symbols of accessibility shall contrast with their background with either a light symbol on a dark background or a dark symbol on a light background.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 703.7.1 Finish and Contrast.  Signs are more legible for persons with low vision when characters contrast as much as possible with their background.  Additional factors affecting the ease with which the text can be distinguished from its background include shadows cast by lighting sources, surface glare, and the uniformity of the text and background colors and textures.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-703_7_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.7.2 Symbols.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<h5 id="ada-703_7_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]703.7.2.1 International Symbol of Accessibility[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The International Symbol of Accessibility shall comply with Figure 703.7.2.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
