<h2 id="ada-704">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704 Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-704_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Public telephones shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704" class="navSectionLink">704</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-704_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.2 Wheelchair Accessible Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair accessible telephones shall comply with 704.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-704_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.2.1 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.  The clear floor or ground space shall not be obstructed by bases, enclosures, or seats.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 704.2.1 Clear Floor or Ground Space.  Because clear floor and ground space is required to be unobstructed, telephones, enclosures and related telephone book storage cannot encroach on the required clear floor or ground space and must comply with the provisions for protruding objects.  (See Section 307).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-704_2_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.2.1.1 Parallel Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a parallel approach is provided, the distance from the edge of the telephone enclosure to the face of the telephone unit shall be 10 inches (255 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 704.2.1.1 Parallel Approach to Telephone"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB100.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La distancia máxima desde la cara del teléfono hasta el borde de la carcasa del teléfono es de 10 pulgadas (255 mm).  El espacio libre para un enfoque paralelo se encuentra frente al recinto."[-END TRANSLATE-]

The maximum distance from the face of the telephone to the edge of the telephone enclosure is 10 inches (255 mm).  Clear floor space for a parallel approach is located in front of the enclosure. 

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-704_2_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.2.1.2 Forward Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a forward approach is provided, the distance from the front edge of a counter within the telephone enclosure to the face of the telephone unit shall be 20 inches (510 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 704.2.1.2 Forward Approach to Telephone"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB101.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La distancia máxima desde el borde frontal de un mostrador dentro de la carcasa del teléfono hasta la cara del teléfono es de 20 pulgadas (510 mm).  La carcasa del teléfono se superpone al espacio libre del piso para un enfoque hacia adelante"[-END TRANSLATE-]

The maximum distance from the front edge of a counter within the telephone enclosure to the face of the telephone is 20 inches (510 mm).  The telephone enclosure overlaps the clear floor space for a forward approach.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-704_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.2.2 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Operable parts shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Telephones shall have push-button controls where such service is available.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-704_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.2.3 Telephone Directories[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Telephone directories, where provided, shall be located in accordance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-704_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.2.4 Cord Length[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The cord from the telephone to the handset shall be 29 inches (735 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-704_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.3 Volume Control Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Public telephones required to have volume controls shall be equipped with a receive volume control that provides a gain adjustable up to 20 dB minimum.  For incremental volume control, provide at least one intermediate step of 12 dB of gain minimum.  An automatic reset shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 704.3 Volume Control Telephones.  Amplifiers on pay phones are located in the base or the handset or are built into the telephone. Most are operated by pressing a button or key.  If the microphone in the handset is not being used, a mute button that temporarily turns off the microphone can also reduce the amount of background noise which the person hears in the earpiece.  If a volume adjustment is provided that allows the user to set the level anywhere from the base volume to the upper requirement of 20 dB, there is no need to specify a lower limit.  If a stepped volume control is provided, one of the intermediate levels must provide 12 dB of gain.  Consider compatibility issues when matching an amplified handset with a phone or phone system.  Amplified handsets that can be switched with pay telephone handsets are available.  Portable and in-line amplifiers can be used with some phones but are not practical at most public phones covered by these requirements.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-704_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.4 TTYs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]TTYs required at a public pay telephone shall be permanently affixed within, or adjacent to, the telephone enclosure.  Where an acoustic coupler is used, the telephone cord shall be sufficiently long to allow connection of the TTY and the telephone receiver.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 704.4 TTYs.  Ensure that sufficient electrical service is available where TTYs are to be installed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-704_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.4.1 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]When in use, the touch surface of TTY keypads shall be 34 inches (865 mm) minimum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where seats are provided, TTYs shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_4_1" class="navSectionLink">704.4.1</a>.</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 704.4.1 Height.  A telephone with a TTY installed underneath cannot also be a wheelchair accessible telephone because the required 34 inches (865 mm) minimum keypad height can cause the highest operable part of the telephone, usually the coin slot, to exceed the maximum permitted side and forward reach ranges.  (See Section 308).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="last">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 704.4.1 Height Exception. While seats are not required at TTYs, reading and typing at a TTY is more suited to sitting than standing. Facilities that often provide seats at TTY’s include, but are not limited to, airports and other passenger terminals or stations, courts, art galleries, and convention centers.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
<h3 id="ada-704_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]704.5 TTY Shelf[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Public pay telephones required to accommodate portable TTYs shall be equipped with a shelf and an electrical outlet within or adjacent to the telephone enclosure.  The telephone handset shall be capable of being placed flush on the surface of the shelf.  The shelf shall be capable of accommodating a TTY and shall have 6 inches (150 mm) minimum vertical clearance above the area where the TTY is to be placed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-705">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]705 Detectable Warnings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-705_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]705.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Detectable warnings shall consist of a surface of truncated domes and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-705" class="navSectionLink">705</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-705_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]705.1.1 Dome Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Truncated domes in a detectable warning surface shall have a base diameter of 0.9 inch (23 mm) minimum and 1.4 inches (36 mm) maximum, a top diameter of 50 percent of the base diameter minimum to 65 percent of the base diameter maximum, and a height of 0.2 inch (5.1 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-705_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]705.1.2 Dome Spacing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Truncated domes in a detectable warning surface shall have a center-to-center spacing of 1.6 inches (41 mm) minimum and 2.4 inches (61 mm) maximum, and a base-to-base spacing of 0.65 inch (17 mm) minimum, measured between the most adjacent domes on a square grid.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-705_1_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]705.1.3 Contrast[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Detectable warning surfaces shall contrast visually with adjacent walking surfaces either light-on-dark, or dark-on-light.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 705.1 Size and Spacing of Truncated Domes"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB102.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación ampliado de una sola cúpula que muestra el diámetro de la base como 0.9 a 1.4 pulgadas (23 a 36 mm) y la superficie superior como teniendo un diámetro del 50% al 65% del bas.  La altura de la cúpula es de 0,2 pulgadas (5,1 mm).  La Figura (b) es una vista plana de una superficie de advertencia detectable que muestra el espaciado de la cúpula de centro a centro de 1.6 a 2.4 pulgadas (41 a 61 mm) con una separación de base a base de 0.65 pulgadas (17 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an enlarged elevation drawing of a single dome showing the base diameter as 0.9 to 1.4 inches (23 to 36 mm) and the top surface as having a diameter of 50% to 65% of the bas.  The dome height is 0.2 inch (5.1 mm).  Figure (b) is a plan view of a detectable warning surface showing the center-to-center dome spacing of 1.6 to 2.4 inches (41 to 61 mm) with a base-to-base separation of 0.65 inch (17 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-705_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]705.2 Platform Edges[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Detectable warning surfaces at platform boarding edges shall be 24 inches (610 mm) wide and shall extend the full length of the public use areas of the platform.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-706">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]706 Assistive Listening Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-706_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]706.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Assistive listening systems required in assembly areas shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-706" class="navSectionLink">706</a>.</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 706.1 General.  Assistive listening systems are generally categorized by their mode of transmission.  There are hard-wired systems and three types of wireless systems: induction loop, infrared, and FM radio transmission.  Each has different advantages and disadvantages that can help determine which system is best for a given application.  For example, an FM system may be better than an infrared system in some open-air assemblies since infrared signals are less effective in sunlight.  On the other hand, an infrared system is typically a better choice than an FM system where confidential transmission is important because it will be contained within a given space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The technical standards for assistive listening systems describe minimum performance levels for volume, interference, and distortion.  Sound pressure levels (SPL), expressed in decibels, measure output sound volume.  Signal-to-noise ratio (SNR or S/N), also expressed in decibels, represents the relationship between the loudness of a desired sound (the signal) and the background noise in a space or piece of equipment.  The higher the SNR, the more intelligible the signal.  The peak clipping level limits the distortion in signal output produced when high-volume sound waves are manipulated to serve assistive listening devices.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="last">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Selecting or specifying an effective assistive listening system for a large or complex venue requires assistance from a professional sound engineer.  The Access Board has published technical assistance on assistive listening devices and systems.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
<h3 id="ada-706_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]706.2 Receiver Jacks[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Receivers required for use with an assistive listening system shall include a 1/8 inch (3.2 mm) standard mono jack.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-706_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]706.3 Receiver Hearing-Aid Compatibility[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Receivers required to be hearing-aid compatible shall interface with telecoils in hearing aids through the provision of neckloops.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 706.3 Receiver Hearing-Aid Compatibility.  Neckloops and headsets that can be worn as neckloops are compatible with hearing aids. Receivers that are not compatible include earbuds, which may require removal of hearing aids, earphones, and headsets that must be worn over the ear, which can create disruptive interference in the transmission and can be uncomfortable for people wearing hearing aids.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-706_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]706.4 Sound Pressure Level[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Assistive listening systems shall be capable of providing a sound pressure level of 110 dB minimum and 118 dB maximum with a dynamic range on the volume control of 50 dB.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-706_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]706.5 Signal-to-Noise Ratio[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The signal-to-noise ratio for internally generated noise in assistive listening systems shall be 18 dB minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-706_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]706.6 Peak Clipping Level[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Peak clipping shall not exceed 18 dB of clipping relative to the peaks of speech.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-707">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707 Automatic Teller Machines and Fare Machines[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 707 Automatic Teller Machines and Fare Machines.  Interactive transaction machines (ITMs), other than ATMs, are not covered by Section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-707" class="navSectionLink">707</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]However, for entities covered by the ADA, the Department of Justice regulations that implement the ADA provide additional guidance regarding the relationship between these requirements and elements that are not directly addressed by these requirements.  Federal procurement law requires that ITMs purchased by the Federal government comply with standards issued by the Access Board under Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, as amended.  This law covers a variety of products, including computer hardware and software, websites, phone systems, fax machines, copiers, and similar technologies.  For more information on Section 508 consult the Access Board’s website at www.access-board.gov.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Automatic teller machines and fare machines shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-707" class="navSectionLink">707</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 707.1 General.  If farecards have one tactually distinctive corner they can be inserted with greater accuracy. Token collection devices that are designed to accommodate tokens which are perforated can allow a person to distinguish more readily between tokens and common coins.  Place accessible gates and fare vending machines in close proximity to other accessible elements when feasible so the facility is easier to use.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.2 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Clear floor or ground space shall not be required at drive-up only automatic teller machines and fare machines.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.3 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Operable parts shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Unless a clear or correct key is provided, each operable part shall be able to be differentiated by sound or touch, without activation.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Drive-up only automatic teller machines and fare machines shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_2" class="navSectionLink">309.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_3" class="navSectionLink">309.3</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.4 Privacy[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Automatic teller machines shall provide the opportunity for the same degree of privacy of input and output available to all individuals.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 707.4 Privacy.  In addition to people who are blind or visually impaired, people with limited reach who use wheelchairs or have short stature, who cannot effectively block the ATM screen with their bodies, may prefer to use speech output.  Speech output users can benefit from an option to render the visible screen blank, thereby affording them greater personal security and privacy.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.5 Speech Output[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Machines shall be speech enabled.  Operating instructions and orientation, visible transaction prompts, user input verification, error messages, and all displayed information for full use shall be accessible to and independently usable by individuals with vision impairments. Speech shall be delivered through a mechanism that is readily available to all users, including but not limited to, an industry standard connector or a telephone handset.  Speech shall be recorded or digitized human, or synthesized.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-707_5x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Audible tones shall be permitted instead of speech for visible output that is not displayed for security purposes, including but not limited to, asterisks representing personal identification numbers.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-707_5x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Advertisements and other similar information shall not be required to be audible unless they convey information that can be used in the transaction being conducted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-707_5x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Where speech synthesis cannot be supported, dynamic alphabetic output shall not be required to be audible.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 707.5 Speech Output.  If an ATM provides additional functions such as dispensing coupons, selling theater tickets, or providing copies of monthly statements, all such functions must be available to customers using speech output.  To avoid confusion at the ATM, the method of initiating the speech mode should be easily discoverable and should not require specialized training.  For example, if a telephone handset is provided, lifting the handset can initiate the speech mode.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-707_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.5.1 User Control[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Speech shall be capable of being repeated or interrupted.  Volume control shall be provided for the speech function.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Speech output for any single function shall be permitted to be automatically interrupted when a transaction is selected.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-707_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.5.2 Receipts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where receipts are provided, speech output devices shall provide audible balance inquiry information, error messages, and all other information on the printed receipt necessary to complete or verify the transaction.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-707_5_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Machine location, date and time of transaction, customer account number, and the machine identifier shall not be required to be audible.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-707_5_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Information on printed receipts that duplicates information available on-screen shall not be required to be presented in the form of an audible receipt.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-707_5_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Printed copies of bank statements and checks shall not be required to be audible.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.6 Input[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Input devices shall comply with 707.6.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-707_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.6.1 Input Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one tactilely discernible input control shall be provided for each function.  Where provided, key surfaces not on active areas of display screens, shall be raised above surrounding surfaces.  Where membrane keys are the only method of input, each shall be tactilely discernable from surrounding surfaces and adjacent keys.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-707_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.6.2 Numeric Keys[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Numeric keys shall be arranged in a 12-key ascending or descending telephone keypad layout. The number five key shall be tactilely distinct from the other keys.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 707.6.2 Numeric Keys.  Telephone keypads and computer keyboards differ in one significant feature, ascending versus descending numerical order.  Both types of keypads are acceptable, provided the computer-style keypad is organized similarly to the number pad located at the right on most computer keyboards, and does not resemble the line of numbers located above the computer keys.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 707.6.2 Numeric Key Layout"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB103.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) muestra un diseño ascendente de 12 teclas con "1" en la esquina superior izquierda, como un teléfono.  La figura (b) muestra un diseño descendente con "7" en la esquina superior izquierda, como un teclado numérico de computadora."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a 12-key ascending layout with “1” in the upper left corner, such as a telephone.  Figure (b) shows a descending layout with “7” in the upper left corner, such as a computer numeric keypad.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-707_6_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.6.3 Function Keys[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Function keys shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-707_6_3" class="navSectionLink">707.6.3</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-707_6_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.6.3.1 Contrast[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Function keys shall contrast visually from background surfaces.  Characters and symbols on key surfaces shall contrast visually from key surfaces.  Visual contrast shall be either light-on-dark or dark-on-light.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Tactile symbols required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-707_6_3_2" class="navSectionLink">707.6.3.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-707_6_3_1" class="navSectionLink">707.6.3.1</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-707_6_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.6.3.2 Tactile Symbols[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Function key surfaces shall have tactile symbols as follows:  Enter or Proceed key: raised circle; Clear or Correct key: raised left arrow; Cancel key: raised letter ex; Add Value key: raised plus sign; Decrease Value key: raised minus sign.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.7 Display Screen[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The display screen shall comply with 707.7.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Drive-up only automatic teller machines and fare machines shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-707_7_1" class="navSectionLink">707.7.1</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-707_7_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.7.1 Visibility[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The display screen shall be visible from a point located 40 inches (1015 mm) above the center of the clear floor space in front of the machine.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-707_7_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.7.2 Characters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Characters displayed on the screen shall be in a sans serif font.  Characters shall be 3/16 inch (4.8 mm) high minimum based on the uppercase letter “I”.  Characters shall contrast with their background with either light characters on a dark background or dark characters on a light background.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-707_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]707.8 Braille Instructions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Braille instructions for initiating the speech mode shall be provided.  Braille shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_3" class="navSectionLink">703.3</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-708">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]708 Two-Way Communication Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-708_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]708.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Two-way communication systems shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-708" class="navSectionLink">708</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 708.1 General.  Devices that do not require handsets are easier to use by people who have a limited reach.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-708_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]708.2 Audible and Visual Indicators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The system shall provide both audible and visual signals.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 708.2 Audible and Visual Indicators.  A light can be used to indicate visually that assistance is on the way.  Signs indicating the meaning of visual signals should be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-708_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]708.3 Handsets[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handset cords, if provided, shall be 29 inches (735 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-708_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]708.4 Residential Dwelling Unit Communication Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Communications systems between a residential dwelling unit and a site, building, or floor entrance shall comply with 708.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-708_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]708.4.1 Common Use or Public Use System Interface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The common use or public use system interface shall include the capability of supporting voice and TTY communication with the residential dwelling unit interface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-708_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]708.4.2 Residential Dwelling Unit Interface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The residential dwelling unit system interface shall include a telephone jack capable of supporting voice and TTY communication with the common use or public use system interface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
  <h1></h1> <!--empty last heading for kms load function to work-->
  </div>   <!--close #adaCh7-->
  <div id="adaCh8">
  <h1 id="a8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Chapter 8: Special Rooms, Spaces, and Elements[-END TRANSLATE-]</h1>
  <h2 id="ada-801">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]801 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-801_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]801.1 Scope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The provisions of Chapter 8 shall apply where required by Chapter 2 or where referenced by a requirement in this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 801.1 Scope.  Facilities covered by these requirements are also subject to the requirements of the other chapters.  For example, <a href="#ada-806" class="navSectionLink">806</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]addresses guest rooms in transient lodging facilities while[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902" class="navSectionLink">902</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]contains the technical specifications for dining surfaces.  If a transient lodging facility contains a restaurant, the restaurant must comply with requirements in other chapters such as those applicable to certain dining surfaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-802">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802 Wheelchair Spaces, Companion Seats, and Designated Aisle Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-802_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.1 Wheelchair Spaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair spaces shall comply with 802.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.1.1 Floor or Ground Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The floor or ground surface of wheelchair spaces shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Changes in level are not permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.1.2 Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A single wheelchair space shall be 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum Where two adjacent wheelchair spaces are provided, each wheelchair space shall be 33 inches (840 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 802.1.2 Width of Wheelchair Spaces in Assembly Areas"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB104.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es una vista en planta de un solo espacio para sillas de ruedas de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho como mínimo.  La Figura (b) es una vista plana de dos espacios para sillas de ruedas uno al lado del otro.  Cada espacio tiene un mínimo de 33 pulgadas (840 mm) de ancho"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is a plan view of a single wheelchair space 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum.  Figure (b) is a plan view of two wheelchair spaces side by side.  Each space is 33 inches (840 mm) wide minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-802_1_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.1.3 Depth[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a wheelchair space can be entered from the front or rear, the wheelchair space shall be 48 inches (1220 mm) deep minimum. Where a wheelchair space can be entered only from the side, the wheelchair space shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) deep minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 802.1.3 Depth of Wheelchair Spaces in Assembly Areas"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB105.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) muestra un espacio para sillas de ruedas al que se puede ingresar desde la parte delantera o trasera que tiene un mínimo de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) de profundidad.  La Figura (b) muestra un espacio para sillas de ruedas ingresado desde el lado que tiene un mínimo de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de profundidad."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) shows a wheelchair space that can be entered from the front or rear that is 48 inches (1220 mm) deep minimum.  Figure (b) shows a wheelchair space entered from the side that is 60 inches (1525 mm) deep minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-802_1_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.1.4 Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair spaces shall adjoin accessible routes.  Accessible routes shall not overlap wheelchair spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 802.1.4 Approach.  Because accessible routes serving wheelchair spaces are not permitted to overlap the clear floor space at wheelchair spaces, access to any wheelchair space cannot be through another wheelchair space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_1_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.1.5 Overlap[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair spaces shall not overlap circulation paths.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 802.1.5 Overlap.  The term “circulation paths” used in Section 802.1.5 means aisle width required by applicable building or life safety codes for the specific assembly occupancy.  Where the circulation path provided is wider than the required aisle width, the wheelchair space may intrude into that portion of the circulation path that is provided in excess of the required aisle width.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-802_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.2 Lines of Sight[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Lines of sight to the screen, performance area, or playing field for spectators in wheelchair spaces shall comply with 802.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.2.1 Lines of Sight Over Seated Spectators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where spectators are expected to remain seated during events, spectators in wheelchair spaces shall be afforded lines of sight complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-802_2_1" class="navSectionLink">802.2.1</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-802_2_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.2.1.1 Lines of Sight Over Heads[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where spectators are provided lines of sight over the heads of spectators seated in the first row in front of their seats, spectators seated in wheelchair spaces shall be afforded lines of sight over the heads of seated spectators in the first row in front of wheelchair spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 802.2.1.1 Lines of Sight Over the Heads of Seated Spectators"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB106.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra a una persona usando una silla de ruedas en un nivel superior de asientos escalonados que tiene una línea de visión sobre las cabezas de los espectadores sentados al frente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows a person using a wheelchair on an upper level of tiered seating having a line of sight over the heads of spectators seated in front.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-802_2_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.2.1.2 Lines of Sight Between Heads[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where spectators are provided lines of sight over the shoulders and between the heads of spectators seated in the first row in front of their seats, spectators seated in wheelchair spaces shall be afforded lines of sight over the shoulders and between the heads of seated spectators in the first row in front of wheelchair spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 802.2.1.2 Lines of Sight Between the Heads of Seated Spectators"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB107.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra a una persona usando una silla de ruedas en un nivel superior de asientos escalonados que tiene una línea de visión entre las cabezas de los espectadores sentados al frente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows a person using a wheelchair on an upper level of tiered seating having a line of sight between the heads of spectators seated in front.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-802_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.2.2 Lines of Sight Over Standing Spectators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where spectators are expected to stand during events, spectators in wheelchair spaces shall be afforded lines of sight complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-802_2_2" class="navSectionLink">802.2.2</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-802_2_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.2.2.1 Lines of Sight Over Heads[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where standing spectators are provided lines of sight over the heads of spectators standing in the first row in front of their seats, spectators seated in wheelchair spaces shall be afforded lines of sight over the heads of standing spectators in the first row in front of wheelchair spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 802.2.2.1 Lines of Sight Over the Heads of Standing Spectators"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB108.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra a una persona usando una silla de ruedas en un nivel superior de asientos escalonados lo suficientemente elevados como para tener una línea de visión sobre las cabezas de los espectadores de pie en frente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows a person using a wheelchair on an upper level of tiered seating elevated sufficiently to have a line of sight over the heads of spectators standing in front.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h5 id="ada-802_2_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.2.2.2 Lines of Sight Between Heads[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where standing spectators are provided lines of sight over the shoulders and between the heads of spectators standing in the first row in front of their seats, spectators seated in wheelchair spaces shall be afforded lines of sight over the shoulders and between the heads of standing spectators in the first row in front of wheelchair spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 802.2.2.2 Lines of Sight Between the Heads of Standing Spectators"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB109.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "El dibujo de elevación muestra a una persona usando una silla de ruedas en un nivel superior de asientos escalonados lo suficientemente elevados como para tener una línea de visión entre las cabezas de los espectadores que están parados al frente."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Elevation drawing shows a person using a wheelchair on an upper level of tiered seating elevated sufficiently to have a line of sight between the heads of spectators standing in front.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-802_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.3 Companion Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Companion seats shall comply with 802.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.3.1 Alignment[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In row seating, companion seats shall be located to provide shoulder alignment with adjacent wheelchair spaces.  The shoulder alignment point of the wheelchair space shall be measured 36 inches (915 mm) from the front of the wheelchair space.  The floor surface of the companion seat shall be at the same elevation as the floor surface of the wheelchair space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.3.2 Type[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Companion seats shall be equivalent in size, quality, comfort, and amenities to the seating in the immediate area.  Companion seats shall be permitted to be movable.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-802_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.4 Designated Aisle Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Designated aisle seats shall comply with 802.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.4.1 Armrests[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where armrests are provided on the seating in the immediate area, folding or retractable armrests shall be provided on the aisle side of the seat.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-802_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]802.4.2 Identification[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each designated aisle seat shall be identified by a sign or marker.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 802.4.2 Identification.  Seats with folding or retractable armrests are intended for use by individuals who have difficulty walking.  Consider identifying such seats with signs that contrast (light-on-dark or dark-on-light) and that are also photo luminescent.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-803">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]803 Dressing, Fitting, and Locker Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-803_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]803.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Dressing, fitting, and locker rooms shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-803" class="navSectionLink">803</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 803.1 General.  Partitions and doors should be designed to ensure people using accessible dressing and fitting rooms privacy equivalent to that afforded other users of the facility.  Section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-903_5" class="navSectionLink">903.5</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]requires dressing room bench seats to be installed so that they are at the same height as a typical wheelchair seat, 17 inches (430 mm) to 19 inches (485 mm).  However, wheelchair seats can be lower than dressing room benches for people of short stature or children using wheelchairs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-803_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]803.2 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided within the room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-803_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]803.3 Door Swing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Doors shall not swing into the room unless a clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305_3" class="navSectionLink">305.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is provided beyond the arc of the door swing.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-803_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]803.4 Benches[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A bench complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-903" class="navSectionLink">903</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided within the room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-803_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]803.5 Coat Hooks and Shelves[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Coat hooks provided within the room shall be located within one of the reach ranges specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Shelves shall be 40 inches (1015 mm) minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-804">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804 Kitchens and Kitchenettes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-804_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Kitchens and kitchenettes shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804" class="navSectionLink">804</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-804_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.2 Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a pass through kitchen is provided, clearances shall comply with 804.2.1.  Where a U-shaped kitchen is provided, clearances shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804_2_2" class="navSectionLink">804.2.2</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Spaces that do not provide a cooktop or conventional range shall not be required to comply with 804.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 804.2 Clearance.  Clearances are measured from the furthest projecting face of all opposing base cabinets, counter tops, appliances, or walls, excluding hardware.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.2.1 Pass Through Kitchen[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In pass through kitchens where counters, appliances or cabinets are on two opposing sides, or where counters, appliances or cabinets are opposite a parallel wall, clearance between all opposing base cabinets, counter tops, appliances, or walls within kitchen work areas shall be 40 inches (1015 mm) minimum.  Pass through kitchens shall have two entries.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 804.2.1 Pass Through Kitchens"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB110.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista en planta de una cocina con electrodomésticos y gabinetes a ambos lados de un pasillo abierto en ambos extremos muestra el ancho del pasillo central como mínimo 40 pulgadas (1015 mm)."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view of a kitchen with appliances and cabinets on both sides of an aisle open on both ends shows the width of the central aisle as 40 inches (1015 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-804_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.2.2 U-Shaped[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In U-shaped kitchens enclosed on three contiguous sides, clearance between all opposing base cabinets, counter tops, appliances, or walls within kitchen work areas shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 804.2.2 U-Shaped Kitchens"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB111.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es una vista plana de una cocina con electrodomésticos y gabinetes en tres lados.  La figura (b) es una vista en planta de una cocina con electrodomésticos y gabinetes en dos opuestos con una pared en la parte trasera.  El ancho de la abertura de entrada de la cocina es de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is a plan view of a kitchen with appliances and cabinets on three sides.  Figure (b) is a plan view of a kitchen with appliances and cabinets on two opposites with a wall at the rear.  The width of the kitchen entry opening is 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-804_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.3 Kitchen Work Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In residential dwelling units required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809" class="navSectionLink">809</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]at least one 30 inches (760 mm) wide minimum section of counter shall provide a kitchen work surface that complies with 804.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.3.1 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for a forward approach shall be provided.  The clear floor or ground space shall be centered on the kitchen work surface and shall provide knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Cabinetry shall be permitted under the kitchen work surface provided that all of the following conditions are met:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<ol class="standards" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]the cabinetry can be removed without removal or replacement of the kitchen work surface;[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]the finish floor extends under the cabinetry; and[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
<li>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]the walls behind and surrounding the cabinetry are finished.[-END TRANSLATE-]</li>
</ol>
<h4 id="ada-804_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.3.2 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The kitchen work surface shall be 34 inches (865 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  A counter that is adjustable to provide a kitchen work surface at variable heights, 29 inches (735 mm) minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) maximum, shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.3.3 Exposed Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]There shall be no sharp or abrasive surfaces under the work surface counters.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-804_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.4 Sinks[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Sinks shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-606" class="navSectionLink">606</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-804_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.5 Storage[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least 50 percent of shelf space in storage facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-811" class="navSectionLink">811</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-804_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6 Appliances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, kitchen appliances shall comply with 804.6.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.1 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided at each kitchen appliance.  Clear floor or ground spaces shall be permitted to overlap.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.2 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All appliance controls shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-804_6_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Appliance doors and door latching devices shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-804_6_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Bottom-hinged appliance doors, when in the open position, shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_3" class="navSectionLink">309.3</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_6_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.3 Dishwasher[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clear floor or ground space shall be positioned adjacent to the dishwasher door.  The dishwasher door, in the open position, shall not obstruct the clear floor or ground space for the dishwasher or the sink.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_6_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.4 Range or Cooktop[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a forward approach is provided, the clear floor or ground space shall provide knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where knee and toe space is provided, the underside of the range or cooktop shall be insulated or otherwise configured to prevent burns, abrasions, or electrical shock.  The location of controls shall not require reaching across burners.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_6_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.5 Oven[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ovens shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804_6_5" class="navSectionLink">804.6.5</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-804_6_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.5.1 Side-Hinged Door Ovens[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Side-hinged door ovens shall have the work surface required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804_3" class="navSectionLink">804.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned adjacent to the latch side of the oven door.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-804_6_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.5.2 Bottom-Hinged Door Ovens[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bottom-hinged door ovens shall have the work surface required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804_3" class="navSectionLink">804.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned adjacent to one side of the door.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-804_6_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.5.3 Controls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ovens shall have controls on front panels.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-804_6_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]804.6.6 Refrigerator/Freezer[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Combination refrigerators and freezers shall have at least 50 percent of the freezer space 54 inches (1370 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.  The clear floor or ground space shall be positioned for a parallel approach to the space dedicated to a refrigerator/freezer with the centerline of the clear floor or ground space offset 24 inches (610 mm) maximum from the centerline of the dedicated space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-805">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]805 Medical Care and Long-Term Care Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-805_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]805.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Medical care facility and long-term care facility patient or resident sleeping rooms required to provide mobility features shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-805" class="navSectionLink">805</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-805_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]805.2 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided within the room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-805_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]805.3 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on each side of the bed.  The clear floor space shall be positioned for parallel approach to the side of the bed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-805_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]805.4 Toilet and Bathing Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet and bathing rooms that are provided as part of a patient or resident sleeping room shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, no fewer than one water closet, one lavatory, and one bathtub or shower shall comply with the applicable requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-806">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806 Transient Lodging Guest Rooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-806_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transient lodging guest rooms shall comply with 806.  Guest rooms required to provide mobility features shall comply with 806.2.  Guest rooms required to provide communication features shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806_3" class="navSectionLink">806.3</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-806_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2 Guest Rooms with Mobility Features[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Guest rooms required to provide mobility features shall comply with 806.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 806.2 Guest Rooms.  The requirements in Section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-806_2" class="navSectionLink">806.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]do not include requirements that are common to all accessible spaces. For example, closets in guest rooms must comply with the applicable provisions for storage specified in scoping.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2.1 Living and Dining Areas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Living and dining areas shall be accessible.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2.2 Exterior Spaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Exterior spaces, including patios, terraces and balconies, that serve the guest room shall be accessible.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2.3 Sleeping Areas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one sleeping area shall provide a clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]on both sides of a bed.  The clear floor space shall be positioned for parallel approach to the side of the bed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where a single clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for parallel approach is provided between two beds, a clear floor or ground space shall not be required on both sides of a bed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2.4 Toilet and Bathing Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one bathroom that is provided as part of a guest room shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]No fewer than one water closet, one lavatory, and one bathtub or shower shall comply with applicable requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In addition, required roll-in shower compartments shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-608_2_2" class="navSectionLink">608.2.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-608_2_3" class="navSectionLink">608.2.3</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet and bathing fixtures required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to be located in more than one toilet or bathing area, provided that travel between fixtures does not require travel between other parts of the guest room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-806_2_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2.4.1 Vanity Counter Top Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]If vanity counter top space is provided in non-accessible guest toilet or bathing rooms, comparable vanity counter top space, in terms of size and proximity to the lavatory, shall also be provided in accessible guest toilet or bathing rooms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 806.2.4.1 Vanity Counter Top Space.  This provision is intended to ensure that accessible guest rooms are provided with comparable vanity counter top space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_2_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2.5 Kitchens and Kitchenettes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Kitchens and kitchenettes shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804" class="navSectionLink">804</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_2_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.2.6 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided within the guest room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-806_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.3 Guest Rooms with Communication Features[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Guest rooms required to provide communication features shall comply with 806.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 806.3 Guest Rooms with Communication Features.  In guest rooms required to have accessible communication features, consider ensuring compatibility with adaptive equipment used by people with hearing impairments.  To ensure communication within the facility, as well as on commercial lines, provide telephone interface jacks that are compatible with both digital and analog signal use.  If an audio headphone jack is provided on a speaker phone, a cutoff switch can be included in the jack so that insertion of the jack cuts off the speaker.  If a telephone-like handset is used, the external speakers can be turned off when the handset is removed from the cradle.  For headset or external amplification system compatibility, a standard subminiature jack installed in the telephone will provide the most flexibility.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.3.1 Alarms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where emergency warning systems are provided, alarms complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-806_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]806.3.2 Notification Devices[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Visible notification devices shall be provided to alert room occupants of incoming telephone calls and a door knock or bell.  Notification devices shall not be connected to visible alarm signal appliances.  Telephones shall have volume controls compatible with the telephone system and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_3" class="navSectionLink">704.3</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Telephones shall be served by an electrical outlet complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]located within 48 inches (1220 mm) of the telephone to facilitate the use of a TTY.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-807">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807 Holding Cells and Housing Cells[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-807_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Holding cells and housing cells shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-807" class="navSectionLink">807</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-807_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.2 Cells with Mobility Features[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Cells required to provide mobility features shall comply with 807.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-807_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.2.1 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided within the cell.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-807_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.2.2 Benches[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where benches are provided, at least one bench shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-903" class="navSectionLink">903</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-807_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.2.3 Beds[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where beds are provided, clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on at least one side of the bed.  The clear floor space shall be positioned for parallel approach to the side of the bed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-807_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.2.4 Toilet and Bathing Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet facilities or bathing facilities that are provided as part of a cell shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, no fewer than one water closet, one lavatory, and one bathtub or shower shall comply with the applicable requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 807.2.4 Toilet and Bathing Facilities.  In holding cells, housing cells, or rooms required to be accessible, these requirements do not require a separate toilet room.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-807_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.3 Cells with Communication Features[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Cells required to provide communication features shall comply with 807.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-807_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.3.1 Alarms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where audible emergency alarm systems are provided to serve the occupants of cells, visible alarms complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Visible alarms shall not be required where inmates or detainees are not allowed independent means of egress.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-807_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]807.3.2 Telephones[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Telephones, where provided within cells, shall have volume controls complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_3" class="navSectionLink">704.3</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-808">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]808 Courtrooms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-808_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]808.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Courtrooms shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-808" class="navSectionLink">808</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-808_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]808.2 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, areas that are raised or depressed and accessed by ramps or platform lifts with entry ramps shall provide unobstructed turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-808_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]808.3 Clear Floor Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each jury box and witness stand shall have, within its defined area, clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In alterations, wheelchair spaces are not required to be located within the defined area of raised jury boxes or witness stands and shall be permitted to be located outside these spaces where ramp or platform lift access poses a hazard by restricting or projecting into a means of egress required by the appropriate administrative authority.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-808_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]808.4 Judges’ Benches and Courtroom Stations[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Judges’ benches, clerks’ stations, bailiffs’ stations, deputy clerks’ stations, court reporters’ stations and litigants’ and counsel stations shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902" class="navSectionLink">902</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-809">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809 Residential Dwelling Units[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-809_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Residential dwelling units shall comply with 809.  Residential dwelling units required to provide mobility features shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_2" class="navSectionLink">809.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through 809.4.  Residential dwelling units required to provide communication features shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_5" class="navSectionLink">809.5</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-809_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.2 Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes complying with Chapter 4 shall be provided within residential dwelling units in accordance with 809.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: Accessible routes shall not be required to or within unfinished attics or unfinished basements.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.2.1 Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one accessible route shall connect all spaces and elements which are a part of the residential dwelling unit.  Where only one accessible route is provided, it shall not pass through bathrooms, closets, or similar spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.2.2 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All rooms served by an accessible route shall provide a turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Turning space shall not be required in exterior spaces 30 inches (760 mm) maximum in depth or width.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 809.2.2 Turning Space.  It is generally acceptable to use required clearances to provide wheelchair turning space.  For example, in kitchens, <a href="#ada-804_3_1" class="navSectionLink">804.3.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]requires at least one work surface with clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to be centered beneath.  If designers elect to provide clear floor space that is at least 36 inches (915 mm) wide, as opposed to the required 30 inches (760 mm) wide, that clearance can be part of a T-turn, thereby maximizing efficient use of the kitchen area.  However, the overlap of turning space must be limited to one segment of the T-turn so that back-up maneuvering is not restricted.  It would, therefore, be unacceptable to use both the clearances under the work surface and the sink as part of a T-turn.  See Section[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304_3_2" class="navSectionLink">304.3.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]regarding T-turns.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-809_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.3 Kitchen[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a kitchen is provided, it shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-804" class="navSectionLink">804</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-809_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.4 Toilet Facilities and Bathing Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one bathroom shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]No fewer than one of each type of fixture provided shall comply with applicable requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Toilet and bathing fixtures required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-603" class="navSectionLink">603</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-610" class="navSectionLink">610</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be located in the same toilet and bathing area, such that travel between fixtures does not require travel between other parts of the residential dwelling unit.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 809.4 Toilet Facilities and Bathing Facilities.  In an effort to promote space efficiency, vanity counter top space in accessible residential dwelling units is often omitted.  This omission does not promote equal access or equal enjoyment of the unit.  Where comparable units have vanity counter tops, accessible units should also have vanity counter tops located as close as possible to the lavatory for convenient access to toiletries.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-809_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5 Residential Dwelling Units with Communication Features[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Residential dwelling units required to provide communication features shall comply with 809.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.1 Building Fire Alarm System[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a building fire alarm system is provided, the system wiring shall be extended to a point within the residential dwelling unit in the vicinity of the residential dwelling unit smoke detection system.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-809_5_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.1.1 Alarm Appliances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where alarm appliances are provided within a residential dwelling unit as part of the building fire alarm system, they shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-702" class="navSectionLink">702</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-809_5_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.1.2 Activation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All visible alarm appliances provided within the residential dwelling unit for building fire alarm notification shall be activated upon activation of the building fire alarm in the portion of the building containing the residential dwelling unit.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.2 Residential Dwelling Unit Smoke Detection System[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Residential dwelling unit smoke detection systems shall comply with NFPA 72 (1999 or 2002 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-809_5_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.2.1 Activation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All visible alarm appliances provided within the residential dwelling unit for smoke detection notification shall be activated upon smoke detection.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.3 Interconnection[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The same visible alarm appliances shall be permitted to provide notification of residential dwelling unit smoke detection and building fire alarm activation.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_5_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.4 Prohibited Use[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Visible alarm appliances used to indicate residential dwelling unit smoke detection or building fire alarm activation shall not be used for any other purpose within the residential dwelling unit.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_5_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.5 Residential Dwelling Unit Primary Entrance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Communication features shall be provided at the residential dwelling unit primary entrance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-809_5_5" class="navSectionLink">809.5.5</a>.</p>
<h5 id="ada-809_5_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.5.1 Notification[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A hard-wired electric doorbell shall be provided. A button or switch shall be provided outside the residential dwelling unit primary entrance.  Activation of the button or switch shall initiate an audible tone and visible signal within the residential dwelling unit.  Where visible doorbell signals are located in sleeping areas, they shall have controls to deactivate the signal.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-809_5_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.5.2 Identification[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A means for visually identifying a visitor without opening the residential dwelling unit entry door shall be provided and shall allow for a minimum 180 degree range of view.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 809.5.5.2 Identification.  In doors, peepholes that include prisms clarify the image and should offer a wide-angle view of the hallway or exterior for both standing persons and wheelchair users.  Such peepholes can be placed at a standard height and permit a view from several feet from the door.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-809_5_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]809.5.6 Site, Building, or Floor Entrance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a system, including a closed-circuit system, permitting voice communication between a visitor and the occupant of the residential dwelling unit is provided, the system shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-708_4" class="navSectionLink">708.4</a>.</p>
<h2 id="ada-810">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810 Transportation Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-810_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transportation facilities shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810" class="navSectionLink">810</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-810_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.2 Bus Boarding and Alighting Areas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bus boarding and alighting areas shall comply with 810.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 810.2 Bus Boarding and Alighting Areas.  At bus stops where a shelter is provided, the bus stop pad can be located either within or outside of the shelter.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.2.1 Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bus stop boarding and alighting areas shall have a firm, stable surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.2.2 Dimensions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bus stop boarding and alighting areas shall provide a clear length of 96 inches (2440 mm) minimum, measured perpendicular to the curb or vehicle roadway edge, and a clear width of 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum, measured parallel to the vehicle roadway.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 810.2.2 Dimensions of Bus Boarding and Alighting Areas"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB112.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de plano muestra un autobús detenido en un área para que los pasajeros aborden o bajen.  Un área despejada inmediatamente fuera de la puerta del autobús se muestra 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como mínimo, medido paralelo a la carretera y 96 pulgadas (1220 mm) como mínimo, medido perpendicularmente al bordillo o borde de la carretera."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows a bus pulled up to an area for passengers to board or alight.  A clear area immediately outside the bus door is shown 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum, measured parallel to the roadway and 96 inches (1220 mm) minimum, measured perpendicular to the curb or roadway edge.

