<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<p class="standards"><em>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Note to Reader:[-END TRANSLATE-]</em> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The Department of Transportation’s ADA standards indicate that compliance is required to the extent construction specifications are within a public entity’s control:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards"><strong>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.2.2 Dimensions.[-END TRANSLATE-]</strong> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bus boarding and alighting areas shall provide a clear length of 96 inches (2440 mm), measured perpendicular to the curb or vehicle roadway edge, and a clear width of 60 inches (1525 mm), measured parallel to the vehicle roadway. [-END TRANSLATE-]<em>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Public entities shall ensure that the construction of bus boarding and alighting areas comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_2_2" class="navSectionLink">810.2.2</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to the extent the construction specifications are within their control.[-END TRANSLATE-]</em></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4 id="ada-810_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.2.3 Connection[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bus stop boarding and alighting areas shall be connected to streets, sidewalks, or pedestrian paths by an accessible route complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-402" class="navSectionLink">402</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.2.4 Slope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Parallel to the roadway, the slope of the bus stop boarding and alighting area shall be the same as the roadway, to the maximum extent practicable.  Perpendicular to the roadway, the slope of the bus stop boarding and alighting area shall not be steeper than1:48.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-810_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.3 Bus Shelters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bus shelters shall provide a minimum clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]entirely within the shelter.  Bus shelters shall be connected by an accessible route complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-402" class="navSectionLink">402</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to a boarding and alighting area complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_2" class="navSectionLink">810.2</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 810.3 Bus Shelters"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB113.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista del plan muestra una marquesina de autobús con una persona que usa una silla de ruedas sentada completamente dentro.  Una ruta accesible conecta el área de asientos para sillas de ruedas dentro del refugio con el área de embarque y descenso del autobús que, en este caso, está fuera del refugio."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows a bus shelter with a person using a wheelchair seated fully within.  An accessible route connects the wheelchair seating area within the shelter to the bus boarding and alighting area which, in this case, is outside of the shelter. 

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-810_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.4 Bus Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Bus route identification signs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_1" class="navSectionLink">703.5.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]through[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_4" class="navSectionLink">703.5.4</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_7" class="navSectionLink">703.5.7</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_8" class="navSectionLink">703.5.8</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In addition, to the maximum extent practicable, bus route identification signs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5.5</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Bus schedules, timetables and maps that are posted at the bus stop or bus bay shall not be required to comply.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-810_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.5 Rail Platforms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Rail platforms shall comply with 810.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.5.1 Slope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Rail platforms shall not exceed a slope of 1:48 in all directions.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where platforms serve vehicles operating on existing track or track laid in existing roadway, the slope of the platform parallel to the track shall be permitted to be equal to the slope (grade) of the roadway or existing track.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.5.2 Detectable Warnings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Platform boarding edges not protected by platform screens or guards shall have detectable warnings complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-705" class="navSectionLink">705</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]along the full length of the public use area of the platform.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.5.3 Platform and Vehicle Floor Coordination[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Station platforms shall be positioned to coordinate with vehicles in accordance with the applicable requirements of 36 CFR Part 1192.  Low-level platforms shall be 8 inches (205 mm) minimum above top of rail.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where vehicles are boarded from sidewalks or street-level, low-level platforms shall be permitted to be less than 8 inches (205 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table role="presentation"  class="standards" style="width: 100%; background-color: #eeeeee; border: 1px solid #000000;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<p class="standards"><em>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Note to Reader:[-END TRANSLATE-]</em> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The Department of Transportation’s ADA standards note permitted alternatives where compliance is not operationally or structurally feasible in light rail, commuter rail, or intercity rail systems:[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards"><strong>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.5.3 Platform and Vehicle Floor Coordination.[-END TRANSLATE-]</strong> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Station platforms shall be positioned to coordinate with vehicles in accordance with the applicable requirements of 36 CFR part 1192. Low-level platforms shall be 8 inches (205 mm) minimum above top of rail.[-END TRANSLATE-]<em>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In light rail, commuter rail, and intercity rail systems where it is not operationally or structurally feasible to meet the horizontal gap or vertical difference requirements of part 1192 or 49 CFR part 38, mini-high platforms, car-borne or platform-mounted lifts, ramps or bridge plates or similarly manually deployed devices, meeting the requirements of 49 CFR part 38, shall suffice.[-END TRANSLATE-]</em></p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION: Where vehicles are boarded from sidewalks or street- level, low-level platforms shall be permitted to be less than 8 inches (205 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 810.5.3 Platform and Vehicle Floor Coordination.  The height and position of a platform must be coordinated with the floor of the vehicles it serves to minimize the vertical and horizontal gaps, in accordance with the ADA Accessibility Guidelines for Transportation Vehicles (36 CFR Part 1192).  The vehicle guidelines, divided by bus, van, light rail, rapid rail, commuter rail, intercity rail, are available at www.access-board.gov.  The preferred alignment is a high platform, level with the vehicle floor.  In some cases, the vehicle guidelines permit use of a low platform in conjunction with a lift or ramp.  Most such low platforms must have a minimum height of eight inches above the top of the rail.  Some vehicles are designed to be boarded from a street or the sidewalk along the street and the exception permits such boarding areas to be less than eight inches high.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-810_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.6 Rail Station Signs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Rail station signs shall comply with 810.6.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION.  Signs shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_6_1" class="navSectionLink">810.6.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-810_6_2" class="navSectionLink">810.6.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]where audible signs are remotely transmitted to hand-held receivers, or are user- or proximity-actuated.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 810.6 Rail Station Signs Exception.  Emerging technologies such as an audible sign systems using infrared transmitters and receivers may provide greater accessibility in the transit environment than traditional Braille and raised letter signs.  The transmitters are placed on or next to print signs and transmit their information to an infrared receiver that is held by a person.  By scanning an area, the person will hear the sign.  This means that signs can be placed well out of reach of Braille readers, even on parapet walls and on walls beyond barriers.  Additionally, such signs can be used to provide wayfinding information that cannot be efficiently conveyed on Braille signs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.6.1 Entrances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where signs identify a station or its entrance, at least one sign at each entrance shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be placed in uniform locations to the maximum extent practicable.  Where signs identify a station that has no defined entrance, at least one sign shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and shall be placed in a central location.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.6.2 Routes and Destinations[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Lists of stations, routes and destinations served by the station which are located on boarding areas, platforms, or mezzanines shall comply with 703.5.  At least one tactile sign identifying the specific station and complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_2" class="navSectionLink">703.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on each platform or boarding area.  Signs covered by this requirement shall, to the maximum extent practicable, be placed in uniform locations within the system.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where sign space is limited, characters shall not be required to exceed 3 inches (75 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 810.6.2 Routes and Destinations.  Route maps are not required to comply with the informational sign requirements in this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_6_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.6.3 Station Names[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Stations covered by this section shall have identification signs complying with 703.5.  Signs shall be clearly visible and within the sight lines of standing and sitting passengers from within the vehicle on both sides when not obstructed by another vehicle.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 810.6.3 Station Names.  It is also important to place signs at intervals in the station where passengers in the vehicle will be able to see a sign when the vehicle is either stopped at the station or about to come to a stop in the station.  The number of signs necessary may be directly related to the size of the lettering displayed on the sign.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-810_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.7 Public Address Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where public address systems convey audible information to the public, the same or equivalent information shall be provided in a visual format.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-810_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.8 Clocks[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where clocks are provided for use by the public, the clock face shall be uncluttered so that its elements are clearly visible.  Hands, numerals and digits shall contrast with the background either light-on-dark or dark-on-light.  Where clocks are installed overhead, numerals and digits shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_5" class="navSectionLink">703.5</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-810_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.9 Escalators[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, escalators shall comply with the sections 6.1.3.5.6 and 6.1.3.6.5 of ASME A17.1 (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1) and shall have a clear width of 32 inches (815 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Existing escalators in key stations shall not be required to comply with 810.9.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-810_10">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]810.10 Track Crossings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where a circulation path serving boarding platforms crosses tracks, it shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-402" class="navSectionLink">402</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Openings for wheel flanges shall be permitted to be 2½ inches (64 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 810.10 (Exception) Track Crossings"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB114.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Se muestra una sección transversal de un par de rieles de tren con superficies de pasarela que colindan con los rieles en el exterior del par.  La superficie entre los rieles está al mismo nivel que las superficies exteriores, pero se muestra un espacio horizontal de 21/2 pulgadas (64 mm) como máximo en el borde interior de cada riel para acomodar una brida de rueda de tren."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A cross section of a pair of train rails is shown with walkway surfaces abutting the rails on the outside of the pair.  The surface between the rails is at the same level as the outside surfaces, but a horizontal gap 2½ inches (64 mm) maximum is shown on the inner edge of each rail to accommodate a train wheel flange.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h2 id="ada-811">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]811 Storage[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-811_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]811.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Storage shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-811" class="navSectionLink">811</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-811_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]811.2 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-811_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]811.3 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Storage elements shall comply with at least one of the reach ranges specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-811_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]811.4 Operable Parts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Operable parts shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309" class="navSectionLink">309</a>.</p>
  <h1></h1> <!--empty last heading for kms load function to work-->
  </div>   <!--close #adaCh8-->
  <div id="adaCh9">
  <h1 id="a9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Chapter 9: Built-In Elements[-END TRANSLATE-]</h1>
  <h2 id="ada-901">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]901 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-901_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]901.1 Scope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The provisions of Chapter 9 shall apply where required by Chapter 2 or where referenced by a requirement in this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-902">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]902 Dining Surfaces and Work Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-902_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]902.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Dining surfaces and work surfaces shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902_2" class="navSectionLink">902.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902_3" class="navSectionLink">902.3</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Dining surfaces and work surfaces for children’s use shall be permitted to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902_4" class="navSectionLink">902.4</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 902.1 General. Dining surfaces include, but are not limited to, bars, tables, lunch counters, and booths. Examples of work surfaces include writing surfaces, study carrels, student laboratory stations, baby changing and other tables or fixtures for personal grooming, coupon counters, and where covered by the ABA scoping provisions, employee work stations.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-902_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]902.2 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for a forward approach shall be provided.  Knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-902_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]902.3 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The tops of dining surfaces and work surfaces shall be 28 inches (710 mm) minimum and 34 inches (865 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-902_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]902.4 Dining Surfaces and Work Surfaces for Children’s Use[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible dining surfaces and work surfaces for children’s use shall comply with 902.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Dining surfaces and work surfaces that are used primarily by children 5 years and younger shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902_4" class="navSectionLink">902.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]where a clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for a parallel approach is provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-902_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]902.4.1 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for forward approach shall be provided.  Knee and toe clearance complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided, except that knee clearance 24 inches (610 mm) minimum above the finish floor or ground shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-902_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]902.4.2 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The tops of tables and counters shall be 26 inches (660 mm) minimum and 30 inches (760 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-903">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903 Benches[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-903_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Benches shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-903" class="navSectionLink">903</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-903_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903.2 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided and shall be positioned at the end of the bench seat and parallel to the short axis of the bench.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-903_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903.3 Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Benches shall have seats that are 42 inches (1065 mm) long minimum and 20 inches (510 mm) deep minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) deep maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-903_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903.4 Back Support[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The bench shall provide for back support or shall be affixed to a wall.  Back support shall be 42 inches (1065 mm) long minimum and shall extend from a point 2 inches (51 mm) maximum above the seat surface to a point 18 inches (455 mm) minimum above the seat surface.  Back support shall be 2½ inches (64 mm) maximum from the rear edge of the seat measured horizontally.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 903.4 Back Support.  To assist in transferring to the bench, consider providing grab bars on a wall adjacent to the bench, but not on the seat back.  If provided, grab bars cannot obstruct transfer to the bench.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 903.4 Bench Back Support"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB115.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación de un banco con respaldo.  El borde inferior del respaldo es de 2 pulgadas (51 mm) como máximo por encima de la superficie del asiento y el borde superior del respaldo está a 18 pulgadas (455 mm) por encima de la superficie del asiento.  La figura (b) muestra la distancia entre el borde trasero del asiento y la cara delantera del soporte trasero como máximo 2 pulgadas (64 mm)."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing of a bench with a back.  The bottom edge of the back is 2 inches (51 mm) maximum above the seat surface and the top edge of the back is 18 inches (455 mm) above the seat surface.  Figure (b) shows the distance between the rear edge of the seat and the front face of the back support as 2 inches (64 mm) maximum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-903_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903.5 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The top of the bench seat surface shall be 17 inches (430 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-903_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903.6 Structural Strength[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Allowable stresses shall not be exceeded for materials used when a vertical or horizontal force of 250 pounds (1112 N) is applied at any point on the seat, fastener, mounting device, or supporting structure.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-903_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]903.7 Wet Locations[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where installed in wet locations, the surface of the seat shall be slip resistant and shall not accumulate water.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-904">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904 Check-Out Aisles and Sales and Service Counters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-904_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Check-out aisles and sales and service counters shall comply with the applicable requirements of[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904" class="navSectionLink">904</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-904_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.2 Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All portions of counters required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904" class="navSectionLink">904</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be located adjacent to a walking surface complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-403" class="navSectionLink">403</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 904.2 Approach.  If a cash register is provided at the sales or service counter, locate the accessible counter close to the cash register so that a person using a wheelchair is visible to sales or service personnel and to minimize the reach for a person with a disability.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-904_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.3 Check-Out Aisles[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Check-out aisles shall comply with 904.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-904_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.3.1 Aisle[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Aisles shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-403" class="navSectionLink">403</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-904_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.3.2 Counter[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The counter surface height shall be 38 inches (965 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.  The top of the counter edge protection shall be 2 inches (51 mm) maximum above the top of the counter surface on the aisle side of the check-out counter.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 904.3.2 Check-Out Aisle Counters"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB116.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una superficie de contador se muestra en elevación con una altura máxima de 38 pulgadas (965 mm) sobre el piso o el suelo y con protección de borde sobre la superficie que es de 2 pulgadas (51 mm) de altura máximo"[-END TRANSLATE-]

A counter surface is shown in elevation with a maximum height of 38 inches (965 mm) above the floor or ground and with edge protection above the surface that is 2 inches (51 mm) high maximum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-904_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.3.3 Check Writing Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, check writing surfaces shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-902_3" class="navSectionLink">902.3</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-904_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.4 Sales and Service Counters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Sales counters and service counters shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_4_1" class="navSectionLink">904.4.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]or[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_4_2" class="navSectionLink">904.4.2</a>. [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The accessible portion of the counter top shall extend the same depth as the sales or service counter top.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In alterations, when the provision of a counter complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_4" class="navSectionLink">904.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]would result in a reduction of the number of existing counters at work stations or a reduction of the number of existing mail boxes, the counter shall be permitted to have a portion which is 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-904_4_1" class="navSectionLink">904.4.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]provided that the required clear floor or ground space is centered on the accessible length of the counter.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 904.4 (Exception) Alteration of Sales and Service Counters"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB117.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de planta muestra una porción de un contador de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) de largo como mínimo en el que se centra la dimensión larga del piso despejado o el espacio del suelo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows a portion of a counter 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum at which is centered the long dimension of clear floor or ground space.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-904_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.4.1 Parallel Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A portion of the counter surface that is 36 inches (915 mm) long minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) high maximum above the finish floor shall be provided.  A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be positioned for a parallel approach adjacent to the 36 inch (915 mm) minimum length of counter.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where the provided counter surface is less than 36 inches (915 mm) long, the entire counter surface shall be 36 inches (915 mm) high maximum above the finish floor.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-904_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.4.2 Forward Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A portion of the counter surface that is 30 inches (760 mm) long minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) high maximum shall be provided.  Knee and toe space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-306" class="navSectionLink">306</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided under the counter.  A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be positioned for a forward approach to the counter.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-904_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.5 Food Service Lines[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Counters in food service lines shall comply with 904.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-904_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.5.1 Self-Service Shelves and Dispensing Devices[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Self-service shelves and dispensing devices for tableware, dishware, condiments, food and beverages shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-308" class="navSectionLink">308</a>.</p>
<h4 id="ada-904_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.5.2 Tray Slides[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The tops of tray slides shall be 28 inches (710 mm) minimum and 34 inches (865 mm) maximum above the finish floor or ground.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-904_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]904.6 Security Glazing[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where counters or teller windows have security glazing to separate personnel from the public, a method to facilitate voice communication shall be provided. Telephone handset devices, if provided, shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-704_3" class="navSectionLink">704.3</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 904.6 Security Glazing.  Assistive listening devices complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-706" class="navSectionLink">706</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]can facilitate voice communication at counters or teller windows where there is security glazing which promotes distortion in audible information. Where assistive listening devices are installed, place signs complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-703_7_2_4" class="navSectionLink">703.7.2.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]to identify those facilities which are so equipped.  Other voice communication methods include, but are not limited to, grilles, slats, talk-through baffles, intercoms, or telephone handset devices.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
  <h1></h1> <!--empty last heading for kms load function to work-->
  </div>   <!--close #adaCh9-->
  <div id="adaCh10">
  <h1 id="ada-10">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Chapter 10: Recreation Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h1>
  <h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1001 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1001_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1001.1 Scope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The provisions of Chapter 10 shall apply where required by Chapter 2 or where referenced by a requirement in this document.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1001.1 Scope.  Unless otherwise modified or specifically addressed in Chapter 10, all other ADAAG provisions apply to the design and construction of recreation facilities and elements.  The provisions in Section 1001.1 apply wherever these elements are provided.  For example, office buildings may contain a room with exercise equipment to which these sections would apply.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002 Amusement Rides[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1002_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Amusement rides shall comply with 1002.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1002_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.2 Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving amusement rides shall comply with Chapter 4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1002_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  In load or unload areas and on amusement rides, where compliance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_2" class="navSectionLink">405.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is not structurally or operationally feasible, ramp slope shall be permitted to be 1:8 maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1002_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  In load or unload areas and on amusement rides, handrails provided along walking surfaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-403" class="navSectionLink">403</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and required on ramps complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405" class="navSectionLink">405</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]where compliance is not structurally or operationally feasible.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1002.2 Accessible Routes Exception 1.  Steeper slopes are permitted on accessible routes connecting the amusement ride in the load and unload position where it is “structurally or operationally infeasible.” In most cases, this will be limited to areas where the accessible route leads directly to the amusement ride and where there are space limitations on the ride, not the queue line.  Where possible, the least possible slope should be used on the accessible route that serves the amusement ride.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1002_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.3 Load and Unload Areas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304_2" class="navSectionLink">304.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304_3" class="navSectionLink">304.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in load and unload areas.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1002_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4 Wheelchair Spaces in Amusement Rides[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair spaces in amusement rides shall comply with 1002.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.1 Floor or Ground Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The floor or ground surface of wheelchair spaces shall be stable and firm.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.2 Slope[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The floor or ground surface of wheelchair spaces shall have a slope not steeper than 1:48 when in the load and unload position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.3 Gaps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Floors of amusement rides with wheelchair spaces and floors of load and unload areas shall be coordinated so that, when amusement rides are at rest in the load and unload position, the vertical difference between the floors shall be within plus or minus 5/8 inches (16 mm) and the horizontal gap shall be 3 inches (75 mm) maximum under normal passenger load conditions.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where compliance is not operationally or structurally feasible, ramps, bridge plates, or similar devices complying with the applicable requirements of 36 CFR 1192.83(c) shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1002.4.3 Gaps Exception.  36 CFR 1192.83© ADA Accessibility Guidelines for Transportation Vehicles – Light Rail Vehicles and Systems – Mobility Aid Accessibility is available at www.access-board.gov.  It includes provisions for bridge plates and ramps that can be used at gaps between wheelchair spaces and floors of load and unload areas.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.4 Clearances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearances for wheelchair spaces shall comply with 1002.4.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1002_4_4x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS: 1.  Where provided, securement devices shall be permitted to overlap required clearances.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1002_4_4x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Wheelchair spaces shall be permitted to be mechanically or manually repositioned.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1002_4_4x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Wheelchair spaces shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-307_4" class="navSectionLink">307.4</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1002.4.4 Clearances Exception 3.  This exception for protruding objects applies to the ride devices, not to circulation areas or accessible routes in the queue lines or the load and unload areas.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1002_4_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.4.1 Width and Length.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair spaces shall provide a clear width of 30 inches (760 mm) minimum and a clear length of 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum measured to 9 inches (230 mm) minimum above the floor surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1002_4_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.4.2 Side Entry.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where wheelchair spaces are entered only from the side, amusement rides shall be designed to permit sufficient maneuvering clearance for individuals using a wheelchair or mobility aid to enter and exit the ride.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1002.4.4.2 Side Entry.  The amount of clear space needed within the ride, and the size and position of the opening are interrelated.  A 32 inch (815 mm) clear opening will not provide sufficient width when entered through a turn into an amusement ride.  Additional space for maneuvering and a wider door will be needed where a side opening is centered on the ride.  For example, where a 42 inch (1065 mm) opening is provided, a minimum clear space of 60 inches (1525 mm) in length and 36 inches (915mm) in depth is needed to ensure adequate space for maneuvering.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1002_4_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.4.3 Permitted Protrusions in Wheelchair Spaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Objects are permitted to protrude a distance of 6 inches (150 mm) maximum along the front of the wheelchair space, where located 9 inches (230 mm) minimum and 27 inches (685 mm) maximum above the floor or ground surface of the wheelchair space. Objects are permitted to protrude a distance of 25 inches (635 mm) maximum along the front of the wheelchair space, where located more than 27 inches (685 mm) above the floor or ground surface of the wheelchair space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1002.4.4.3 Protrusions in Wheelchair Spaces in Amusement Rides"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB118.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación de una persona sentada en una silla de ruedas en un paseo de diversión muestra que los objetos pueden sobresalir 6 pulgadas (150 mm) como máximo a lo largo de la parte delantera del espacio para sillas de ruedas donde se encuentran 9 pulgadas (230 mm) como mínimo y 27 pulgadas (685 mm) como máximo sobre el piso o la superficie del suelo del espacio para sillas de ruedas.  Los objetos pueden sobresalir a una distancia de 25 pulgadas como máximo a lo largo de la parte delantera del espacio para sillas de ruedas, donde se encuentran a más de 27 pulgadas sobre el piso o la superficie del suelo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing of a person seated in a wheelchair on an amusement ride shows that objects may protrude 6 inches (150 mm) maximum along the front of the wheelchair space where located 9 inches (230 mm) minimum and 27 inches (685 mm) maximum above the floor or ground surface of the wheelchair space.  Objects may protrude a distance of 25 inches maximum along the front of the wheelchair space, where located more than 27 inches above the floor or ground surface.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1002_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.5 Ride Entry[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Openings providing entry to wheelchair spaces on amusement rides shall be 32 inches (815 mm) minimum clear.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_4_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.6 Approach[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]One side of the wheelchair space shall adjoin an accessible route when in the load and unload position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_4_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.7 Companion Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where the interior width of the amusement ride is greater than 53 inches (1345 mm), seating is provided for more than one rider, and the wheelchair is not required to be centered within the amusement ride, a companion seat shall be provided for each wheelchair space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1002_4_7_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.4.7.1 Shoulder-to-Shoulder Seating.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where an amusement ride provides shoulder-to-shoulder seating, companion seats shall be shoulder-to-shoulder with the adjacent wheelchair space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where shoulder-to-shoulder companion seating is not operationally or structurally feasible, compliance with this requirement shall be required to the maximum extent practicable.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1002_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.5 Amusement Ride Seats Designed for Transfer[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Amusement ride seats designed for transfer shall comply with 1002.5 when positioned for loading and unloading.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1002.5 Amusement Ride Seats Designed for Transfer.  The proximity of the clear floor or ground space next to an element and the height of the element one is transferring to are both critical for a safe and independent transfer.  Providing additional clear floor or ground space both in front of and diagonal to the element will provide flexibility and will increase usability for a more diverse population of individuals with disabilities.  Ride seats designed for transfer should involve only one transfer.  Where possible, designers are encouraged to locate the ride seat no higher than 17 to 19 inches (430 to 485 mm) above the load and unload surface.  Where greater distances are required for transfers, providing gripping surfaces, seat padding, and avoiding sharp objects in the path of transfer will facilitate the transfer.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.5.1 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in the load and unload area adjacent to the amusement ride seats designed for transfer.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.5.2 Transfer Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The height of amusement ride seats designed for transfer shall be 14 inches (355 mm) minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) maximum measured from the surface of the load and unload area.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.5.3 Transfer Entry[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where openings are provided for transfer to amusement ride seats, the openings shall provide clearance for transfer from a wheelchair or mobility aid to the amusement ride seat.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_5_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.5.4 Wheelchair Storage Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair storage spaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in or adjacent to unload areas for each required amusement ride seat designed for transfer and shall not overlap any required means of egress or accessible route.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1002_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.6 Transfer Devices for Use with Amusement Rides[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer devices for use with amusement rides shall comply with 1002.6 when positioned for loading and unloading.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1002.6 Transfer Devices for Use with Amusement Rides.  Transfer devices for use with amusement rides should permit individuals to make independent transfers to and from their wheelchairs or mobility devices.  There are a variety of transfer devices available that could be adapted to provide access onto an amusement ride.  Examples of devices that may provide for transfers include, but are not limited to, transfer systems, lifts, mechanized seats, and custom designed systems.  Operators and designers have flexibility in developing designs that will facilitate individuals to transfer onto amusement rides.  These systems or devices should be designed to be reliable and sturdy.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="last">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Designs that limit the number of transfers required from a wheelchair or mobility device to the ride seat are encouraged.  When using a transfer device to access an amusement ride, the least number of transfers and the shortest distance is most usable.  Where possible, designers are encouraged to locate the transfer device seat no higher than 17 to 19 inches (430 to 485 mm) above the load and unload surface.  Where greater distances are required for transfers, providing gripping surfaces, seat padding, and avoiding sharp objects in the path of transfer will facilitate the transfer.  Where a series of transfers are required to reach the amusement ride seat, each vertical transfer should not exceed 8 inches (205 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
<h4 id="ada-1002_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.6.1 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in the load and unload area adjacent to the transfer device.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.6.2 Transfer Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The height of transfer device seats shall be 14 inches (355 mm) minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) maximum measured from the load and unload surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1002_6_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1002.6.3 Wheelchair Storage Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Wheelchair storage spaces complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided in or adjacent to unload areas for each required transfer device and shall not overlap any required means of egress or accessible route.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003 Recreational Boating Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1003_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Recreational boating facilities shall comply with 1003.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1003_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003.2 Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving recreational boating facilities, including gangways and floating piers, shall comply with Chapter 4 except as modified by the exceptions in 1003.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1003_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003.2.1 Boat Slips[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving boat slips shall be permitted to use the exceptions in 1003.2.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Where an existing gangway or series of gangways is replaced or altered, an increase in the length of the gangway shall not be required to comply with 1003.2 unless required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-202_4" class="navSectionLink">202.4</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Gangways shall not be required to comply with the maximum rise specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_6" class="navSectionLink">405.6</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Where the total length of a gangway or series of gangways serving as part of a required accessible route is 80 feet (24 m) minimum, gangways shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_2" class="navSectionLink">405.2</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]4.  Where facilities contain fewer than 25 boat slips and the total length of the gangway or series of gangways serving as part of a required accessible route is 30 feet (9145 mm) minimum, gangways shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_2" class="navSectionLink">405.2</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]5.  Where gangways connect to transition plates, landings specified by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_7" class="navSectionLink">405.7</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]6.  Where gangways and transition plates connect and are required to have handrails, handrail extensions shall not be required. Where handrail extensions are provided on gangways or transition plates, the handrail extensions shall not be required to be parallel with the ground or floor surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]7.  The cross slope specified in[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-403_3" class="navSectionLink">403.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_3" class="navSectionLink">405.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]for gangways, transition plates, and floating piers that are part of accessible routes shall be measured in the static position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]8.  Changes in level complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303_3" class="navSectionLink">303.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-303_4" class="navSectionLink">303.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted on the surfaces of gangways and boat launch ramps.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1003.2.1 Boat Slips Exception 3.  The following example shows how exception 3 would be applied:  A gangway is provided to a floating pier which is required to be on an accessible route.  The vertical distance is 10 feet (3050 mm) between the elevation where the gangway departs the landside connection and the elevation of the pier surface at the lowest water level.  Exception 3 permits the gangway to be 80 feet (24 m) long. Another design solution would be to have two 40 foot (12 m) plus continuous gangways joined together at a float, where the float (as the water level falls) will stop dropping at an elevation five feet below the landside connection.  The length of transition plates would not be included in determining if the gangway(s) meet the requirements of the exception.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1003_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003.2.2 Boarding Piers at Boat Launch Ramps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving boarding piers at boat launch ramps shall be permitted to use the exceptions in 1003.2.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Accessible routes serving floating boarding piers shall be permitted to use Exceptions 1, 2, 5, 6, 7 and 8 in 1003.2.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where the total length of the gangway or series of gangways serving as part of a required accessible route is 30 feet (9145 mm) minimum, gangways shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_2" class="navSectionLink">405.2</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_2_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Where the accessible route serving a floating boarding pier or skid pier is located within a boat launch ramp, the portion of the accessible route located within the boat launch ramp shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405" class="navSectionLink">405</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-1003_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003.3 Clearances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clearances at boat slips and on boarding piers at boat launch ramps shall comply with 1003.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1003.3 Clearances.  Although the minimum width of the clear pier space is 60 inches (1525 mm), it is recommended that piers be wider than 60 inches (1525 mm) to improve the safety for persons with disabilities, particularly on floating piers.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1003_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003.3.1 Boat Slip Clearance[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Boat slips shall provide clear pier space 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and at least as long as the boat slips.  Each 10 feet (3050 mm) maximum of linear pier edge serving boat slips shall contain at least one continuous clear opening 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_3_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Clear pier space shall be permitted to be 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum for a length of 24 inches (610 mm) maximum, provided that multiple 36 inch (915 mm) wide segments are separated by segments that are 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and 60 inches (1525 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_3_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Edge protection shall be permitted at the continuous clear openings, provided that it is 4 inches (100 mm) high maximum and 2 inches (51 mm) wide maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_3_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  In existing piers, clear pier space shall be permitted to be located perpendicular to the boat slip and shall extend the width of the boat slip, where the facility has at least one boat slip complying with 1003.3, and further compliance with 1003.3 would result in a reduction in the number of boat slips available or result in a reduction of the widths of existing slips.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1003.3.1 Boat Slip Clearance Exception 3. Where the conditions in exception 3 are satisfied, existing facilities are only required to have one accessible boat slip with a pier clearance which runs the length of the slip. All other accessible slips are allowed to have the required pier clearance at the head of the slip. Under this exception, at piers with perpendicular boat slips, the width of most “finger piers” will remain unchanged. However, where mooring systems for floating piers are replaced as part of pier alteration projects, an opportunity may exist for increasing accessibility.  Piers may be reconfigured to allow an increase in the number of wider finger piers, and serve as accessible boat slips.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1003.3.1 Boat Slip Clearance"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB119.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Las holguras del muelle se muestran en la vista de plano.  Los resbalones de bote accesibles son servidos por un espacio de muelle despejado de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de largo como mínimo y al menos tan largo como el bote accesible se desliza.  Cada 10 pies (3050 mm) máximo de borde lineal del muelle que sirve a los resbalones accesibles del barco contiene al menos una abertura transparente continua de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de largo mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Pier clearances are shown in plan view.  Accessible boat slips are served by clear pier space 60 inches (1525 mm) long minimum and at least as long as the accessible boat slips.  Every 10 feet (3050 mm) maximum of linear pier edge serving the accessible boat slips contains at least one continuous clear opening 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum long.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
