An elevation drawing shows pier edge protection that is 4 inches (100 mm) high maximum and 2 inches (51 mm) thick maximum. 

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
    %}
<h4 id="ada-1003_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1003.3.2 Boarding Pier Clearances[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Boarding piers at boat launch ramps shall provide clear pier space 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and shall extend the full length of the boarding pier.  Every 10 feet (3050 mm) maximum of linear pier edge shall contain at least one continuous clear opening 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_3_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  The clear pier space shall be permitted to be 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum for a length of 24 inches (610 mm) maximum provided that multiple 36 inch (915 mm) wide segments are separated by segments that are 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and 60 inches (1525 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1003_3_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Edge protection shall be permitted at the continuous clear openings provided that it is 4 inches (100 mm) high maximum and 2 inches (51 mm) wide maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1003.3.2 Boarding Pier Clearances.  These requirements do not establish a minimum length for accessible boarding piers at boat launch ramps.  The accessible boarding pier should have a length at least equal to that of other boarding piers provided at the facility.  If no other boarding pier is provided, the pier would have a length equal to what would have been provided if no access requirements applied.  The entire length of accessible boarding piers would be required to comply with the same technical provisions that apply to accessible boat slips.  For example, at a launch ramp, if a 20 foot (6100 mm) long accessible boarding pier is provided, the entire 20 feet (6100 mm) must comply with the pier clearance requirements in 1003.3.  Likewise, if a 60 foot (18 m) long accessible boarding pier is provided, the pier clearance requirements in 1003.3 would apply to the entire 60 feet (18 m).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="last">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The following example applies to a boat launch ramp boarding pier:  A chain of floats is provided on a launch ramp to be used as a boarding pier which is required to be accessible by 1003.3.2.  At high water, the entire chain is floating and a transition plate connects the first float to the surface of the launch ramp.  As the water level decreases, segments of the chain end up resting on the launch ramp surface, matching the slope of the launch ramp.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1003.3.2 Boarding Pier Clearance"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB122.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Las holguras del muelle se muestran en la vista de plano.  El muelle de embarque accesible en una rampa de lanzamiento de botes tiene un espacio de muelle libre de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de largo como mínimo, la longitud completa del muelle de embarque.  Cada 10 pies (3050 mm) máximo de borde lineal del muelle contiene al menos una abertura transparente continua de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) de largo como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Pier clearances are shown in plan view.  Accessible boarding pier at a boat launch ramp has clear pier space 60 inches (1525 mm) long minimum, the full length of the boarding pier.  Every 10 feet (3050 mm) maximum of linear pier edge contains at least one continuous clear opening 60 inches (1525 mm) long minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
    text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1003.3.2 (Exception 1) Clear Pier Space Reduction at Boarding Piers"[-END TRANSLATE-]
    img-file= "ADA-AB123.gif"
    img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de plano muestra que el ancho del espacio del muelle libre puede ser de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho como mínimo para una longitud de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) como máximo, donde varios segmentos de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho están separados por segmentos claros de 60 por 60 pulgadas (1525 por 1525 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows that the width of the clear pier space can be 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum for a length of 24 inches (610 mm) maximum where multiple 36 inch (915 mm) wide segments are separated by clear segments 60 by 60 inches (1525 by 1525 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
    %}
    {% include_cached figure-caption.html
        text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1003.3.2 (Exception 2) Edge Protection at Boarding Piers"[-END TRANSLATE-]
        img-file= "ADA-AB124.gif"
        img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación muestra la protección del borde del muelle que es de 4 pulgadas (100 mm) de alto máximo y 2 pulgadas (51 mm) de espesor máximo"[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing shows pier edge protection that is 4 inches (100 mm) high maximum and 2 inches (51 mm) thick maximum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
        %}

<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1004 Exercise Machines and Equipment[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1004_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1004.1 Clear Floor Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Exercise machines and equipment shall have a clear floor space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]positioned for transfer or for use by an individual seated in a wheelchair. Clear floor or ground spaces required at exercise machines and equipment shall be permitted to overlap.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1004.1 Clear Floor Space.  One clear floor or ground space is permitted to be shared between two pieces of exercise equipment.  To optimize space use, designers should carefully consider layout options such as connecting ends of the row and center aisle spaces.  The position of the clear floor space may vary greatly depending on the use of the equipment or machine.  For example, to provide access to a shoulder press machine, clear floor space next to the seat would be appropriate to allow for transfer.  Clear floor space for a bench press machine designed for use by an individual seated in a wheelchair, however, will most likely be centered on the operating mechanisms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005 Fishing Piers and Platforms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1005_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.1 Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving fishing piers and platforms, including gangways and floating piers, shall comply with Chapter 4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1005_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Accessible routes serving floating fishing piers and platforms shall be permitted to use Exceptions 1, 2, 5, 6, 7 and 8 in 1003.2.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1005_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where the total length of the gangway or series of gangways serving as part of a required accessible route is 30 feet (9145 mm) minimum, gangways shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_2" class="navSectionLink">405.2</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-1005_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.2 Railings[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, railings, guards, or handrails shall comply with 1005.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1005_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.2.1 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least 25 percent of the railings, guards, or handrails shall be 34 inches (865 mm) maximum above the ground or deck surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where a guard complying with sections 1003.2.12.1 and 1003.2.12.2 of the International Building Code (2000 edition) or sections[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1012_2" class="navSectionLink">1012.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1012_3" class="navSectionLink">1012.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]of the International Building Code (2003 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1) is provided, the guard shall not be required to comply with 1005.2.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1005_2_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.2.1.1 Dispersion.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Railings, guards, or handrails required to comply with 1005.2.1 shall be dispersed throughout the fishing pier or platform.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1005.2.1.1 Dispersion.  Portions of the railings that are lowered to provide fishing opportunities for persons with disabilities must be located in a variety of locations on the fishing pier or platform to give people a variety of locations to fish.  Different fishing locations may provide varying water depths, shade (at certain times of the day), vegetation, and proximity to the shoreline or bank.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1005_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.3 Edge Protection[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where railings, guards, or handrails complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1005_2" class="navSectionLink">1005.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]are provided, edge protection complying with 1005.3.1 or 1005.3.2 shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1005.3 Edge Protection.  Edge protection is required only where railings, guards, or handrails are provided on a fishing pier or platform.  Edge protection will prevent wheelchairs or other mobility devices from slipping off the fishing pier or platform.  Extending the deck of the fishing pier or platform 12 inches (305 mm) where the 34 inch (865 mm) high railing is provided is an alternative design, permitting individuals using wheelchairs or other mobility devices to pull into a clear space and move beyond the face of the railing.  In such a design, curbs or barriers are not required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1005_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.3.1 Curb or Barrier[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Curbs or barriers shall extend 2 inches (51 mm) minimum above the surface of the fishing pier or platform.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1005_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.3.2 Extended Ground or Deck Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The ground or deck surface shall extend 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beyond the inside face of the railing.  Toe clearance shall be provided and shall be 30 inches (760 mm) wide minimum and 9 inches (230 mm) minimum above the ground or deck surface beyond the railing.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1005.3.2 Extended Ground or Deck Surface at Fishing Piers and Platforms"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB125.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación lateral y la figura (b) es un dibujo de elevación frontal de protección de borde en muelles de pesca. Cuando una barandilla o protector tiene un máximo de 34 pulgadas (865 mm) de altura, no se requiere protección de borde si la superficie de la cubierta se extiende 12 pulgadas (305 mm) como mínimo más allá de la cara interior de la barandilla.  El espacio libre de los dedos de los pies debe tener al menos 9 pulgadas (230 mm) de alto más allá de la barandilla y al menos 30 pulgadas (760 mm) de ancho"[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is a side elevation drawing and figure (b) is a front elevation drawing of edge protection at fishing piers. Where a railing or guard is 34 inches (865 mm) high maximum, edge protection is not required if the deck surface extends 12 inches (305 mm) minimum beyond the inside face of the railing.  Toe clearance must be at least 9 inches (230 mm) high beyond the railing and at least 30 inches (760 mm) wide.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-1005_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.4 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At each location where there are railings, guards, or handrails complying with 1005.2.1, a clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided. Where there are no railings, guards, or handrails, at least one clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305" class="navSectionLink">305</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on the fishing pier or platform.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1005_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1005.5 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304_3" class="navSectionLink">304.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on fishing piers and platforms.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1006 Golf Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1006_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1006.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Golf facilities shall comply with 1006.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1006_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1006.2 Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving teeing grounds, practice teeing grounds, putting greens, practice putting greens, teeing stations at driving ranges, course weather shelters, golf car rental areas, bag drop areas, and course toilet rooms shall comply with Chapter 4 and shall be 48 inches (1220 mm) wide minimum.  Where handrails are provided, accessible routes shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Handrails shall not be required on golf courses. Where handrails are provided on golf courses, the handrails shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>.</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1006.2 Accessible Routes.  The 48 inch (1220 mm) minimum width for the accessible route is necessary to ensure passage of a golf car on either the accessible route or the golf car passage.  This is important where the accessible route is used to connect the golf car rental area, bag drop areas, practice putting greens, practice teeing grounds, course toilet rooms, and course weather shelters.  These are areas outside the boundary of the golf course, but are areas where an individual using an adapted golf car may travel.  A golf car passage may not be substituted for other accessible routes to be located outside the boundary of the course.  For example, an accessible route connecting an accessible parking space to the entrance of a golf course clubhouse is not covered by this provision.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="last">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Providing a golf car passage will permit a person that uses a golf car to practice driving a golf ball from the same position and stance used when playing the game.  Additionally, the space required for a person using a golf car to enter and maneuver within the teeing stations required to be accessible should be considered.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div>
<h3 id="ada-1006_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1006.3 Golf Car Passages[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Golf car passages shall comply with 1006.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1006_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1006.3.1 Clear Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The clear width of golf car passages shall be 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1006_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1006.3.2 Barriers[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where curbs or other constructed barriers prevent golf cars from entering a fairway, openings 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum shall be provided at intervals not to exceed 75 yards (69 m).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1006_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1006.4 Weather Shelters[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum by 96 inches (2440 mm) minimum shall be provided within weather shelters.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1007 Miniature Golf Facilities[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1007_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1007.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Miniature golf facilities shall comply with 1007.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1007_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1007.2 Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving holes on miniature golf courses shall comply with Chapter 4.  Accessible routes located on playing surfaces of miniature golf holes shall be permitted to use the exceptions in 1007.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1007_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Playing surfaces shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302_2" class="navSectionLink">302.2</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1007_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where accessible routes intersect playing surfaces of holes, a 1 inch (25 mm) maximum curb shall be permitted for a width of 32 inches (815 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1007_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  A slope not steeper than 1:4 for a 4 inch (100 mm) maximum rise shall be permitted.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1007_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]4.  Ramp landing slopes specified by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_7_1" class="navSectionLink">405.7.1</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to be 1:20 maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1007_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]5.  Ramp landing length specified by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_7_3" class="navSectionLink">405.7.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to be 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1007_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]6.  Ramp landing size specified by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_7_4" class="navSectionLink">405.7.4</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to be 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum by 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1007_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]7.  Handrails shall not be required on holes.  Where handrails are provided on holes, the handrails shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>.</p>
<h3 id="ada-1007_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1007.3 Miniature Golf Holes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Miniature golf holes shall comply with 1007.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1007_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1007.3.1 Start of Play[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear floor or ground space 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum by 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum with slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be provided at the start of play.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1007_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1007.3.2 Golf Club Reach Range Area[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]All areas within holes where golf balls rest shall be within 36 inches (915 mm) maximum of a clear floor or ground space 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum having a running slope not steeper than 1:20.  The clear floor or ground space shall be served by an accessible route.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1007.3.2 Golf Club Reach Range Area.  The golf club reach range applies to all holes required to be accessible.  This includes accessible routes provided adjacent to or, where provided, on the playing surface of the hole.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1007.3.2 Golf Club Reach Range Area"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB126.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de plano muestra a una persona que usa una silla de ruedas alcanzando una pelota de golf.  El espacio para sillas de ruedas es de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) de largo como mínimo y 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho como mínimo, teniendo una pendiente de carrera no más pronunciada que 1:20.  La pelota de golf es de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) como máximo desde el espacio libre de la silla de ruedas."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows a person using a wheelchair reaching a golf ball.  The wheelchair space is 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum, having a running slope not steeper than 1:20.  The golf ball are is 36 inches (915 mm) maximum from the wheelchair clear space. 

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008 Play Areas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1008_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Play areas shall comply with 1008.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1008_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2 Accessible Routes[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving play areas shall comply with Chapter 4 and 1008.2 and shall be permitted to use the exceptions in 1008.2.1 through 1008.2.3.  Where accessible routes serve ground level play components, the vertical clearance shall be 80 inches high (2030 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.1 Ground Level and Elevated Play Components[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving ground level play components and elevated play components shall be permitted to use the exceptions in 1008.2.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Transfer systems complying with 1008.3 shall be permitted to connect elevated play components except where 20 or more elevated play components are provided no more than 25 percent of the elevated play components shall be permitted to be connected by transfer systems.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where transfer systems are provided, an elevated play component shall be permitted to connect to another elevated play component as part of an accessible route.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.2 Soft Contained Play Structures[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving soft contained play structures shall be permitted to use the exception in 1008.2.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Transfer systems complying with 1008.3 shall be permitted to be used as part of an accessible route.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.3 Water Play Components[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes serving water play components shall be permitted to use the exceptions in 1008.2.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Where the surface of the accessible route, clear floor or ground spaces, or turning spaces serving water play components is submerged, compliance with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-302" class="navSectionLink">302</a>, <a href="#ada-403_3" class="navSectionLink">403.3</a>, <a href="#ada-405_2" class="navSectionLink">405.2</a>, <a href="#ada-405_3" class="navSectionLink">405.3</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1008_2_6" class="navSectionLink">1008.2.6</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Transfer systems complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1008_3" class="navSectionLink">1008.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be permitted to connect elevated play components in water.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1008.2.3 Water Play Components.  Personal wheelchairs and mobility devices may not be appropriate for submerging in water when using play components in water.  Some may have batteries, motors, and electrical systems that when submerged in water may cause damage to the personal mobility device or wheelchair or may contaminate the water.  Providing an aquatic wheelchair made of non-corrosive materials and designed for access into the water will protect the water from contamination and avoid damage to personal wheelchairs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.4 Clear Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Accessible routes connecting play components shall provide a clear width complying with 1008.2.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_2_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.4.1  Ground Level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At ground level, the clear width of accessible routes shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_4_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  In play areas less than 1000 square feet (93 m2), the clear width of accessible routes shall be permitted to be 44 inches (1120 mm) minimum, if at least one turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304_3" class="navSectionLink">304.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is provided where the restricted accessible route exceeds 30 feet (9145 mm) in length.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_4_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  The clear width of accessible routes shall be permitted to be 36 inches (915 mm) minimum for a distance of 60 inches (1525 mm) maximum provided that multiple reduced width segments are separated by segments that are 60 inches (1525 mm) wide minimum and 60 inches (1525 mm) long minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_2_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.4.2  Elevated.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The clear width of accessible routes connecting elevated play components shall be 36 inches (915 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_4_2x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  The clear width of accessible routes connecting elevated play components shall be permitted to be reduced to 32 inches (815 mm) minimum for a distance of 24 inches (610 mm) maximum provided that reduced width segments are separated by segments that are 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum and 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_4_2x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  The clear width of transfer systems connecting elevated play components shall be permitted to be 24 inches (610 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_2_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.5 Ramps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Within play areas, ramps connecting ground level play components and ramps connecting elevated play components shall comply with 1008.2.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_2_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.5.1 Ground Level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ramp runs connecting ground level play components shall have a running slope not steeper than 1:16.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_2_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.5.2 Elevated.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The rise for any ramp run connecting elevated play components shall be 12 inches (305 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_2_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.5.3 Handrails.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where required on ramps serving play components, the handrails shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]except as modified by 1008.2.5.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_5_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Handrails shall not be required on ramps located within ground level use zones.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1008_2_5_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Handrail extensions shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-1008_2_5_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.5.3.1 Handrail Gripping Surfaces.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Handrail gripping surfaces with a circular cross section shall have an outside diameter of 0.95 inch (24 mm) minimum and 1.55 inches (39 mm) maximum.  Where the shape of the gripping surface is non-circular, the handrail shall provide an equivalent gripping surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h6 id="ada-1008_2_5_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.5.3.2 Handrail Height.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h6>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The top of handrail gripping surfaces shall be 20 inches (510 mm) minimum and 28 inches (710 mm) maximum above the ramp surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_2_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.6 Ground Surfaces[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ground surfaces on accessible routes, clear floor or ground spaces, and turning spaces shall comply with 1008.2.6.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1008.2.6 Ground Surfaces.  Ground surfaces must be inspected and maintained regularly to ensure continued compliance with the ASTM F 1951 standard.  The type of surface material selected and play area use levels will determine the frequency of inspection and maintenance activities.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_2_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.6.1 Accessibility.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ground surfaces shall comply with ASTM F 1951 (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1). Ground surfaces shall be inspected and maintained regularly and frequently to ensure continued compliance with ASTM F 1951.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_2_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.2.6.2 Use Zones.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ground surfaces located within use zones shall comply with ASTM F 1292 (1999 edition or 2004 edition) (incorporated by reference, see “Referenced Standards” in Chapter 1).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1008_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3 Transfer Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where transfer systems are provided to connect to elevated play components, transfer systems shall comply with 1008.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1008.3 Transfer Systems.  Where transfer systems are provided, consideration should be given to the distance between the transfer system and the elevated play components.  Moving between a transfer platform and a series of transfer steps requires extensive exertion for some children.  Designers should minimize the distance between the points where a child transfers from a wheelchair or mobility device and where the elevated play components are located.  Where elevated play components are used to connect to another elevated play component instead of an accessible route, careful consideration should be used in the selection of the play components used for this purpose.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.1 Transfer Platforms[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer platforms shall be provided where transfer is intended from wheelchairs or other mobility aids.  Transfer platforms shall comply with 1008.3.1.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_3_1_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.1.1 Size.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer platforms shall have level surfaces 14 inches (355 mm) deep minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_3_1_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.1.2 Height.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The height of transfer platforms shall be 11 inches (280 mm) minimum and 18 inches (455 mm) maximum measured to the top of the surface from the ground or floor surface.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_3_1_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.1.3 Transfer Space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A transfer space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305_2" class="navSectionLink">305.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305_3" class="navSectionLink">305.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided adjacent to the transfer platform.  The 48 inch (1220 mm) long minimum dimension of the transfer space shall be centered on and parallel to the 24 inch (610 mm) long minimum side of the transfer platform.  The side of the transfer platform serving the transfer space shall be unobstructed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_3_1_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.1.4 Transfer Supports.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one means of support for transferring shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1008.3.1 Transfer Platforms"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB127.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La Figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación que muestra una plataforma de transferencia con una altura de superficie de 11 a 18 pulgadas (280 a 455 mm) sobre el suelo.  La Figura (b) es una vista plana de la plataforma con una profundidad de 14 pulgadas (355 mm) como mínimo y un ancho de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) como mínimo.  Un espacio de tierra despejado que es de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) de largo como mínimo se centra en esta dimensión paralelo al lado sin obstrucciones de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) de largo mínimo de la plataforma de transferencia."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing showing a transfer platform with a surface height 11 to 18 inches (280 to 455 mm) above the ground.  Figure (b) is a plan view of the platform having a depth of 14 inches (355 mm) minimum and a width of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum.  A clear ground space that is 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum is centered on this dimension parallel to the 24 in (610 mm) minimum long unobstructed side of the transfer platform.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1008_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.2 Transfer Steps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer steps shall be provided where movement is intended from transfer platforms to levels with elevated play components required to be on accessible routes.  Transfer steps shall comply with 1008.3.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_3_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.2.1 Size.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer steps shall have level surfaces 14 inches (355 mm) deep minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_3_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.2.2 Height.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each transfer step shall be 8 inches (205 mm) high maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h5 id="ada-1008_3_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.3.2.3 Transfer Supports.[-END TRANSLATE-]</h5>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one means of support for transferring shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1008.3.2.3 Transfer Supports.  Transfer supports are required on transfer platforms and transfer steps to assist children when transferring.  Some examples of supports include a rope loop, a loop type handle, a slot in the edge of a flat horizontal or vertical member, poles or bars, or D rings on the corner posts.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1008.3.2 Transfer Steps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB128.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "La figura (a) es un dibujo de elevación de un paso de transferencia de 8 pulgadas (205 mm) de alto como máximo.  La Figura (b) es una vista plana de un paso de transferencia que tiene un mínimo de 14 pulgadas (355 mm) de profundidad y un mínimo de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) de largo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Figure (a) is an elevation drawing of a transfer step 8 inches (205 mm) high maximum.  Figure (b) is a plan view of a transfer step that is 14 inches (355 mm) deep minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) long minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-1008_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.4 Play Components[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ground level play components on accessible routes and elevated play components connected by ramps shall comply with 1008.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.4.1 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one turning space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-304" class="navSectionLink">304</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on the same level as play components.  Where swings are provided, the turning space shall be located immediately adjacent to the swing.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.4.2 Clear Floor or Ground Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Clear floor or ground space complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305_2" class="navSectionLink">305.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-305_3" class="navSectionLink">305.3</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided at play components.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<div class="advisory">
<p class="first">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1008.4.2 Clear Floor or Ground Space.  Clear floor or ground spaces, turning spaces, and accessible routes are permitted to overlap within play areas.  A specific location has not been designated for the clear floor or ground spaces or turning spaces, except swings, because each play component may require that the spaces be placed in a unique location.  Where play components include a seat or entry point, designs that provide for an unobstructed transfer from a wheelchair or other mobility device are recommended.  This will enhance the ability of children with disabilities to independently use the play component.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]When designing play components with manipulative or interactive features, consider appropriate reach ranges for children seated in wheelchairs.  The following table provides guidance on reach ranges for children seated in wheelchairs.  These dimensions apply to either forward or side reaches.  The reach ranges are appropriate for use with those play components that children seated in wheelchairs may access and reach.  Where transfer systems provide access to elevated play components, the reach ranges are not appropriate.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<table class="standards data"><caption>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Children’s Reach Ranges[-END TRANSLATE-]</caption>
<thead>
<tr><th scope="col">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Forward or Side Reach[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ages 3 and 4[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ages 5 through 8[-END TRANSLATE-]</th><th>[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Ages 9 through 12[-END TRANSLATE-]</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]High (maximum)[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
<td>36 in (915 mm)</td>
<td>40 in (1015 mm)</td>
<td>44 in (1120 mm)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Low (minimum)[-END TRANSLATE-]</td>
<td>20 in (510 mm)</td>
<td>18 in (455 mm)</td>
<td>16 in (405 mm)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h4 id="ada-1008_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.4.3 Play Tables[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where play tables are provided, knee clearance 24 inches (610 mm) high minimum, 17 inches deep (430 mm) minimum, and 30 inches (760 mm) wide minimum shall be provided.  The tops of rims, curbs, or other obstructions shall be 31 inches (785 mm) high maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Play tables designed and constructed primarily for children 5 years and younger shall not be required to provide knee clearance where the clear floor or ground space required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-1008_4_2" class="navSectionLink">1008.4.2</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]is arranged for a parallel approach.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.4.4 Entry Points and Seats[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where play components require transfer to entry points or seats, the entry points or seats shall be 11 inches (280 mm) minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) maximum from the clear floor or ground space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Entry points of slides shall not be required to comply with 1008.4.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1008_4_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1008.4.5 Transfer Supports[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where play components require transfer to entry points or seats, at least one means of support for transferring shall be provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-100">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009 Swimming Pools, Wading Pools, and Spas[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1009_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.1 General[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Where provided, pool lifts, sloped entries, transfer walls, transfer systems, and pool stairs shall comply with 1009.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1009_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2 Pool Lifts[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pool lifts shall comply with 1009.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1009.2 Pool Lifts.  There are a variety of seats available on pool lifts ranging from sling seats to those that are preformed or molded.  Pool lift seats with backs will enable a larger population of persons with disabilities to use the lift.  Pool lift seats that consist of materials that resist corrosion and provide a firm base to transfer will be usable by a wider range of people with disabilities.  Additional options such as armrests, head rests, seat belts, and leg support will enhance accessibility and better accommodate people with a wide range of disabilities.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.1 Pool Lift Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pool lifts shall be located where the water level does not exceed 48 inches (1220 mm).[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1009_2_1x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Where the entire pool depth is greater than 48 inches (1220 mm), compliance with 1009.2.1 shall not be required.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1009_2_1x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where multiple pool lift locations are provided, no more than one pool lift shall be required to be located in an area where the water level is 48 inches (1220 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.2 Seat Location[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]In the raised position, the centerline of the seat shall be located over the deck and 16 inches (405 mm) minimum from the edge of the pool.  The deck surface between the centerline of the seat and the pool edge shall have a slope not steeper than 1:48.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.2.2 Pool Lift Seat Location"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB129.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de plano muestra el asiento elevador de la piscina ubicado sobre la cubierta a 16 pulgadas como mínimo desde el borde de la piscina, medido hasta la línea central del asiento."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows pool lift seat located over the deck 16 inches minimum from the edge of the pool, measured to the seat centerline.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.3 Clear Deck Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]On the side of the seat opposite the water, a clear deck space shall be provided parallel with the seat.  The space shall be 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum and shall extend forward 48 inches (1220 mm) minimum from a line located 12 inches (305 mm) behind the rear edge of the seat.  The clear deck space shall have a slope not steeper than 1:48.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.2.3 Clear Deck Space at Pool Lifts"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB130.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista en planta del espacio despejado de la cubierta en los ascensores de la piscina muestra un espacio de cubierta clara de 36 pulgadas (915 mm) de ancho como mínimo y un mínimo de 48 pulgadas (1220 mm) de largo que se muestra paralelo al asiento, en el lado del asiento opuesto al agua.  La longitud de 48 pulgadas se extiende desde una línea ubicada a 12 pulgadas detrás del borde trasero del asiento."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view of clear deck space at pool lifts shows a clear deck space 36 inches (915 mm) wide minimum and 48 inches (1220 mm) long minimum is shown parallel to the seat, on the side of the seat opposite the water.  The 48-inch length extends from a line located 12 inches behind the rear edge of the seat.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.4 Seat Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The height of the lift seat shall be designed to allow a stop at 16 inches (405 mm) minimum to 19 inches (485 mm) maximum measured from the deck to the top of the seat surface when in the raised (load) position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.2.4 Pool Lift Seat Height"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB131.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación muestra que la altura del asiento de elevación de la piscina es de 16 a 19 pulgadas (405 a 485 mm) medida desde la cubierta hasta la parte superior de la superficie del asiento cuando está en la posición elevada (carga)."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing shows pool lift seat height to be 16 to 19 inches (405 to 485 mm) measured from the deck to the top of the seat surface when in the raised (load) position.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.5 Seat Width[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The seat shall be 16 inches (405 mm) wide minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.6 Footrests and Armrests[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Footrests shall be provided and shall move with the seat.  If provided, the armrest positioned opposite the water shall be removable or shall fold clear of the seat when the seat is in the raised (load) position.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Footrests shall not be required on pool lifts provided in spas.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.7 Operation[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The lift shall be capable of unassisted operation from both the deck and water levels. Controls and operating mechanisms shall be unobstructed when the lift is in use and shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-309_4" class="navSectionLink">309.4</a>.</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1009.2.7 Operation.  Pool lifts must be capable of unassisted operation from both the deck and water levels.  This will permit a person to call the pool lift when the pool lift is in the opposite position.  It is extremely important for a person who is swimming alone to be able to call the pool lift when it is in the up position so he or she will not be stranded in the water for extended periods of time awaiting assistance.  The requirement for a pool lift to be independently operable does not preclude assistance from being provided.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_8">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.8 Submerged Depth[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The lift shall be designed so that the seat will submerge to a water depth of 18 inches (455 mm) minimum below the stationary water level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.2.8 Pool Lift Submerged Depth"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB132.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación muestra un elevador de piscina con la superficie del asiento sumergida a una profundidad de agua de 18 pulgadas (455 mm) como mínimo por debajo del nivel de agua estacionario."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing shows a pool lift with the surface of the seat submerged to a water depth of 18 inches (455 mm) minimum below the stationary water level.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_2_9">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.2.9 Lifting Capacity[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Single person pool lifts shall have a weight capacity of 300 pounds. (136 kg) minimum and be capable of sustaining a static load of at least one and a half times the rated load.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1009.2.9 Lifting Capacity.  Single person pool lifts must be capable of supporting a minimum weight of 300 pounds (136 kg) and sustaining a static load of at least one and a half times the rated load.  Pool lifts should be provided that meet the needs of the population they serve.  Providing a pool lift with a weight capacity greater than 300 pounds (136 kg) may be advisable.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h3 id="ada-1009_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.3 Sloped Entries[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Sloped entries shall comply with 1009.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1009.3 Sloped Entries.  Personal wheelchairs and mobility devices may not be appropriate for submerging in water. Some may have batteries, motors, and electrical systems that when submerged in water may cause damage to the personal mobility device or wheelchair or may contaminate the pool water. Providing an aquatic wheelchair made of non-corrosive materials and designed for access into the water will protect the water from contamination and avoid damage to personal wheelchairs or other mobility aids.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_3_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.3.1 Sloped Entries[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Sloped entries shall comply with Chapter 4 except as modified in 1009.3.1 through 1009.3.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Where sloped entries are provided, the surfaces shall not be required to be slip resistant.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_3_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.3.2 Submerged Depth[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Sloped entries shall extend to a depth of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum and 30 inches (760 mm) maximum below the stationary water level. Where landings are required by[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-405_7" class="navSectionLink">405.7</a>, [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]at least one landing shall be located 24 inches (610 mm) minimum and 30 inches (760 mm) maximum below the stationary water level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  In wading pools, the sloped entry and landings, if provided, shall extend to the deepest part of the wading pool.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.3.2 Sloped Entry Submerged Depth"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB133.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación muestra una entrada inclinada con una profundidad sumergida de 24 a 30 pulgadas (610 a 760 mm) por debajo del nivel estacionario del agua en el aterrizaje."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing shows a sloped entry with a submerged depth of 24 to 30 inches (610 to 760 mm) below the stationary water level at the landing.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_3_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.3.3 Handrails[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least two handrails complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on the sloped entry.  The clear width between required handrails shall be 33 inches (840 mm) minimum and 38 inches (965 mm) maximum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1009_3_3x1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTIONS:  1.  Handrail extensions specified by 505.10.1 shall not be required at the bottom landing serving a sloped entry.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1009_3_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]2.  Where a sloped entry is provided for wave action pools, leisure rivers, sand bottom pools, and other pools where user access is limited to one area, the handrails shall not be required to comply with the clear width requirements of 1009.3.3.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions" id="ada-1009_3_3x">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]3.  Sloped entries in wading pools shall not be required to provide handrails complying with 1009.3.3.  If provided, handrails on sloped entries in wading pools shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-505" class="navSectionLink">505</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.3.3 Handrails for Sloped Entry"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB134.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación de una entrada inclinada muestra pasamanos en ambos lados que proporcionan un ancho claro de 33 a 38 pulgadas (840 a 965 mm)."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing of a sloped entry shows handrails on both sides that provide a clear width of 33 to 38 inches (840 to 965 mm).

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-1009_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.4 Transfer Walls[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer walls shall comply with 1009.4.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_4_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.4.1 Clear Deck Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A clear deck space of 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum by 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum with a slope not steeper than 1:48 shall be provided at the base of the transfer wall.  Where one grab bar is provided, the clear deck space shall be centered on the grab bar.  Where two grab bars are provided, the clear deck space shall be centered on the clearance between the grab bars.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.4.1 Clear Deck Space at Transfer Walls"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB135.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de planta muestra un espacio de cubierta despejado de 60 por 60 pulgadas (1525 por 1525 mm) mínimo adyacente a una pared de transferencia.  La figura (a) muestra este espacio centrado en una barra de agarre.  La figura (b) muestra este espacio centrado en el espacio libre entre dos barras de agarre."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows clear deck space of 60 by 60 inches (1525 by 1525 mm) minimum adjacent to a transfer wall.  Figure (a) shows this space centered at one grab bar.  Figure (b) shows this space centered on the clearance between two grab bars.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_4_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.4.2 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The height of the transfer wall shall be 16 inches (405 mm) minimum and 19 inches (485 mm) maximum measured from the deck.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.4.2 Transfer Wall Height"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB136.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación muestra la altura de una pared de transferencia de 16 a 19 pulgadas (405 a 485 mm) medida desde la cubierta."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing shows the height of a transfer wall as 16 to 19 inches (405 to 485 mm) measured from the deck.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_4_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.4.3 Wall Depth and Length[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The depth of the transfer wall shall be 12 inches (305 mm) minimum and 16 inches (405 mm) maximum. The length of the transfer wall shall be 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum and shall be centered on the clear deck space.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.4.3 Depth and Length of Transfer Walls"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB137.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de planta muestra una pared de transferencia con una profundidad de 12 a 16 pulgadas (305 a 405 mm) y una longitud de 60 pulgadas (1525 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows a transfer wall with a depth of 12 to 16 inches (305 to 405 mm) and a length of 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_4_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.4.4 Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Surfaces of transfer walls shall not be sharp and shall have rounded edges.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_4_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.4.5 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one grab bar complying with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]shall be provided on the transfer wall.  Grab bars shall be perpendicular to the pool wall and shall extend the full depth of the transfer wall.  The top of the gripping surface shall be 4 inches (100 mm) minimum and 6 inches (150 mm) maximum above transfer walls.  Where one grab bar is provided, clearance shall be 24 inches (610 mm) minimum on both sides of the grab bar. Where two grab bars are provided, clearance between grab bars shall be 24 inches (610 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Grab bars on transfer walls shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609_4" class="navSectionLink">609.4</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.4.5 Grab Bars for Transfer Walls"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB138.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Las barras de agarre en las paredes de transferencia se muestran perpendiculares a la pared de la piscina y extendiendo toda la profundidad de la pared de transferencia.  La figura (a) muestra en la vista de plano dos barras de agarre con un espacio libre entre ellas de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) como mínimo.  La figura (b) muestra en la vista de plano una barra de agarre con un espacio libre de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) como mínimo en ambos lados.  La figura (c) muestra en la elevación lateral una altura de la superficie de agarre de la barra de agarre de 4 a 6 pulgadas (100 a 150 mm) por encima de la pared, medida hasta la parte superior de la superficie de agarre."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Grab bars at transfer walls are shown perpendicular to the pool wall and extending the full depth of the transfer wall.  Figure (a) shows in plan view two grab bars with a clearance between them of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum.  Figure (b) shows in plan view one grab bar with a clearance of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum on both sides.  Figure (c) shows in side elevation a height of the grab bar gripping surface 4 to 6 inches (100 to 150 mm) above the wall, measured to the top of the gripping surface.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-1009_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5 Transfer Systems[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer systems shall comply with 1009.5.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_5_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5.1 Transfer Platform[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A transfer platform shall be provided at the head of each transfer system.  Transfer platforms shall provide 19 inches (485 mm) minimum clear depth and 24 inches (610 mm) minimum clear width.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.5.1 Size of Transfer Platform"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB139.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de plano muestra una plataforma de transferencia en la parte superior de una serie de escalones de transferencia que conducen al agua.  La plataforma en la parte superior tiene una profundidad clara de 19 pulgadas (485 mm) como mínimo y un ancho claro de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows a transfer platform at the top of a series of transfer steps leading down into the water.  The platform at the top has a clear depth of 19 inches (485 mm) minimum and a clear width of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_5_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5.2 Transfer Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A transfer space of 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum by 60 inches (1525 mm) minimum with a slope not steeper than 1:48 shall be provided at the base of the transfer platform surface and shall be centered along a 24 inch (610 mm) minimum side of the transfer platform.  The side of the transfer platform serving the transfer space shall be unobstructed.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.5.2 Clear Deck Space at Transfer Platform"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB140.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de planta muestra un espacio de cubierta despejado de 60 por 60 pulgadas (1525 por 1525 mm) como mínimo en la base de la superficie de la plataforma de transferencia que se centra a lo largo de un lado mínimo sin obstrucciones de 24 pulgadas de la plataforma de transferencia."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows clear deck space 60 by 60 inches (1525 by 1525 mm) minimum at the base of the transfer platform surface that is centered along a 24 inch minimum unobstructed side of the transfer platform.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_5_3">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5.3 Height[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The height of the transfer platform shall comply with 1009.4.2.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_5_4">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5.4 Transfer Steps[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Transfer step height shall be 8 inches (205 mm) maximum. The surface of the bottom tread shall extend to a water depth of 18 inches (455 mm) minimum below the stationary water level.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="advisory">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Advisory 1009.5.4 Transfer Steps.  Where possible, the height of the transfer step should be minimized to decrease the distance an individual is required to lift up or move down to reach the next step to gain access.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.5.4 Transfer Steps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB141.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Un dibujo de elevación muestra los pasos del sistema de transferencia que son de 8 pulgadas (205 mm) de alto máximo que se extienden a una profundidad de agua de 18 pulgadas (455 mm) como mínimo por debajo del nivel de agua estacionario."[-END TRANSLATE-]

An elevation drawing shows transfer system steps that are 8 inches (205 mm) high maximum which extend to a water depth of 18 inches (455 mm) minimum below the stationary water level.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_5_5">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5.5 Surface[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The surface of the transfer system shall not be sharp and shall have rounded edges.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_5_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5.6 Size[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Each transfer step shall have a tread clear depth of 14 inches (355 mm) minimum and 17 inches (430 mm) maximum and shall have a tread clear width of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.5.6 Size of Transfer Steps"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB142.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Una vista de plano muestra un sistema de transferencia con cada paso que tiene una profundidad clara de la banda de rodadura de 14 a 17 pulgadas (355 a 430 mm) y un ancho libre de la banda de rodadura de 24 pulgadas (610 mm) como mínimo."[-END TRANSLATE-]

A plan view shows a transfer system with each step having a tread clear depth of 14 to 17 inches (355 to 430 mm) and a tread clear width of 24 inches (610 mm) minimum.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h4 id="ada-1009_5_7">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.5.7 Grab Bars[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]At least one grab bar on each transfer step and the transfer platform or a continuous grab bar serving each transfer step and the transfer platform shall be provided.  Where a grab bar is provided on each step, the tops of gripping surfaces shall be 4 inches (100 mm) minimum and 6 inches (150 mm) maximum above each step and transfer platform. Where a continuous grab bar is provided, the top of the gripping surface shall be 4 inches (100 mm) minimum and 6 inches (150 mm) maximum above the step nosing and transfer platform.  Grab bars shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609" class="navSectionLink">609</a> [-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]and be located on at least one side of the transfer system.  The grab bar located at the transfer platform shall not obstruct transfer.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Grab bars on transfer systems shall not be required to comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-609_4" class="navSectionLink">609.4</a>.</p>
{% include_cached figure-caption.html
text=[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Figure 1009.5.7 Grab Bars"[-END TRANSLATE-]
img-file= "ADA-AB143.gif"
img-alt=[-ALT BEGIN TRANSLATE-] "Dos dibujos de elevación muestran barras de agarre en los sistemas de transferencia.  La Figura (a) muestra barras de agarre individuales en la plataforma y cada paso con la parte superior de la superficie de agarre de 4 a 6 pulgadas (100 a 150 mm) por encima de cada paso y plataforma de transferencia.  La figura (b) muestra una barra de agarre continua con la parte superior de la superficie de agarre de 4 a 6 pulgadas (100 a 150) por encima de la plataforma de nariz y transferencia de escalones."[-END TRANSLATE-]

Two elevation drawings show grab bars at transfer systems.  Figure (a) shows individual grab bars on the platform and each step with the top of the gripping surface 4 to 6 inches (100 to 150 mm) above each step and transfer platform.  Figure (b) shows a continuous grab bar with the top of the gripping surface 4 to 6 inches (100 to 150) above the step nosing and transfer platform.

"[-END TRANSLATE-]
%}
<h3 id="ada-1009_6">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.6 Pool Stairs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pool stairs shall comply with 1009.6.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_6_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.6.1 Pool Stairs[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]Pool stairs shall comply with[-END TRANSLATE-] <a href="#ada-504" class="navSectionLink">504</a>.</p>
<p class="standards exceptions">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]EXCEPTION:  Pool step riser heights shall not be required to be 4 inches (100 mm) high minimum and 7 inches (180 mm) high maximum provided that riser heights are uniform.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h4 id="ada-1009_6_2">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1009.6.2 Handrails[-END TRANSLATE-]</h4>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]The width between handrails shall be 20 inches (510 mm) minimum and 24 inches (610 mm) maximum.  Handrail extensions required by 505.10.3 shall not be required on pool stairs.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
<h2 id="ada-101">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1010 Shooting Facilities with Firing Positions[-END TRANSLATE-]</h2>
<h3 id="ada-1010_1">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]1010.1 Turning Space[-END TRANSLATE-]</h3>
<p class="standards">[-BEGIN TRANSLATE-]A circular turning space 60 inches (1525 mm) diameter minimum with slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be provided at shooting facilities with firing positions.[-END TRANSLATE-]</p>
</div> <!--close #adaCh10-->
</div> <!--close .standards-->
